var contents = new Array("   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  2  1  2026-02-06T07:30:00Z  2026-02-06T07:31:00Z  1  8  52  1  1  59  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rACCOUNTS PAYABLE APPLICATION    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Accounts Payable Application","topics\\Accounts_Payable_Application.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  19  105  2026-02-06T07:32:00Z  2026-02-24T10:00:00Z  8  1111  6333  52  14  7430  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Accounts Payable Application\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Accounts PayableApplication from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know thesupplier’s code, enter it directly in the Supplier Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheDocument No. field is read-only andwill be automatically assigned when the record is saved.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Whena SupplierCode is selected, the system automatically retrieves anddisplays all outstandingor floating payable documents such as Debit memo, Credit memoand Purchase invoice or other related document to the chosen supplier in the Create Application Grid.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOnlydocuments with a remaining balance or unapplied status are shown. Fully paid orclosed documents are excluded from the list\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Xbutton next to the Doc.ID if you want to apply the entireremaining balance of the selected document. Alternatively, youcan directly enter the desired amountin the AppliedAmount column. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleScenario (based on the picture above, 6.a.):\n\r\n\rInthis example, we need to offset or deduct DM#1 against PI#143.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; For DM#1:\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the amount in the AppliedAmount column as a negative value.\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This indicates that the debit memo isbeing deductedfrom the invoice.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; ForPI#143:\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the same amount in the AppliedAmount column as a positive value.\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This ensures the credit is applied tothe invoice.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Result:\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The total amount will equal zero,confirming that DM#1 has been fully offset against PI#143.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Note:\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Theamount to be entered does not necessarily need to be the full amount of theinvoice. It may be part of the invoice amount\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Multiple documents can be applied. Thismeans that multiple debit memos and/or purchase adjustment document can beapplied to multiple purchase invoices or receiving report.\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The system will not allow you tosave the transaction unless the total applied amount iszero.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe SearchDocument button to quickly look up a specific document, such asinvoices, debit memos, or other relevant documents, without having to scrollthrough the entire list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe Remarksfield to enter additional notes, comments, specific instructions or reason ofoffsetting, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. A confirmationmessage may appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to post therecord or No to cancel the action. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is posted, the system will automatically updatethe SupplierLedger and the Aging of Payables.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is cancelled, the systemwill automatically updatethe SupplierLedger and the Aging of Payables.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Click Other Information button to view the cancellation details.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Accounts Payable Application","topics\\Accounts_Payable_Application_creating.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  3  9  2026-02-06T10:40:00Z  2026-02-10T02:06:00Z  3  415  2369  19  5  2779  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing an Accounts Payable Application\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Accounts Payable Application windowwill appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: This field is disabled and not used in this module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosetransactions whosedocument number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All transactionsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier:If you want to filter by a specific supplier, click the magnifying glass iconto open the supplier list window and select the desired supplier. If you leaveit empty, all suppliers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the transactions that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correcttransactions and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall transactions that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Accounts Payable Application window.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing an Accounts Payable Application","topics\\Accounts_Payable_Application_printing.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  4  5  2026-02-06T10:23:00Z  2026-02-10T01:59:00Z  2  120  689  5  1  808  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in theAccounts Payable Application\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Accounts PayableApplication from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button from Search Document Number window to display the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II.	Searching for a Transaction in the Accounts Payable Application","topics\\Accounts_Payable_Application_searching.htm","        Business Box - SQL       version      ACCOUNTS RECEIVABLES       APPLICATION\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Accounts Receivables Application","topics\\Accounts_Receivable_Application.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  14  91  2026-02-10T02:22:00Z  2026-02-24T09:53:00Z  8  1110  6333  52  14  7429  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Accounts ReceivableApplication\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Accounts ReceivableApplication from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the customer list, or if you know thecustomer’s code, enter it directly in the Customer Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheDocument No. field is read-only andwill be automatically assigned when the record is saved.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Whena CustomerCode is selected, the system automatically retrieves anddisplays all outstandingor floating Receivable documents such as Debit memo, Creditmemo and Sales invoice or other related document to the chosen customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOnlydocuments with a remaining balance or unapplied status are shown. Fully paid orclosed documents are excluded from the list\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Xbutton next to the Doc.ID if you want to apply the entireremaining balance of the selected document. Alternatively, youcan directly enter the desired amountin the AppliedAmount column. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleScenario (based on the picture above, 6.a.):\n\r\n\rInthis example, we need to offset or deduct CM#1 against SI#4.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; For CM#1:\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the amount in the AppliedAmount column as a negative value.\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This indicates that the credit memo isbeing deductedfrom the invoice.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; ForSI#4:\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the same amount in the AppliedAmount column as a positive value.\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This ensures the credit is applied tothe invoice.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Result:\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The total amount will equal zero,confirming that CM#1 has been fully offset against SI#4.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Note:\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Theamount to be entered does not necessarily need to be the full amount of theinvoice. It may be part of the invoice amount\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Multiple documents can be applied. Thismeans that multiple debit memos and/or Sales adjustment document can be appliedto multiple Sales invoices.\n\r\n\ro&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The system will not allow youto save the transaction unless the total appliedamount is zero.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe SearchDocument button to quickly look up a specific document, such asinvoices, debit memos, or other relevant documents, without having to scrollthrough the entire list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe Remarksfield to enter additional notes, comments, specific instructions or reason ofoffsetting, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. A confirmationmessage may appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to post therecord or No to cancel the action. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r                        Note:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is posted, the system will automatically updatethe CustomerLedger and the Aging of Receivables.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is cancelled, the systemwill automatically updatethe CustomerLedger and the Aging of Receivables.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Click Other Information button to view the cancellation details.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Accounts Receivable Application","topics\\Accounts_Receivable_Application_creating.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  61  78  2025-10-06T02:21:00Z  2025-10-30T13:49:00Z  11  910  5190  43  12  6088  16.00        Print  110  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rAGENT   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Agent module is where you enter allyour sales agents and the pertinent information about them. This includesdetails such as the agent’s name, contact information, address and otherrelevant data. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding an Agent\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r Select     Agent from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the AgentCode and Agent Name in their respective fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In General Section: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.1Enter the E-mail address, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.2&nbsp;Enter the Address, Contact Person, Telephone Number&nbsp;,&nbsp; and Fax Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.3&nbsp;Select the&nbsp;Area   , Team and&nbsp; enter the Zip Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding an Address:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the magnifyingglass besides the Address label and the Address List window will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Add button to add a new address.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Address, Contact Person, TelephoneNumber and Fax Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the&nbsp;Area and enter the Zip Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To addanother address follow steps&nbsp;a to d.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rf.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Close button toclose the window.&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inthe Details section (Transaction Default Values):\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSelect the Cost Center, if any.If you know the Cost Center Code, you may enter it directly in the Cost Centerfield. If the Cost Center Code does not exist the lists of Cost Center willappear:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; These are the ways of selecting costcenter from the list\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type the first few characters of the CostCenter Code in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type the first few characters of the CostCenter Description in the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type a specific code or word in the spaceprovided (3) to filter the Cost Center Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Browse through the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrow keys.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button in the Navigation Toolbar to save the record. Click the Cancelbutton to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Edit button toedit the record. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Delete button todelete the record. Deletion will only be allowed if thesaid record has not been used in other modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Updating Agent Status:\n\r\n\r\n\rTo update the record of an agent who has resigned or is no longer active,choose Inactivefrom the Statusdropdown list in the Agent Module, then click Saveto apply the changes.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rInformation inputted can be selected in the A/R SummaryEntry, Sales Invoice and Cash Receipt modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r“SAVETO “ Feature\n\r\n\rThe **Save To**feature allows you to copy or extract agent information to other modules suchas Customer, Supplier, Employee or Collector. This ensures consistency of dataacross modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r(e.g. Save to Customer)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the SaveTo button and the Save To window will appear. Select the module to whichthe Agent Information will be extracted. To select, tick the circle besides theCustomer, Supplier, Employee or Collector labels. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the OK button tosave the Agent information. Click the Cancel button toclose the window. When you select Customer and click the OK button the Customermodule will open.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSince all pertinent information in the Agent wasextracted, then all you have to do is to review that information.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r Click the Save button to     save the record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching an Agent\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of agents will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Agent from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Codein the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type the first few characters of the Name in the spaceprovided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type a specific code or word in thespace provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Browse through the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrow keys or scroll wheel of optical mouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After selecting the agent, click the OKbutton. The agent’s details will be displayed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r","Agent","topics\\Agent.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  4  2  2026-01-28T10:05:00Z  2026-02-05T07:28:00Z  1  115  661  5  1  775  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rA/P SUMMARY ENTRY    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe A/PSummary Entry module allows you to record adjustments related to accountspayable transactions. This module is typically used when a transaction containsincorrect or incomplete information, such as when the unit cost has beenunderstated or overstated, or when other payable amounts need to be corrected.By using this module, users can properly adjust existing A/P records to ensurethat financial data remains accurate and up to date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIn addition to making corrections, theA/P Summary Entry module is also used to establish the beginning balance for asupplier or vendor when setting up new records or transitioning from anothersystem, ensuring that all outstanding payables are properly reflected in thesystem.","AP Summary Entry","topics\\AP_Summary_Entry.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  39  238  2026-01-22T09:20:00Z  2026-02-24T09:59:00Z  22  2747  15664  130  36  18375  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use AP Summary Entry\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select AP Summary Entryfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know thesupplier’s code, enter it directly in the Supplier Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea supplier is selected, the Payable Tofield is automatically updated based on the Supplier Master Files. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Payable To field can be manually edited when necessary. Users may type directly intothis field to specify a different payee name,such as:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A differentregistered business name\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Abranch name or alternate payee\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Aspecific individual authorized to receive payment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThisflexibility allows users to handle special payment arrangements while stillusing the same supplier record.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTerms field is automatically setbased on the supplier’s default terms. You can change it and select differentterms if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SelectTransaction Type, this field isautomatically set based on the supplier’s default transaction type configuredin the Supplier Module. It can be modified if necessary; however, it is arequired field and cannot be left blank. This field is used to identify thetransaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;EnterP.O. number, If needed\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. It is automatically filled with thesupplier’s address. If the address is different from default address, you canselect another address. Click the magnifying glass icon tosee available addresses. If the address is not listed, you can add it in the Suppliermodule.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Use the Particulars field to enter additionalnotes, comments, or specific instructions related to the A/P Summary Entryif needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. If the amount is VAT-inclusive, tick the VAT Inclusive checkbox to ensure correcttax computation.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Select the Expanded Withholding Tax (EWT) code as needed. The system willdisplay the corresponding rate and automatically compute the EWT amount.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Enter the Amount as a positive value toincreases the payables, or enter the Amount as a negative value to reductionsin payables.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. Enter the Discount Rate (%) to be applied to the Amount. The system willautomatically calculate the corresponding DiscountAmount. If a specific discount value is preferred, you may enter itdirectly in the Discount Amount field\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. Enter any additional adjustment amount,if needed. \n\r\n\r§&nbsp;A positivevalue increasesthe net amount.\n\r\n\r§&nbsp;Anegative value decreasesthe net amount.\n\r\n\r§&nbsp;Thisfield can only be used if the original amount entered is positive.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNetAmount – This isthe subtotal after applying discounts and adjustments. It is automaticallycomputed by the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. The Currency/Ratefields are automatically filled using the supplier’s default currency. You maychange these fields if the transaction requires a different currency.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. The highlighted section displays thetransaction values based on the selected currency and their equivalent amountsin Philippine Peso (PHP). This allows the user to view both the originalcurrency values and their converted peso amounts side by side. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TotalAmount – Refers tothe final payable amount or amount due.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Applied Amount – Total amount that has been paid orcredited.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Balance – The remaining amount due.\n\r\n\rFormula:\n\rBalance= Total Amount – Applied Amount\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r20. To modify an existingrecord, click the Edit button. This will allow you to update theinformation as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes to applythem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means alltransactions will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the document associated with that identifier, while still applying anyother filters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosetransactions whosedocument number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All transactionsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier:If you want to filter by a specific supplier, click the magnifying glass iconto open the supplier list window and select the desired supplier. If you leaveit empty, all suppliers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotal Field: Displays the total amount of all transactionsthat are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOKto proceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be includedin the posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOffset Payables Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25. The OffsetPayables function allows the outstanding AP balance to be reduced either byreallocating it to an alternate supplier account or by offsetting it against anassociated receivable for the same supplier.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selector enter the Reference No. for theoffset transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe appropriate Offset Type:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier – The Supplier OffsetInformation section will be enabled for entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer – The Customer OffsetInformation section will be enabled for entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sample Scenario: \n\r\n\rWewant to allocate the selected payable amount to a different supplier/branch.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required OffsetAmount.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; If the available balanceis a positivevalue, enter the Offset Amount as a positivevalue.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifthe availablebalance is a negative value, enterthe OffsetAmount as a negative value.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fillin the required supplier information for allocated or offset payable, includingSupplierCode, Document Number, and TransactionType.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOKto proceed with the offsetting. Click Cancel to close thewindow and discard the offsetting.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Aconfirmation message will appear once the offsetting is successfully completed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Output:\n\r\n\rThe currenttransaction will be partially offset (e.g., This current transaction ispartially offset to DM#3).\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe allocatedor offset payable to different supplier will be automatically created by thesystem\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract A/P Entry Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract A/P Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract A/P Entry button is used tocopy or duplicate the current transaction under AP Summary Entry module. Whenyou click this button, the system automatically extracts all information fromthe existing transaction —such as supplier details and creates a newtransaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date or EWT) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rPayment / Application Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r27. Once the transaction is posted, thePayments/Application button can be used. Click the button and Payment /Application window will appear on screen. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDivided into three sections:\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; View Payments – Displayspayments recorded in the Cash Disbursementmodule. Users can review all payments that have been entered.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; View Application Breakdown – Thissection presents a detailed breakdown of how credits, or adjustments areapplied to specific invoices or transactions within the AccountsReceivable Application module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;GenerateCM Application – This function allows you to directlyapply or offset the current transaction against an existing Credit Memo (CM) orDebit Memo (DM) transaction. Once the application is completed, the transactionis recorded and displayed in the View Application Breakdownsection, providing a detailed view of how it has been applied. At the sametime, the AccountsPayable Application module is updated to reflect the appliedtransaction, and the supplier ledger is alsoupdated to ensure that account balances remain accurate.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use AP Summary Entry","topics\\AP_Summary_entry_creating.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  4  8  2026-01-28T08:52:00Z  2026-02-02T04:56:00Z  3  458  2611  21  6  3063  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing an A/P Summary Entry \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the A/P Summary Entry windowwill appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means alltransactions will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the document associated with that identifier, while still applying anyother filters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosetransactions whosedocument number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All transactionsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier:If you want to filter by a specific supplier, click the magnifying glass iconto open the supplier list window and select the desired supplier. If you leaveit empty, all suppliers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the transactions that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correct transactionsand that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall transactions that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the AP Summary Entry window.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing an AP Summary Entry","topics\\AP_Summary_Entry_printing.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  6  11  2026-01-28T08:50:00Z  2026-02-06T10:30:00Z  3  140  800  6  1  939  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the A/PSummary Entry\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select A/P Summary Entryfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe document number you want to search in the space provided, then a list of supplierswith the same number will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe supplier then click OK button todisplay the transaction.\n\r\n\r","II. Searching for a Transaction in the AP Summary Entry","topics\\AP_Summary_Entry_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  2  3  2026-02-05T07:23:00Z  2026-02-05T07:26:00Z  1  105  605  5  1  709  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rA/R SUMMARY ENTRY    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe A/R Summary Entry module allows users to recordadjustments related to accounts receivable transactions. It is typically usedwhen a transaction contains incorrect or incomplete information, such as whenother receivable amounts need to be corrected. By using this module, users canadjust existing A/R records to ensure that financial data remains accurate andup to date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIn addition to making corrections, the A/R Summary Entrymodule can also be used to establish the beginning balance for a customer whensetting up new records or transitioning from another system. This ensures thatall outstanding receivables are properly reflected in the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","AR Summary Entry","topics\\AR_Summary_Entry.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  22  89  2026-01-28T10:10:00Z  2026-02-24T09:52:00Z  23  2821  16083  134  37  18867  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use A/R Summary Entry\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select A/R Summary Entryfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the customer list, or if you know thecustomer’s code, enter it directly in the Customer field. If thecode does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea customer is selected, the Bill Tofield is automatically updated based on the customer information. The firstline shows the customer’s full name. You can change or typedirectly in this field if you need to specify a different name.This is useful when the transaction needs to be billed to a branch, department,or another contact person.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTerms field is automatically setbased on the customer’s default terms. You can change it and select differentterms if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SelectTransaction Type, this field isautomatically set based on the customer’s default transaction type configuredin the Customer Module. It can be modified if necessary; however, it is arequired field and cannot be left blank. This field is used to identify thetransaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;EnterP.O. number, if needed\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. The BaseArea field is automatically set based on the customer’s default base areaspecified in the billing address. If the address is changed, the Base Area willupdate according to the default base area of the new address. You may alsomanually select a different Base Area if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. It is automatically filled with thecustomer’s address. If the address is different from default address, you canselect another address. Click the magnifying glass icon tosee available addresses. If the address is not listed, you can add it in the customermodule.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. When you select a customer, the Default Agent assigned to that customerwill automatically appear in the Agent field. This information is based on thesetup defined in the customer module. If necessary, you can change or replacethe default agent by selecting another one from the dropdown list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Use the Particulars field to enter additionalnotes, comments, or specific instructions related to the A/R Summary Entryif needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Enter the Amount as a positive value to increases the receivables, or enterthe Amount as a negative value to reductions in receivables.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. Enter the Discount Rate (%) to be applied to the Amount. The system willautomatically calculate the corresponding DiscountAmount. If a specific discount value is preferred, you may enter itdirectly in the Discount Amount field\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. Enter any additional adjustment amount,if needed. \n\r\n\r§&nbsp;Apositive value increasesthe net amount.\n\r\n\r§&nbsp;Anegative value decreasesthe net amount.\n\r\n\r§&nbsp;Thisfield can only be used if the original amount entered is positive.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNetAmount – This isthe subtotal after applying discounts and adjustments. It is automaticallycomputed by the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. The Currency/Ratefields are automatically filled using the customer’s default currency. You maychange these fields if the transaction requires a different currency.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. If the amount is VAT-inclusive, tick the VAT Inclusive checkbox to ensure correcttax computation.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. The highlighted section displays thetransaction values based on the selected currency and their equivalent amountsin Philippine Peso (PHP). This allows the user to view both the originalcurrency values and their converted peso amounts side by side. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TotalAmount – Refers tothe final receivable amount or amount due.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Applied Amount – Total amount that has been paid orcredited.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Balance – The remaining amount due.\n\r\n\rFormula:\n\rBalance= Total Amount – Applied Amount\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r20. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means alltransactions will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the document associated with that identifier, while still applying anyother filters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or customer\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosetransactions whosedocument number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All transactionsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotal Field: Displays the total amount of alltransactions that are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOKto proceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be includedin the posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOffset Receivables Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26. The OffsetReceivables function allows the outstanding accounts receivable balance tobe reduced either by reallocating it to an alternate customer account or byoffsetting it against an associated payable when the customer also functions asa supplier.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selector enter the Reference No. for theoffset transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe appropriate Offset Type:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier – The Supplier OffsetInformation section will be enabled for entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer – The Customer OffsetInformation section will be enabled for entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sample Scenario: \n\r\n\rWewant to allocate the selected receivable amount to a different customer/branch.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required OffsetAmount.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; If the available balanceis a positivevalue, enter the Offset Amount as a positivevalue.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifthe availablebalance is a negative value, enterthe OffsetAmount as a negative value.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fillin the required customer information for allocated or offset receivables, including Customer Code, Document Number,and TransactionType.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOKto proceed with the offsetting. Click Cancel to close thewindow and discard the offsetting.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Aconfirmation message will appear once the offsetting is successfully completed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Output:\n\r\n\rThe currenttransaction will be partially offset (e.g., This current transaction ispartially offset to CM#4).\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe allocatedor offset payable to different customer will be automatically created by thesystem\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract A/R Entry Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r27. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract A/R Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTheExtract A/R Entry button is used tocopy or duplicate the current transaction under A/R Summary Entry module. Whenyou click this button, the system automatically extracts all information fromthe existing Transaction—such as customer details and creates a new Transactionentry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThisfunction is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp; Creating a new transaction that hassimilar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp; Saving time by eliminating the need tore-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp; Maintaining consistency and accuracy inrepeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfter extraction, you may edit or updatethe new transaction as needed (for example, changing the document date oraddress) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rPayment / Application Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r28. Once the transaction is posted, thePayments/Application button can be used. Click the button and Payment /Application window will appear on screen. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDivided into three sections:\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; View Payments – Displayspayments recorded in the Cash Receipt module. Userscan review all payments that have been entered.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; View Application Breakdown – Thissection presents a detailed breakdown of how credits, or adjustments areapplied to specific invoices or transactions within the AccountsReceivable Application module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;GenerateCM Application – This function allows you to directlyapply or offset the current transaction against an existing Credit Memo (CM) orDebit Memo (DM) transaction. Once the application is completed, the transactionis recorded and displayed in the View Application Breakdownsection, providing a detailed view of how it has been applied. At the sametime, the AccountsReceivable Application module is updated to reflect the appliedtransaction, and the customer ledger is alsoupdated to ensure that account balances remain accurate.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use A/R Summary Entry","topics\\AR_Summary_Entry_create.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  6  12  2026-02-02T04:56:00Z  2026-02-02T05:21:00Z  3  444  2536  21  5  2975  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing an A/R Summary Entry \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the A/R Summary Entry windowwill appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means alltransactions will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the document associated with that identifier, while still applying anyother filters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or customer\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosetransactions whosedocument number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All transactionsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the transactions that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correcttransactions and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall transactions that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the AR Summary Entry window.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing an A/R Summary Entry","topics\\AR_Summary_Entry_printing.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  7  2  2026-02-02T04:42:00Z  2026-02-06T10:31:00Z  2  110  630  5  1  739  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the A/RSummary Entry\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select AR Summary Entryfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe supplier then click OK button todisplay the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the A/R Summary Entry","topics\\AR_Summary_Entry_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  39  108  2025-10-21T04:29:00Z  2025-10-30T14:21:00Z  1  539  3078  25  7  3610  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rAREA\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThissection is used to identify the main place or location where the addressbelongs, such as the city, province, or region. It serves as the locationgrouping for the record.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAssigningan Area allows the system to properlygroup and organize records according to their location. This helps ingenerating accurate reports, monitoring activities per area, and comparingperformance or transactions between different regions or territories.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTheuser selects the appropriate Areawhen encoding or updating a record. By choosing the correct area, the systemcan correctly classify the customer, supplier, or transaction under its properlocation, ensuring accurate reporting and tracking.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding an Area\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Area. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Areas. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter the Name/ Description and Division in the fields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew area will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Edit button to modify therecord. If the selected Area is already used in existing transactions, thesystem will automatically apply the changes to all related transactions toensure consistency and accurate posting. Please be reminded that these changesmay also affect historical reports since the updated information will be reflectedin previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching an Area\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of area will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Area from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Area from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Area will thenappear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Area","topics\\Area.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  29  2025-11-06T03:51:00Z  2025-11-06T04:28:00Z  3  333  1903  15  4  2232  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rAUDIT  TRAIL   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis module displays a record of allactions performed within the system. It helps track user activities such ascreating, editing, deleting, posting, or canceling records.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHowto Use the Audit Trail\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Audit Trail from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Atthe upper portion of the screen, you can use the available filters to refineyour search:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.1. Filterrecords by a specific user.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.2. Filterrecords by module name.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.3. Filterby type of activity performed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.4. Filterrecords within a specific date range.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.5. ClickRequery button refresh and apply the selectedfilters.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rIf no filters are set (User, Module,Action, or Date), clicking the Requery button will retrieve and display all actionsrecorded in the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thelower portion of the screen displays the list of records based on the selected filters.Each column provides specific details about the recorded activity:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Action: Indicates the type of transactionperformed (e.g., Add, Edit, Delete, Post, Cancel).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Date: Displays the date and time the action was performed.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Remarks: Shows additional details related to thetransaction.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;User: Identifies the user who performed the action.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Module: Displays the module of the system wherethe action took place.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Reference: Shows the internal control number.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Audit Trail","topics\\Audit_Trail.htm","\n\r\n\r               Back Office\n\r    Cash Receipt     Deposit of   Collection      Bounced Check     Cash   Disbursement     Check Releasing     Clearing of   Issued Checks       Bank Adjustment     Bank   Reconciliation     Petty Cash&nbsp;     Petty Cash   Replenishment \n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Back Office","topics\\back_office_menu.htm","        Business Box - SQL       version      BANK       ADJUSTMENT\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Bank Adjustment","topics\\Bank_Adjustment.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  7  238  2026-02-23T05:14:00Z  2026-02-24T10:06:00Z  5  946  5396  44  12  6330  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Bank Adjustment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Bank Adjustmentfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Bank Name where the payment willbe cleared.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;EnterRemarks for additional instructionsrelated to the Bank Adjustment, if needed.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If theDocument ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number as needed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addingand Deleting an adjustment entry:\n\r\n\r7.1. Select Adjustment Class to show whattype of bank adjustment you are recording. For example, this could be bankcharges, bank interest, service fees, or other related bank adjustments.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.2. Enter additionalnotes or special instructions in Particularscolumn that related to the selected adjustment class, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.3. Enter Amount as a positive value to increase the bank balance, or enter it as a negative value to reduce the bankbalance.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.4. To add another entry in the BankAdjustment, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps7.1 to 7.3. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively,using your optical mouse, right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another entry line.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line, select line thatyou want to delete. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No to cancelthe action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Currency code and Rate are automatically set to PHP with adefault rate of 1. If the transaction needs to be recorded in a differentcurrency, you may update these fields accordingly to reflect the correctcurrency and exchange rate.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to update theinformation as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes to applythem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. A confirmationmessage may appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to post therecord or No to cancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is posted, the system will automatically updatethe Bank Reconciliation module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract BA Entry Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract BA Entry Button, ifneeded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract BA Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Bank Adjustment module. When youclick this button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as adjustment class, amount and creates a newtransaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, amount or remarks) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Bank Adjustment","topics\\Bank_Adjustment_HowTo.htm","        Business Box - SQL       version      BANK       RECONCILIATION\n\r\n\r","Bank Reconciliation","topics\\Bank_Reconciliation.htm","        Business Box - SQL       version      BOUNCED       CHECK\n\r\n\r","Bounced Check","topics\\Bounced_Check.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  2  1  2026-04-24T02:25:00Z  2026-04-24T02:26:00Z  1  7  43  1  1  49  16.00        Print  60  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rCASH DISBURSEMENT   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r ","Cash Disbursement","topics\\Cash_Disbursement.htm","   user  user  3  115  2026-05-20T02:04:00Z  2026-05-22T07:45:00Z  7  1008  5751  47  13  6746  16.00        Print  132  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Application of Advance to Supplier \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Cash Disbursement fromthe Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the Supplier list, or if you know the Supplier’scode, enter it directly in the Supplier field. If thecode does not exist, the Supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Uponselecting a Supplier, if the system detects that the Supplier has existingadvances, a validation message will be displayed. Click OKto proceed, and the “List of Advances” window for the selected Supplier willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fromthe “List of Advances” window, select the document you wish to apply. Onceselected, click the Close button to exit the window and proceedwith the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: This window showsonly posted transactions with advances or overpayments.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Uponclosing the “List of Advances” window, another validation message will appear.Click YESto proceed with creating a new Cash Disbursement transaction. Otherwise, click NOto cancel the creation and return to the main Cash Disbursement screen, wherethe selected advance will be displayed will be available for applying theinvoice.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Applicationof invoice:\n\r\n\r7.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thereare two available options for applying the invoice in the system:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOption 1:Click the Abutton to apply the invoice per payment type. This option allows you toallocate and match the collection according to each specific payment type, thisis recommended when you need a clear breakdown and precise matching ofcollection for accounting or reporting purposes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOption2: Click the ApplyReceivables button to apply the invoice to the totalcollection. This option consolidates the full amount and processes it in asingle transaction, offering a simpler and more efficient approach whendetailed allocation is not required.\n\r\n\rPleasecarefully review both options and select the one that best aligns with yourpreferred processing method and business requirements.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickeither the A button or the Apply to Receivables button, and the Apply to Invoices window will bedisplayed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThere are mayways to apply the invoices:\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe X button to automatically applythe full balance of the invoice. If you prefer a partial application, manuallyenter the desired amount in the Applied Amount column for the specific invoiceline.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;UseOldest Invoiceto automatically allocate the payment starting with the oldest outstandinginvoice. The system prioritizes earlier invoices and continues applying theamount in sequence until the payment is fully utilized or no remaining invoicesare left.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe ByDate Range option to automatically apply payments to invoiceswithin the selected date range. The system will allocate the payment to all invoicesthat fall within the specified period.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe ByDocument No. option to automatically apply the payment toinvoices within a specified document number range. Once you enter the desiredrange, the system will identify all matching invoices and allocate the paymentaccordingly.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: The Payment Balance will be automaticallyupdated as invoices are selected from the grid, continuously deducting appliedamounts until the remaining balance reaches zero.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickFindto look up a specific Invoice from list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to close the Apply to invoice window and all marked invoice willappear on main screen of Cash Disbursement.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Since the advances or overpayments have already beenposted, please ensure that all tagged invoices are carefully reviewed beforeproceeding. Once you click OK, the action will be final and cannot be reversed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If you knowthe document number of the Cash Disbursement with an advance, click the Findbutton on the Navigation Toolbar, then proceed with Step 7.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Application of Advances to Supplier","topics\\Cash_Disbursement_advances.htm","   user  user  3  2  2026-05-22T09:08:00Z  2026-05-22T09:31:00Z  2  113  645  5  1  757  16.00        Print  132  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the CashDisbursement\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Cash Disbursementfrom the Menu and the module will open.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar and theSearch Document number window will appear. Enter the document number you want tosearch in the space provided. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the CashDisbursement.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Searching for a Transaction in the Cash Disbursement","topics\\Cash_Disbursement_find.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  user  11  328  2026-04-24T02:29:00Z  2026-05-20T02:02:00Z  18  2667  15205  126  35  17837  16.00        Print  180  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Cash Disbursement \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Cash Disbursementfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thisfield is optional. The Group fieldshould be used if a single payment is to be applied across multiple branches.However, if the payment is intended for a specific selected Supplier only, thisfield may be left blank.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: If this field is used, ensure that all sub-branches or Suppliershave the same default group name assigned in the Supplier Module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the Supplier list, or if you know theSupplier’s code, enter it directly in the Supplier field. If thecode does not exist, the Supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea Supplier is selected, the Pay To fieldis automatically updated based on the Supplier name encoded in Supplier module.You can changeand type directly in this field if you need to specify adifferent name. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe Remarks field to include anyfurther information regarding the payment to Supplier, if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thesystem provides a Reference sectionwhere users can input related document details, such as the Official Receipt (O.R.) Number, andcorresponding reference date. These fields are intended to establish a linkbetween the Cash Disbursement and any supporting or external documents that arerelevant to the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;By default, the Document Type is setto TRADE, but this may be changed as necessary depending on the natureof the transaction. It is important to select the appropriate document type toensure the payment to supplier is correctly recorded and applied in the system.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TRADE– Select this option when the payment to supplier is made to settle a purchaseinvoice for raw materials. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;NON-TRADE– Select this option when the payment to Supplier is related to non-purchasetransactions, such as services, fees, or other charges that are not connectedto the merchandise items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Select Transaction Type, this field is automatically set based on theSupplier’s default transaction type under Supplier module. You can changeit&nbsp;as needed or leave it blank.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Adding and Deleting Payments:\n\r\n\r11.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe payment type.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe check bank.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the remaining transactiondetails.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFill in the required fields belowfor the Supplier cheque:\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Check Number– Enter the cheque number assigned by your issuing bank \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Check Date– Enter the date you want to appear on the cheque (issue date or post-dateddate, if applicable). \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Check Amount– Enter the exact amount you want to issue on the cheque and ensure it matchesyour payment records and supporting documents. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Currency Code– Select the currency used when issuing the cheque (e.g., PHP, USD). \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Exchange Rate– If the cheque is issued in a foreign currency, enter the exchange rate usedat the time of issuance; if it is in local currency, this can be set to 1.00.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields are automatically updated once the selected payment has been tagged inthe Clearing of issued checks module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toadd another payment, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps11.1 to 11.3. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively,using your optical mouse, select any column on the payment details grid, then right-click anywhere within the moduleand choose Add Payment Entry. A newline will appear, allowing you to add another payment.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.6.&nbsp; To delete a payment line, first selectthe specific entry you wish to remove within the Payment Details grid. Onceselected, use the optical mouse to right-click anywhere within the module. Fromthe available options in the context menu, choose Delete Payment Entry. The selected payment line will then beremoved from the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the payment or Noto cancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:  If the payment type is set to Checkunder the group list (PaymentType) of the Other Files module, the CheckBank, Branch, and CheckNumber fields in the Cash Disbursement modulewill be enabled, allowing the user to enter the relevant cheque details. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHowever, ifthe payment type is not set to Check, these fields willremain disabled and will not be available for data entry.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Application of invoice:\n\r\n\r12.1.There are two available options for applying the invoice inthe system:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOption 1:Click the Abutton to apply the invoice per payment type. This option allows you toallocate and match the payment according to each specific payment type.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOption2: Click the ApplyPayables button to apply the invoice to the total payment. Thisoption consolidates the full amount and processes it in a single transaction,offering a simpler and more efficient approach when detailed allocation is notrequired.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rPleasecarefully review both options and select the one that best aligns with yourpreferred processing method and business requirements.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.2.Click either the Abutton or the Apply to Payablesbutton, and the Apply to Invoiceswindow will be displayed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThere are mayways to apply the invoices:\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe X button to automatically applythe full balance of the invoice. If you prefer a partial application, manuallyenter the desired amount in the Applied Amount column for the specific invoiceline.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;UseOldest Invoiceto automatically allocate the payment starting with the oldest outstandinginvoice. The system prioritizes earlier invoices and continues applying theamount in sequence until the payment is fully utilized or no remaining invoicesare left.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe ByDate Range option to automatically apply payments to invoiceswithin the selected date range. The system will allocate the payment to allinvoices that fall within the specified period.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe ByDocument No. option to automatically apply the payment toinvoices within a specified document number range. Once you enter the desiredrange, the system will identify all matching invoices and allocate the paymentaccordingly.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: The Payment Balance will be automaticallyupdated as invoices are selected from the grid, continuously deducting appliedamounts until the remaining balance reaches zero.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.3.Click Find to look up aspecific Invoice from list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.4.Click OK button to close the Apply to invoice window andall marked invoice will appear on main screen of Cash Disbursement.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.  Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Click the Post buttonin the Navigation Toolbar thatlocated at the top of the window. And the Batch Posting window willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.1.Usethe available filters to retrieve the specific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID:You can set Document ID to All, which means all transactions willbe included without restriction based on their unique identifiers. However, ifyou want to focus on specific transactions, you can select a particularDocument ID, allowing the system to retrieve and display only the transactionassociated with that identifier, while still applying any other filters you mayhave set, such as Document Range, Date Range, or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields let you specify thenumeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example:From 1 To 50 — means only those transactions whose document number is between 1and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange:Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is not checked. This meansthe date range filter will be ignored. All transactions matching the DocumentID and Document Range will be included, regardless of their date. If you wantto filter by date, you must check the &quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier: If you want to filter by a specificSupplier, click the magnifying glass icon to open the Supplier list window andselect the desired Supplier. If you leave it empty, all Suppliers will beincluded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.2.After applying the filters, At thebottom of this window, click the Requery button to refresh the grid and display only theunposted transactions that match your selected criteria\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.3.By default, the checkboxes next to eachdocument are selected, meaning all documents will be included in the batchposting unless you manually uncheck them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotalField: Displays the total amount of alltransactions that are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.4.Click OK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Once the transaction has been posted, itis considered final and cannot be edited or deleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Enter the date and reason forcancellation, then click OK toconfirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Once a transaction has been cancelled,any applied invoice shall be reverted to an unpaid status.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; A transaction cannot be cancelled if thecorresponding payment has already been cleared in the Clearing of Issued checks module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Cash Disbursement","topics\\Cash_Disbursement_Howto.htm","   user  user  3  34  2026-05-22T09:32:00Z  2026-05-22T10:06:00Z  1  343  1959  16  4  2298  16.00        Print  132  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Cash Disbursement / BatchPrinting\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Cash Disbursement window will appear. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which includes all receipts without restricting them by theirunique identifiers. If you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to print onlythe receipts associated with that identifier, while still applying any otherfilters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosereceipts whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All receiptsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass icon toopen the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leave itempty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view a previewof the receipts that match the currently set filter criteria before printingthem. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correct receiptsand that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall receipts that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Cash Disbursement window.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Printing a Cash Disbursement/ Batch Printing","topics\\Cash_Disbursement_print.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  2  0  2026-04-24T02:25:00Z  2026-04-24T02:25:00Z  1  6  38  1  1  43  16.00        Print  60  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rCASH RECEIPT   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Cash Receipt","topics\\Cash_Receipt.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  user  15  75  2026-04-23T03:57:00Z  2026-05-22T07:44:00Z  7  990  5646  47  13  6623  16.00        Print  132  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Application of Advance from Customer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Cash Receiptfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the customer list, or if you know the customer’scode, enter it directly in the Customer field. If thecode does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Uponselecting a customer, if the system detects that the customer has existingadvances, a validation message will be displayed. Click OK toproceed, and the “List of Advances” window for the selected customer willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fromthe “List of Advances” window, select the document you wish to apply. Onceselected, click the Close button to exit the window and proceedwith the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: This window showsonly posted transactions with advances or overpayments.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Uponclosing the “List of Advances” window, another validation message will appear.Click YESto proceed with creating a new Cash Receipt transaction. Otherwise, click NOto cancel the creation and return to the main Cash Receipt screen, where theselected advance will be displayed will be available for applying the invoice.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Applicationof invoice:\n\r\n\r7.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thereare two available options for applying the invoice in the system:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOption 1:Click the Abutton to apply the invoice per payment type. This option allows you toallocate and match the collection according to each specific payment type, thisis recommended when you need a clear breakdown and precise matching ofcollection for accounting or reporting purposes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOption2: Click the ApplyReceivables button to apply the invoice to the totalcollection. This option consolidates the full amount and processes it in asingle transaction, offering a simpler and more efficient approach whendetailed allocation is not required.\n\r\n\rPleasecarefully review both options and select the one that best aligns with yourpreferred processing method and business requirements.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickeither the A button or the Apply to Receivables button, and the Apply to Invoices window will bedisplayed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThere are mayways to apply the invoices:\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe X button to automatically applythe full balance of the invoice. If you prefer a partial application, manuallyenter the desired amount in the Applied Amount column for the specific invoiceline.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;UseOldest Invoiceto automatically allocate the payment starting with the oldest outstandinginvoice. The system prioritizes earlier invoices and continues applying theamount in sequence until the payment is fully utilized or no remaining invoicesare left.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe ByDate Range option to automatically apply payments to invoiceswithin the selected date range. The system will allocate the payment to allinvoices that fall within the specified period.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe ByDocument No. option to automatically apply the payment toinvoices within a specified document number range. Once you enter the desiredrange, the system will identify all matching invoices and allocate the paymentaccordingly.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: The Payment Balance will be automaticallyupdated as invoices are selected from the grid, continuously deducting appliedamounts until the remaining balance reaches zero.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickFindto look up a specific Invoice from list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to close the Apply to invoice window and all marked invoice willappear on main screen of cash receipt.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Since the advances or overpayments have already been posted,please ensure that all tagged invoices are carefully reviewed beforeproceeding. Once you click OK, the action will be final and cannot be reversed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If youknow the document number of the cash receipt with an advance, click the Findbutton on the Navigation Toolbar, then proceed with Step 7.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Application of Advances from Customer","topics\\Cash_Receipt_Advances.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  3  8  2026-04-23T07:14:00Z  2026-04-23T07:25:00Z  2  108  619  5  1  726  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the CashReceipt\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Cash Receiptfrom the Menu and the module will open.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar and theSearch Document number window will appear. Enter the document number you want tosearch in the space provided. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the CashReceipt.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Searching for a Transaction in the Cash Receipt","topics\\Cash_Receipt_find.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  user  49  771  2026-04-20T08:15:00Z  2026-04-27T02:58:00Z  1  2797  15944  132  37  18704  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Cash Receipt \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Cash Receiptfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thisfield is optional. The Group fieldshould be used if a single payment is to be applied across multiple branches.However, if the payment is intended for a specific selected customer only, thisfield may be left blank.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: If this field is used, ensure that all sub-branches orcustomers have the same default group name assigned in the Customer Module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the customer list, or if you know thecustomer’s code, enter it directly in the Customer field. If thecode does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thisfield is optional, Click the magnifying glass icon to open the collector list,or if you know the collector’s code, enter it directly in the collectorfield. If the code does not exist, the collector list willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Collector from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea customer is selected, the Received from fieldis automatically updated based on the customer name encoded in customer module.You can changeand type directly in this field if you need to specify adifferent name or payer. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe Remarks field to include anyfurther information regarding the payment received from customer, if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thesystem provides a Reference sectionwhere users can input related document details, such as the Official Receipt (O.R.) Number, Payment Request (P.R.) Number, andcorresponding reference dates. These fields are intended to establish a linkbetween the Cash Receipt and any supporting or external documents that arerelevant to the transaction.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Bydefault, the Document Type is set to TRADE, but this may be changed asnecessary depending on the nature of the transaction. It is important to selectthe appropriate document type to ensure the customer payment is correctlyrecorded and applied in the system. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TRADE– Select this option when the customer payment is made to settle a salesinvoice for goods or products sold. This applies to all transactions involvingthe sale of merchandise to customers.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;NON-TRADE– Select this option when the customer payment is related to non-salestransactions, such as services, fees, or other charges that are not connectedto the sale of goods.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Select Transaction Type, this field is automatically set based on thecustomer’s default transaction type under customer module. You can changeit&nbsp;as needed or leave it blank.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Adding Payments :\n\r\n\r12.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe payment type.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe check bank.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r12.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the remaining transactiondetails.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFill in the required fields belowfor the customer cheque:\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Branch– Select or enter the branch where the cheque was issued. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cheque Number– Enter the number shown on the cheque. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cheque Date– Enter the date printed on the cheque. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cheque Amount– Enter the amount shown on the cheque and ensure it matches supportingdocuments. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Currency Code– Select the currency of the cheque (e.g., USD, PHP). \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Exchange Rate– Enter the applicable rate for foreign currency cheques, if applicable.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.4.&nbsp; Other fields are automatically updatedonce the selected payment has been tagged in the deposit collection module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.5.&nbsp; To add another payment, press the ArrowDown key on your keyboard and repeat steps 12.1 to 13.3. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively,using your optical mouse, select any column on the payment details grid, then right-click anywhere within the moduleand choose Add Payment Entry. A newline will appear, allowing you to add another payment.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.6.&nbsp; To delete a payment line, first selectthe specific entry you wish to remove within the Payment Details grid. Onceselected, use the optical mouse to right-click anywhere within the module. Fromthe available options in the context menu, choose Delete Payment Entry. The selected payment line will then beremoved from the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the payment or Noto cancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:  If the payment type is set to Checkunder the group list (PaymentType) of the Other Files module, the CheckBank, Branch, and CheckNumber fields in the Cash Receipt module willbe enabled, allowing the user to enter the relevant cheque details. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHowever, ifthe payment type is not set to Check, these fields willremain disabled and will not be available for data entry.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Application of invoice:\n\r\n\r13.1.There are two available options for applying the invoice inthe system:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOption 1:Click the Abutton to apply the invoice per payment type. This option allows you toallocate and match the collection according to each specific payment type, thisis recommended when you need a clear breakdown and precise matching ofcollection for accounting or reporting purposes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOption2: Click the ApplyReceivables button to apply the invoice to the totalcollection. This option consolidates the full amount and processes it in asingle transaction, offering a simpler and more efficient approach whendetailed allocation is not required.\n\r\n\rPleasecarefully review both options and select the one that best aligns with yourpreferred processing method and business requirements.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.2.Click either the Abutton or the Apply to Receivablesbutton, and the Apply to Invoiceswindow will be displayed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThere are mayways to apply the invoices:\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe X button to automatically applythe full balance of the invoice. If you prefer a partial application, manuallyenter the desired amount in the Applied Amount column for the specific invoiceline.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;UseOldest Invoiceto automatically allocate the payment starting with the oldest outstandinginvoice. The system prioritizes earlier invoices and continues applying theamount in sequence until the payment is fully utilized or no remaining invoicesare left.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe ByDate Range option to automatically apply payments to invoiceswithin the selected date range. The system will allocate the payment to allinvoices that fall within the specified period.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe ByDocument No. option to automatically apply the payment toinvoices within a specified document number range. Once you enter the desiredrange, the system will identify all matching invoices and allocate the paymentaccordingly.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: The Payment Balance will be automaticallyupdated as invoices are selected from the grid, continuously deducting appliedamounts until the remaining balance reaches zero.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.3.Click Find to look up aspecific Invoice from list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.4.Click OK button to close the Apply to invoice window andall marked invoice will appear on main screen of cash receipt.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Click Other Information button, If needed. And the Other Information window will open, this window providesadditional details related to the transaction, such as grouping, custom fields,posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.  Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. Click the Post buttonin the Navigation Toolbar thatlocated at the top of the window. And the Batch Posting window willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18.1.Usethe available filters to retrieve the specific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID:You can set Document ID to All, which means all receipts will beincluded without restriction based on their unique identifiers. However, if youwant to focus on specific transactions, you can select a particular DocumentID, allowing the system to retrieve and display only the receipts associatedwith that identifier, while still applying any other filters you may have set,such as Document Range, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields let you specify thenumeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example:From 1 To 50 — means only those receipts whose document number is between 1 and50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange:Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is not checked. This meansthe date range filter will be ignored. All receipts matching the Document IDand Document Range will be included, regardless of their date. If you want tofilter by date, you must check the &quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer: If you want to filter by a specificcustomer, click the magnifying glass icon to open the customer list window andselect the desired customer. If you leave it empty, all customers will beincluded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18.2.After applying the filters, At thebottom of this window, click the Requery button to refresh the grid and display only theunposted transactions that match your selected criteria\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18.3.By default, the checkboxes next to eachdocument are selected, meaning all documents will be included in the batchposting unless you manually uncheck them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotalField: Displays the total amount of alltransactions that are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18.4.Click OKto proceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be includedin the posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Once the transaction has been posted, itis considered final and cannot be edited or deleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Enter the date and reason forcancellation, then click OK toconfirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Once a transaction has been cancelled,any applied invoice shall be reverted to an unpaid status.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; A transaction cannot be cancelled if thecorresponding payment has already been deposited in the deposit collectionmodule.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Cash Receipt","topics\\Cash_Receipt_howto.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  6  125  2026-04-23T07:26:00Z  2026-04-23T09:34:00Z  2  421  2401  20  5  2817  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Cash Receipt / Batch Printing\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Cash Receipt window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which includes all receipts without restricting them by theirunique identifiers. If you want to focus on specific transactions, you can selecta particular Document ID, allowing the system to print onlythe receipts associated with that identifier, while still applying any otherfilters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosereceipts whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All receiptsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the receipts that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correctreceipts and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall receipts that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Cash Receiptwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Printing a Cash Receipt / Batch Printing","topics\\Cash_Receipt_print.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  3  1  2026-04-23T09:37:00Z  2026-04-23T09:38:00Z  1  64  370  3  1  433  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Affected Reports in Report Managermodule:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rGroup List :Account Receivables\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ARSummary \n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Agingof Receivables – Detailed\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Agingof Receivables – Summarized\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CancelledReceipt\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CollectionApplication \n\r\n\rf.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CollectionEfficiency\n\r\n\rg.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Collectionfor the Period\n\r\n\rh.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CustomerLedger\n\r\n\ri.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Statementof Account\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rGroup List : Bank Reconciliation\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Collectionon Hand\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Collectionsby Cheque Date\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Collectionsby Received Date\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;DailyCash Position\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;PostDated Cheques\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","V. Affected Reports in Report Manager Module","topics\\cash_receipt_reports.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  2  2  2026-02-23T04:21:00Z  2026-02-23T04:23:00Z  1  90  515  4  1  604  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rCHECK  RELEASING   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe CheckVoucher Releasing module allows you to manage and release allyour cheque payments to the corresponding suppliers or vendors efficiently.Within this module, you can easily identify and tag or mark the payments thatare ready for release. This ensures that only approved and verified paymentsare processed, helping you maintain accuracy and control over your financialtransactions. By using this feature, you can keep track of all releasedcheques and unreleased payments, and ensure that suppliers or vendorsreceive their payments on time.","Check Releasing","topics\\Check_Releasing.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  6  46  2026-02-19T05:55:00Z  2026-02-23T04:29:00Z  4  323  1847  15  4  2166  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Check Releasing\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Check Releasingfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe released date in Reference date field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickFind button on Navigation toolbar to quickly look up a specific payment withouthaving to scroll through the entire list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Xbutton to tag the payment that need to be released.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Youcan tag multiple payment as long as they have the same released date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When a voucher is selected,the payment and other details such as the transaction details will also beshown.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;PaymentDetails Grid –This grid displays the payment details for the currently selected voucher. Itincludes information such as the mode of payment, check number, check bank,check date, and check amount.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;TransactionDetails Grid –This grid displays the invoices applied to the currently selected voucher. Itincludes details such as the invoice number and the applied amount.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Cheque Update to released theselected payments. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rA confirmationmessage will appear once the released check has been successfully completed.\n\r\n\r","I. How to use Check Releasing","topics\\Check_Releasing_howto.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  3  24  2026-02-23T04:42:00Z  2026-02-23T05:06:00Z  1  53  306  2  1  358  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rCLEARING  OF ISSUED CHECKS   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Clearing of Issued Checks module allowsyou to monitor the status of checks issued to suppliers or vendors. When acheck is cleared, it means the supplier has already encashed or deposited thecheck into their account, and the corresponding amount has been deducted fromthe company\'s bank account.","Clearing of Issued Checks","topics\\Clearing_of_Issued_Checks.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  15  339  2026-02-19T06:33:00Z  2026-02-24T10:05:00Z  6  765  4364  36  10  5119  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Clearing of Issued Checks\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Clearing of Issued Checksfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Bank Name where the payment willbe cleared.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe cleared date in the Document Date field.By default, this field is set to the current date, however you can modify it ifnecessary to reflect the actual cleared date.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Onthe TagPayments page, click the Xbutton next to each payment that needs to be marked as cleared.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Youcan tag multiple payments as long as they have the same cleared date.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;TotalCleared – Showsthe total amount of all payments currently tagged.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe SearchDocument button to quickly look up a specific payment without havingto scroll through the entire list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the tagging you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To modify an existing record, click the Editbutton. This will allow you to update the information as needed, and oncefinished, you can save your changes to apply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation message mayappear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the record or Noto cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion of important data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. A confirmationmessage may appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to post therecord or No to cancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is posted, the system will automatically updatethe Bank Reconciliation module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. A confirmationmessage may appear—click Yes tocancel the record or No to abort thecancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage, the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is cancelled, the systemwill automatically updatethe Bank Reconciliation module.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftercancellation, the tagged details will disappear so they can be re-tagged in thenext transaction. The details of the cancellation will appear in thecancellation remarks.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Allpost-dated cheques will not appearat this time. Only cheques that are dated for today or earlier will be listedor reflected in the system. Post-dated cheques will only become visible ontheir respective dates, as per their scheduled maturity. This ensures that allfuture payments are recorded accurately and are only accessible when they aredue.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Clearing of Issued Checks","topics\\Clearing_of_Issued_Checks_Howto.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  42  38  2025-10-06T06:58:00Z  2025-11-03T04:12:00Z  9  655  3736  31  8  4383  16.00        Print  160  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rCOLLECTOR   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rACollector refers to the person responsible forfollowing up with customers regarding their outstanding payments. In thismodule, you can record all your Collectors along with their necessary details.These collectors can later be selected during the encoding of CashReceipts, allowing you to easily identify and track who isresponsible for each collection.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Collector\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Collector from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the CollectorCode and Collector Name in their respective fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the E-mail address, if any.&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Address, ContactPerson, Telephone Number and Fax Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the&nbsp;Area and enter the Zip Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding an Address:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the magnifyingglass besides the Address label and the Address List window will open:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Addbutton to add a new address.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Address,Contact Person, Telephone Number and Fax Number.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the&nbsp;Areaand enter the Zip Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Toadd another address, follow steps ato d.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rf.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Clickthe Close button to close thewindow.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Savebutton in the Navigation Toolbar to save the record. Click the Cancelbutton to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Edit button to edit the record. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Delete button to delete the record. Deletion will only be allowed if thesaid record has not been used in other modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Updating Collector Status:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTo update the record of a collector who has resignedor is no longer active, choose Resigned from the Statusdropdown list in the collector Module, then click Saveto apply the changes.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Collector \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of collectors will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Collector from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Codein the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browse through the list using the Scroll Bar or the keyboard arrow keys or scroll wheelof optical mouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After selecting the collector, click theOK button. The collector’s detailswill be displayed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Collector","topics\\Collector.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  63  301  2025-10-08T04:40:00Z  2025-11-04T04:16:00Z  26  2673  15237  126  35  17875  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rCUSTOMER     \n\r\n\rA customer may be an individual or anorganization that purchases or uses the company’s products and services.Maintaining accurate and updated customer information is essential forefficient operations such as sales, customer support, billing, and reporting.\n\r\n\rIn this module, users can create and manage customerrecords by entering complete and accurate details, including the customer’sname, contact information, address, and other relevant information.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAddinga Customer\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Customer from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter theunique&nbsp;Customer Code and the corresponding Customer Name intheir respective fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In General Section:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.1. Select the Customer Group. The Customer Group is useful for customer’swho have branches. There are instances that one branch will pay for the otherbranches’ payables. If this happens then these customers should be grouped.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.2. Enter the E-mail address,URL (Uniform Resource Locator), and TIN (Tax Identification Number), if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.3. Enter the BillingAddress, Contact Person, TelephoneNumber&nbsp;,&nbsp;andFax Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.4. Select the&nbsp; Areaand enter the Zip Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.5.Ifthe Delivery Address same withbilling address, Click the magnifying glass besidesthe Billing Address label and the Address List window will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThen tick the “Default Delivery Address” checkbox. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.6. Click the Close button to close the window and the deliver addresswill be updated.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding an Address:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the magnifyingglass besides the Address label and the Address List window will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Addbutton to add a new address.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Address,Contact Person, Telephone Number and Fax Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the&nbsp; Areaand enter the Zip Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To addanother address follow steps&nbsp;a to d.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rf.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tick the “Default Billing Address” and/or “Default Delivery Address” checkbox(es) before saving to designate thisaddress as the most frequently used.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rg.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Close button toclose the window.&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Particulars, if any. The Particulars may be any informationabout the customer (i.e. Date when they become the company’s client, etc.)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inthe Details section (Transaction Default Values):\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.1. Selectthe Transaction Type ,if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.2. Select the appropriate&nbsp; Currency Code basedon the transaction or customer’s location. Ensure that the selected codematches the actual currency used in billing or payment.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.3. Select the&nbsp; Terms of Payment.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.4. Select the  Tax Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.5. Enter the Fix Currency Rate, ifany. The Fixed Currency Rate is used when the transaction of the customer isother than the Local Currency. For instance, the company sells goods toCustomer XYZ in US Dollar. Since the dollar rate increases/decreases you mayset a fixed rate for the dollar. Therefore, no foreign gain/loss will berecognized.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.6. Enter the Discounts, if any. Ifdiscount/s has been assigned to the customer then upon transaction suchdiscount/s will be the default discount.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.7. Tick/Un-tick the box besides theTaxable label. When the customer has been set as taxable then upon transaction (i.e.A/R Summary Entry) the VAT Inclusive box will have a check marker. This meansthat the transaction is VAT Inclusive.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.8. Clickthe box besides the Require P.O. Number. If the feature is activatedthen upon transaction system will not allow empty P.O. Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inthe Details section (Other Information):\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.1. Enterthe Sales Group, if any. This is use for report viewing of Sales forAgents.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.2. &nbsp;Select the&nbsp; Company Class 1 to5, if any. The Company Class is use to classify the customer’s transaction.These classifications are useful in report generation.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.3. &nbsp;Select the&nbsp; Price Reference to set the defaultprice scheme, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.4. Enterthe Credit Limit, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.5. Ifthe customer is identified as a consignee, the user must select the corresponding&nbsp; Warehouse from the available list. This step ensures that all transactions related tothe consignee are properly linked to the correct warehouse where the goods willbe released or stored.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSelectingthe correct warehouse is important for accurate inventory management, stockmonitoring, and reporting. Since consignee customers may have specific deliverypoints or storage locations, assigning the right warehouse helps maintainconsistency between actual stock movements and system records.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBeforesaving the customer, details or proceeding with the transaction, make sure theselected warehouse matches the consignee’s designated location to avoiddiscrepancies in inventory or delivery records.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.6. &nbsp;Other fields include in thismodule. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOutstanding Balance&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; showsthe outstanding balance for this customer. This field is computer generated andis automatically updated during transactions in the Sales Invoice, AR SummaryEntry, Cash Receipts and Accounts Receivable Application modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotal Sales &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; showsthe total net sales by the customer. This field is system generated and isautomatically updated during transactions in the Sales invoice and AR SummaryEntry.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotal Received PDC’s&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; shows all post-dated cheques receivedfrom the customer. This will increase/decrease depending on the cheque dateinputted in the Cash Receipt module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rReferenceNumber &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; this is used for Delivery Receiptmodule. This is used to track the document that the company uses upon deliveryto outright customers and/or consignee.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rCosignNumber &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This is a unique referencenumber used per consignee to track and monitor documents processed underconsignment module, such as sales invoices.\n\r\n\rStatus&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Indicates whether the customer isclassified as Active, Inactive, or On Hold.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Active\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thecustomer is available for normal use within the system.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Canbe selected in all applicable modules such as Sales Order, DeliveryReceipt, Sales Invoice, AR Summary Entry, Cash Receipt,and Accounts receivables Application.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; On Hold\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;No transactionscan be processed for this customer in the Sales Order, DeliveryReceipt, Sales Invoice and AR Summary Entry modules.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Avalidation message will be displayed upon clicking the Save button.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Statusis typically used for temporary restrictions.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Inactive\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thecustomer will not appear in the customer selection lists in the Sales Order,Delivery Receipt, Sales Invoice, AR Summary Entry, CashReceipt, and Accounts receivablesApplication modules.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Preventsthe creation of any new transactions involving this customer.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Statusis generally used when the customer relationship is permanently discontinued orno longer in use.\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inthe Details section (Sales Agents):\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.1. Selectthe Agent/s,if any. If you know the agent’s code, you may enter it directly under the AgentCode field. If the Agent Code does not exist the lists of Agent will appear:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.2. Waysof selecting Agent from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Agent Code in the spaceprovided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the AgentName inthe space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Agent Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Browse through the list using the Scroll Bar or thekeyboard arrow keys or scroll wheel of optical mouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.3. &nbsp;Clickthe box under the Default column to set the Agent as the customer’sdefault Agent.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTo add another Agent, press the ArrowDown key on your keyboard and repeat steps 8.1 to 8.3.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOr Using your optical mouse, right-clickon the grid, then select Add Agent Entry. A newline will appear for adding another Agent.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.4. Selectthe desired record for deletion. Using your optical mouse, right-click therecord and choose Delete Agent Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.Click the Edit button toedit the record. If theselected Customer is already used in existing transactions, the system willautomatically apply the changes to all related transactions to ensureconsistency and accurate posting. Please be reminded that these changes mayalso affect historical reports since the updated information will be reflectedin previously posted transactions\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.Click the Delete button todelete the record. Deletion will only be allowed if thesaid record has not been used in other modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. In the Details section(Collection / Follow Up):\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThecollection and follow up section of the Customer module may be used to recordall future collections. This section has no effect in other modules and merelyshows the history of collection and follows up. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe Date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe Contact. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe Remarks\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe Follow-up Date or Collection Date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Collection Contact.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Amount\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toadd new record, press the ArrowDown key on your keyboard.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOr Using your optical mouse, right-clickon the grid, then select Add Entry. A newline will appear for adding another entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the desired record fordeletion. Using your optical mouse, right-click the record and choose Delete Entry\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r“ SAVE TO “ Feature\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf you want a current Customer to be included in theSupplier, Agent or Employee Lists, the **SAVE TO** feature maybe used. The **Save To**feature allows you to copy or extract customer information to other modulessuch as Supplier, Agent or Employee.This ensures consistency of data across modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r(e.g. Save to Supplier)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save To button andthe Save To window will appear. Select the module to which the CustomerInformation will be extracted. To select, tick the circle besides theSupplier, Agent or Employee labels. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the OK button tosave the customer information. Click the Cancel button toclose the window. When you select Supplier and click the OK button the Suppliermodule will open.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSince all pertinent information in the Customer wasextracted, then all you have to do is to review that information.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearchinga Customer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of customers will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ways of selecting Customer from thelist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Codein the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Browse through the list using the Scroll Bar or thekeyboard arrow keys or scroll wheel of optical mouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After selecting the Customer, click the OK button. The customer’s details will bedisplayed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r","Customer","topics\\Customer.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  45  801  2025-11-13T07:09:00Z  2025-11-25T10:04:00Z  1  176  1006  8  2  1180  16.00        Print  120  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rDELIVERY RECEIPT   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTheDelivery Receipt module is mainly used to record items that will bedelivered to your customers. This is where you enter the products, quantities, andother delivery details to make sure everything leaving the warehouse isproperly documented. Once the Delivery Receipt is posted, the systemautomatically updates your inventory to reflect that the items have alreadybeen released, and the stock count for those products is reduced.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAsidefrom regular deliveries, this module can also be used to record pull-outtransactions from the customer, depending on the selected Document Type.If the user chooses a document type intended for pull-out, the system willtreat the transaction differently—items will be returned or deducted from thecustomer\'s end and added back to the warehouse inventory. This setup allows themodule to handle both delivery and pull-out processes in one place, making itflexible and easy to use.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOverall,posting a Delivery Receipt (or pull-out transaction) keeps your recordsaccurate, updates your inventory in real time, and helps maintain smoothoperations across sales, warehouse, and accounting.","Delivery Receipt / Pull Out","topics\\Delivery_Receipt.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  36  107  2025-11-20T10:33:00Z  2026-02-24T09:49:00Z  26  3982  22699  189  53  26628  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Delivery Receipt \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Delivery Receipt from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Type isDelivery Receipt, you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Delivery Receipt (items sent to the customer, inventorydecreases)\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Pull-Out (items returned from customer,inventory increases)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the customer list, or if you know thecustomer’s code, enter it directly in the Customer field. If thecode does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea customer is selected, the Bill Tofield is automatically updated based on the customer information. The firstline shows the customer’s full name, and the second line displays the default billingaddress. You can change or type directly in this field ifyou need to specify a different name or billing address. This is useful whenthe transaction needs to be billed to a branch, department, or another contactperson.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheDeliverTo field shows where the items will be sent. It isautomatically filled with the customer’s default delivery address. If thedelivery location is different from default delivery address, you can selectanother address. Click the magnifying glass icon tosee available addresses. If the address is not listed, you can add it in the Customermodule.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTerms field is automatically setbased on the customer’s default terms. You can change it and select differentterms if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. The TransactionType field is automatically filled based on the customer’s defaulttransaction type. However, you may leave it blank or choose a differenttransaction type when using this module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. The BaseArea field is automatically set based on the customer’s default base areaspecified in the delivery address. If the address is changed, the Base Areawill update according to the default base area of the new address. You may alsomanually select a different Base Area if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Enter the P.O. Number, if any.The P.O. Number will come from your customer.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Itemizeddata Grid, allows youto customize the layout by rearranging the columns according to yourpreference. To do this, click on the column header using your optical mouse, hold the click, and drag the header tothe position you want. Once the column is in the desired location, release theoptical mouse button to set the new position. This feature helps you organizethe grid in a way that makes it easier to view and work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Adding and Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r14.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, PriceReference, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the field provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe quantitythat should be delivered.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf the Document Type is setto Delivery Receipt, the quantity you enter must always be a positivevalue. This indicates that items are being released from your warehouse anddelivered to the customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOn the other hand, if the DocumentType is Pull-out, the quantity should be a negative value.This is used when items are being returned or taken back from the customer, sothe negative quantity reflects that the stock is being added back to yourinventory.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unit ofMeasure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdown list to selecta different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe customer has a default price reference set in the system,this field will be automatically filled in—provided that the selected item isincluded under the same price reference. If the item is not includedin the default price reference, this field will remain blank. Or select the price reference, if needed. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheGross Price, Discount 1-5 and adjustment(adj) fields will automatically update according to the chosen pricereference. If no price reference is selected, the fields will use the defaultUOM (Unit of Measurement) pricing value from the Items module. You can stillmanually adjust the pricing value if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehouse where the items willbe released. Choosing the correct warehouse is important because it determineswhich stock location will be deducted once the Delivery Receipt is posted. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto&nbsp;see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rThis field  displays the final price per unit, which is already net  of discounts and adjustments. This field automatically  computed.         \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal  per item and this field automatically computed.  \n\r\n\rFormula: Qty  x Unit Price         \n\r\n\rVat Incl.      \n\r\n\rWhen  checked, it indicates that the item’s Unit Price already  includes VAT. Otherwise, the price is VAT-exclusive.        \n\r\n\rVAT Rate      \n\r\n\rWhen the Vat Incl. is checked the VAT rate automatically  applied, but users can modify it if the item is tax-exempt or subject to a  different rate.        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rServed Qty      \n\r\n\rShows how many delivered item  have already extracted to sales invoice. This field updates automatically  when a Delivery Receipt (DR) extracted to Sales Invoice (SI).  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rThe quantity is automatically converted to the base unit.  For example, if the conversion rate is 10 and the quantity is 3, the served  quantity will be 30 upon extraction to DR or SI.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rFree      \n\r\n\rIndicates  whether the item is given as a free item (zero-price)  as part of a promotion or bundle. When checked, the system will automatically  set the amount to zero but still record the quantity for tracking purposes.        \n\r\n\rOS No.      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Sales Order (SO) number where the extracted details originated. This helps  the user easily identify which Sales Order was used as the source of the  items shown in the transaction.        \n\r\n\rDR No      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Delivery Receipt (DR) number where the extracted details came from. This is  used when performing DR-to-Pull-out extractions, allowing the user to quickly  trace the specific DR that served as the source of the pull-out details.        \n\r\n\rSN      \n\r\n\rOptional,  enter the serial number of items that should be released        \n\r\n\rD button      \n\r\n\rClick the D button to see which module the item has been extracted to        \n\r\n\rPackage      \n\r\n\rTo add components to a package item, click the *Add*  button next to the main item and choose the components you want to include   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the DeliveryReceipt, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 14.1to 14.8. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.10. To delete a line item, select it by clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. When you select a customer, the Default Agent assigned to that customerwill automatically appear in the Agent field. This information is based on thesetup defined in the customer module. If necessary, you can change or replacethe default agent by selecting another one from the dropdown list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. If the selected customer has a Default Price Reference, it willautomatically appear in the corresponding field. This setting determines whichprice scheme or reference will be used when entering items in the DeliveryReceipt. You can change the price reference at any time before adding items byselecting another available option from the dropdown list. This allowsflexibility when a customer qualifies for a different price list or when aspecific price scheme needs to be applied for special transactions.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. If the customer has a Default Discount Rate, the system willautomatically display up to five (5) discount levels in the discount fields.These discount values are retrieved from the customer module and serve as theinitial discount setup for the transaction. You may edit these discount ratesbased on the customer’s agreement or promotional offers, or set them to zero ifno discount applies. This ensures that pricing adjustments are properlyreflected in the Delivery Receipt before finalizing the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen the userclicks the updatebutton (),each item’s discounts are updated based on the document discount percentages.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,comments, or specific instructions related to the Delivery Receipt,if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Delivery Receipt is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rReferenceNumber              This is used to track the documentthat the company uses upon delivery to outright customers and/or consignee.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rConsign No.                          isa unique reference number used per consignee to track and monitor documentsprocessed under consignment module, such as sales invoices.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r20. Enter the appropriate date in the Delivery Date field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentDate: Specifiesthe date that will be recorded in the Inventory Stock Card. Posting thetransaction updates the stock card based on this date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DeliveryDate: Indicatesthe actual date the customer receives the items. It does not impact inventorybut helps track deliveries for reporting purposes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21. The highlighted section displays thetransaction values based on the selected currency and their equivalent amountsin Philippine Peso (PHP). This allows the user to view both the originalcurrency values and their converted peso amounts side by side, ensuringaccuracy in pricing, reporting, and accounting. You may also apply discountamount or adjustments as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;The Currency/Rate fields are automaticallyfilled using the customer’s default currency. You may change these fields ifthe transaction requires a different currency.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf any itemhas insufficient stock, a validation message will be displayed upon clickingSave. Select Yes to proceed with thetransaction or No to cancel. Thisfeature is designed to alert the user of low stock for each item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHowever, ifthe user does not have access to proceed with insufficient stock, the Yes/No button option will not appear,and only the alert will be shown.\n\r\n\r                              \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allreceipts will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the receipts associated with that identifier, while still applying anyother filters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50— means only thosereceipts whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All receiptsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotal Field: Displays the total amount of alltransactions that are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Youcannot cancel a Delivery Receipt (DR) if it has been fully extracted to a SalesInvoice or Pull-Out.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Whena Delivery Receipt is cancelled, the item quantities are automatically returnedto the Inventory Stock Card.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifthe workflow is Sales Order extract to Delivery Receipt, cancelling the DR willalso restore the quantities back to the Sales Order.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r27. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Fields (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields for additionalinformation not covered by the standard fields. You can input specific databased on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract DR Entry Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r28. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract DR Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract DR Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Delivery Receipt module. When youclick this button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as customer details and creates a new transactionentry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Delivery Receipt & Pull-out","topics\\Delivery_Receipt_create.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  13  16  2025-11-20T10:36:00Z  2026-02-24T09:50:00Z  7  879  5011  41  11  5879  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Delivery ReceiptTransaction to Pull-out Transactions\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThisallows items from a Delivery Receipt to be used in Pull-out transactions,making returns or adjustments easier while keeping inventory records accurate.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingDelivery Receipt to Pull-out: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectDelivery Receipt from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select Pull-out in Document Type field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifying glass icon to openthe customer list, or if you know the customer’s code, enter it directly in theCustomerfield. If the code does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract DR&nbsp;for returns then Extractions of&nbsp;Delivery Receipt windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractionsof&nbsp;Delivery Receipt&nbsp;window has two main sections: the top gridshows a list of delivery receipts, and when you select one, the bottom griddisplays all the item details for that delvery receipt.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the entire delivery receipt  for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the delivery receipt.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique delivery receipt  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the delivery  receipt was created.        \n\r\n\rCustomer      \n\r\n\rCode of the customer.        \n\r\n\rPO Number      \n\r\n\rCustomer’s purchase  order number.        \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal value of the  delivery receipt.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rReturns Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be delivered.        \n\r\n\rDelivered Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity delivered to customer.        \n\r\n\rRemaining Returns Qty       \n\r\n\rThe  Remaining Returns Qty column shows how many units of an item are still  eligible for return. When creating a pull-out transaction, the system  automatically converts these quantities into their base unit of measure.  \n\r\n\rExample:  \n\r   If       the remaining quantity is 3 boxes, and 1 box = 10 pieces       (base unit),\n\r       the system will convert it to:\n\r       3 boxes → 30 pieces in the delivery document. \n\r    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;        \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rUnit price based on delivery receipt   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Delivery Receipt transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Delivery Receipt to Pull-out:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Delivery Receipt,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Delivery Receipt, first select thedelivery receipt in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either clickthe X button next to each item or enter the return quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; If the Delivery Receipt (DR) has beenfully extracted to the Sales Invoice (SI) module, it will no longer appear inthe Extractions window.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once the Extractions of Delivery Receipt window is closed, the quantity willappear as negative. Click Scroll Up to view all extracted items, and proceed toupdate the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I.Creating a Direct Delivery Receipt","V. Extraction DR to Pull-out","topics\\Delivery_Receipt_DRPO.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  49  90  2025-11-20T10:35:00Z  2026-02-24T09:50:00Z  8  947  5403  45  12  6338  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Sales Order module toDelivery Receipt module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Sales Order module to the Delivery Receiptmodule. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item details andquantities, making the delivery process faster, more accurate, and less proneto errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingSales order to Delivery Receipts: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectDelivery Receipt from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The DocumentType should be Delivery Receipt.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifying glass icon to openthe customer list, or if you know the customer’s code, enter it directly in theCustomerfield. If the code does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract from Sales Order thenExtractions of Sales Order window will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractions ofSales Order window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofsales orders, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all the itemdetails for that sales order.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire sales order for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the sales order.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique sales order  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the sales order  was created.        \n\r\n\rCustomer      \n\r\n\rCode of the customer.        \n\r\n\rPO Number      \n\r\n\rCustomer’s purchase  order number.        \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal value of the  sales order.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be delivered.        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity originally ordered by the  customer.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe Pending Qty  column shows the remaining quantity of the item available for delivery. When  creating a Delivery Receipt, these  quantities are automatically converted to the base unit of  measure to ensure consistent and accurate inventory tracking,  and  to allow flexibility in case the unit of measure changes upon delivery (e.g.,  an order for 3 boxes can be delivered as 30 pieces).  \n\r\n\rExample:\n\r  If the pending quantity is 3 boxes  and 1  box = 10 pieces (base unit), the system converts 3  boxes into 30 pieces.         \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rUnit price based on Sales Order        \n\r\n\rQty in Base      \n\r\n\rQuantity converted to the  smallest/base unit.        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rConversion quantity based on the Sales  Order module.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Filter by Item Classification: The system only displays sales ordersthat include at least one-line item with the chosen item classification, andthe bottom grid shows only the line items that match the filtered itemclassification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Sales Order transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Sales Orders for Extraction toDR:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Sales Order, clickthe X next to the Doc.ID in the topgrid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Sales Order, first select the salesorder in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either click the Xnext to each item or enter the delivery quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scroll Up to view all extracted items,and proceed to update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I. Creating a Direct Delivery Receipt\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Extractions from SO to DR","topics\\Delivery_Receipt_extract_SODR.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  6  3  2025-11-20T10:34:00Z  2026-02-06T10:32:00Z  2  416  2372  19  5  2783  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the DeliveryReceipt Document\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen you open the Delivery Receipt module, you’ll notice that the screen is blank by default and no transactiondetails are displayed. This is intentional and designed to keep the system runningsmoothly, especially in businesses with a large volume of transactions. If thesystem tried to load all Delivery Receipts automatically, it could become slow,unresponsive, or even freeze due to the large amount of data. By starting witha blank screen, the system avoids these performance issues. You can easily viewthe records you need by using the search or filter options, which only retrievespecific transactions rather than loading everything at once. This approachensures faster response times and a smoother overall experience when workingwith the Sales module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rToview or retrieve an existing Delivery Receipt record:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Search Option window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Usethe available filters to retrieve the desired Delivery Receipt transactions.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID:You can set Document ID to All, which means all receipts will beincluded without restriction based on their unique identifiers. However, if youwant to focus on specific transactions, you can select a particular DocumentID, allowing the system to retrieve and display only the receipts associatedwith that identifier, while still applying any other filters you may have set,such as Document Range, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields let you specify thenumeric range of document numbers you want to search (Example:From 1 To 50 — means only those receipts whose document number is between 1 and50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange:Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is not checked. This meansthe date range filter will be ignored. All receipts matching the Document IDand Document Range will be included, regardless of their date. If you want tofilter by date, you must check the &quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer: If you want to filter by a specificcustomer, click the magnifying glass icon to open the customer list window andselect the desired customer. If you leave it empty, all customers will beincluded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Clickthe OK button. The system will thendisplay all Delivery Receipts that match the filters you selected.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Delivery Receipt & Pull-out","topics\\Delivery_Receipt_find.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  11  2025-11-20T10:34:00Z  2025-11-25T04:22:00Z  2  465  2655  22  6  3114  16.00        Print  120  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Delivery Receipt Document\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBefore proceeding with printing, makesure to perform a search to retrieve the necessary Delivery Receipt data. Onlythe details currently displayed on the module will be included in the printout,so it is important to ensure that the correct record is loaded before printing.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Delivery Receipt window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which includes all receipts without restricting them by theirunique identifiers. If you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to print onlythe receipts associated with that identifier, while still applying any otherfilters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosereceipts whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All receiptsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the receipts that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correct receiptsand that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall receipts that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Delivery Receiptwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing a Delivery Receipt & Pull-out","topics\\Delivery_Receipt_print.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  2  1  2026-02-19T03:19:00Z  2026-02-19T03:20:00Z  1  54  308  2  1  361  16.00        Print  150  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rDEPOSIT  OF COLLECTION   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe DepositCollection module helps you keep track of your customerpayments and bank deposits. When you tag a payment in thismodule, it means that the payment has been successfully deposited into yourcompany’s bank account. This makes it easy to see which payments are completeand which are still pending.","Deposit of Collection","topics\\Deposit_of_Collection.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  CCC_MARIENEL  14  183  2026-02-18T09:32:00Z  2026-02-24T10:04:00Z  5  708  4042  33  9  4741  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Deposit of Collection\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Deposit of Collectionfrom the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Bank where collections will bedeposited\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe deposit date in the Document Date field.By default, this field is set to the current date, however you can modify it ifnecessary to reflect the actual deposit date.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Onthe TagPayments page, click the X button to tag thecollections that need to be deposited.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Youcan tag multiple collections as long as they have the same deposited bank anddeposit date.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Total Deposits field - Displays thetotal amount of all collection that are currently tagged.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe SearchDocument button to quickly look up a specific collectionwithout having to scroll through the entire list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the tagging you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To modify an existing record, click the Editbutton. This will allow you to update the information as needed, and once finished,you can save your changes to apply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. A confirmationmessage may appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to post the record or No to cancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is posted,the system will automatically updatethe Bank Reconciliation module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage, the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction is cancelled,the system will automatically update theBank Reconciliation module.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftercancellation, the tagged details will disappear so they can be re-tagged in thenext transaction. The details of the cancellation will appear in thecancellation remarks.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Deposit of Collection","topics\\Deposit_of_Collection_howto.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  18  32  2025-10-07T11:47:00Z  2025-10-30T13:55:00Z  9  795  4537  37  10  5322  16.00        Print  110  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rEMPLOYEE   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Employee Module is used to input and manageessential employee information, including address and contact information. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAddingan Employee\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Employee from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp; \n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the Employee Code and Employee Name in their respective fields.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter theE-mail address, if any.&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select&nbsp;Departmentand Enter the Address, Contact Person ,TelephoneNumber and Fax Number. &nbsp; \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the&nbsp;Area &nbsp;andenter the Zip Code, if any. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding an Address:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifyingglass besides the Address label and the Address List window will open:\n\r\n\r&nbsp; \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Add button to add a new address.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the Address, Contact Person, TelephoneNumber and Fax Number.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select the&nbsp;Area and enter the Zip Code,if any.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To add another address, follow stepsa to d.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rf.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Close button to close thewindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Savebutton in the Navigation Toolbar to save the record. Click the Cancelbutton to discard changes made. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Edit button toedit the record. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Delete button todelete the record. Deletion will only be allowed if thesaid record has not been used in other modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. &nbsp;Updating Employee status:&nbsp; If theemployee has resigned,click the Resignedfield or checkbox in the Employee Module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r“ SAVE TO “ Feature\n\r\n\rThe**Save To** feature allows you to copy or extract employee information to othermodules such as Customer, Supplier, Agent or Collector. This ensuresconsistency of data across modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r(e.g. Save to Customer)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save To button and the Save To window will appear.Select the module to which the Employee Information will be extracted. Toselect, tick the circle besides the Customer,Supplier, Agent or Collector labels. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the OK button to save the Employee information.Click the Cancel button to close the window. When you selectCustomer and click the OK button the Customer module will open.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSince all pertinent information in theEmployee was extracted, then all you have to do is to review that information.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Save buttonto save the record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;Searchingan Employee\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp; Clickthe Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. The list of Employee will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp; Ways of selecting Employee from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;Type the first few characters of the Employee Code in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;Type the first few characters of the Employee Name in the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;Type a specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Employee Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;Browse through the list using the Scroll Bar or thekeyboard arrow keys or scroll wheel of optical mouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;After selecting the employee, click the OK button. The employee’s details willbe displayed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Employee","topics\\Employee.htm","\n\r\n\r               ","Front Version","topics\\Front_Version.htm","   user  user  3  1  2025-12-23T04:30:00Z  2025-12-23T04:31:00Z  1  77  444  3  1  520  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rINVENTORY  ADJUSTMENT   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Inventory Adjustment Module helps keep inventoryrecords accurate by allowing users to correct stock quantities when there is adifference between what the system shows and what is actually available in thewarehouse or store.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThese differences can happen because of damaged items,expired products, counting mistakes, theft, or system errors. This module makessure those corrections are recorded properly, approved when required, and savedfor future reference.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Inventory Adjustment","topics\\Inventory_Adjustment.htm","   user  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  18  54  2025-12-22T08:13:00Z  2026-02-24T10:01:00Z  15  2334  13308  110  31  15611  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Inventory Adjustment \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Inventory Adjustment from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe necessary remarksin the space provided to clearly indicate the purpose or reason for theadjustment. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, this field isused to categorize the transaction and this is mandatory.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Itemized data Grid, allows you to customize the layout byrearranging the columns according to your preference. To do this, click on thecolumn header using your optical mouse, hold theclick, and drag the header to the position you want. Once the column is in thedesired location, release the optical mouse button to set the new position.This feature helps you organize the grid in a way that makes it easier to viewand work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addingand Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r8.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;PriceReference filter is not applicable on this module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the fields provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf you enter a positive quantity,this indicates that items are being added from the Warehouse.\n\r\n\r\n\rHowever, if you enter a negative quantity, thisindicates that items are being deducted from the Warehouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unitof Measure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdownlist to select a different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehousewhere the item will be adjusted.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese columns  are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s setup or  any other user-defined reference.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the InventoryAdjustment, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps8.1 to 8.6. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line item, select itby clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Inventory Adjustment is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allinventory adjustments will be included without restriction based on theirunique identifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, youcan select a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve anddisplay only the Inventory Adjustment associated with that identifier, whilestill applying any other filters you may have set, such as Document Range or Date Range.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoseinventory adjustments whose document number is between 1 and 50 will beincluded).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All inventoryadjustments matching the Document ID and Document Range will be included,regardless of their date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the&quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage, the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. Click Other Information button, if needed. And the Other Information window will open, this window providesadditional details related to the transaction, such as grouping, custom fields,posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This section allowsyou to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract IA Entry Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract IA Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract IA Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Inventory Adjustment module. Whenyou click this button, the system automatically extracts all information fromthe existing transaction—such as items,&nbsp;quantities and etc... and createsa new transaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Inventory Adjustment","topics\\Inventory_Adjustment_creating.htm","   user  user  3  4  2025-12-23T03:51:00Z  2025-12-23T04:22:00Z  3  440  2509  20  5  2944  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing an Inventory Adjustment / BatchPrinting\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Inventory Adjustment window willappear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allInventory Adjustments will be included without restriction based on theirunique identifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, youcan select a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve anddisplay only the Inventory Adjustment associated with that identifier, whilestill applying any other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, or Date Range.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoseInventory Adjustments whose document number is between 1 and 50 will beincluded).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All InventoryAdjustments matching the Document ID and Document Range will be included,regardless of their date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the&quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the Inventory Adjustments that match the currently set filtercriteria before printing them. This is useful for verifying that you haveselected the correct Inventory Adjustments and that the printed output will beas expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall Inventory Adjustments that match the currently set filter criteria to theprinter.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the InventoryAdjustment window.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing an Inventory Adjustment","topics\\Inventory_Adjustment_print.htm","   user  CCC_MARIENEL  5  3  2025-12-23T03:50:00Z  2026-02-06T10:29:00Z  2  111  634  5  1  744  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Inventory Adjustment from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the inventoryadjustment.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Inventory Adjustment","topics\\Inventory_Adjustment_searching.htm","  Business Box - SQL       version  INVENTORY       COSTING             \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Inventory Costing","topics\\Inventory_Costing.htm","\n\r\n\r               Inventory : \n\r    Inventory Costing    Inventory Adjustment    Requisition   Slip     Issuance Slip     Stock   Requisition     Stock   Transfer \n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Inventory","topics\\Inventory_menu.htm","   user  user  2  0  2025-12-22T07:43:00Z  2025-12-22T07:43:00Z  1  76  434  3  1  509  16.00        Print  108  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rISSUANCE SLIP   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Issuancemodule is specifically designed to manage and track thedistribution of items from the central inventory to various departments withinan organization. Whenever items such as materials, supplies, or equipment areissued, this module records the transaction in a structured and organizedmanner. Each issuance entry automatically adjusts the inventory stock levels,ensuring that the system reflects the current quantity of items available inreal time.","Issuance Slip","topics\\Issuance_Slip.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  21  27  2025-12-18T06:39:00Z  2026-02-24T10:02:00Z  17  2607  14864  123  34  17437  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Issuance Slip \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Issuance Slip from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the employee list, or if you know the employee’scode, enter it directly in the Employee Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the employee list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Employee from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theEmployee Code in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the EmployeeName inthe space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Employee Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once an employee is selected, the Department field is automaticallyfilled with the employee’s default department from the Employee module. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number, thenumber field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, if applicable.This field is used to categorize the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Itemized data Grid, allows you to customize the layout byrearranging the columns according to your preference. To do this, click on thecolumn header using your optical mouse, hold theclick, and drag the header to the position you want. Once the column is in thedesired location, release the optical mouse button to set the new position.This feature helps you organize the grid in a way that makes it easier to viewand work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addingand Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r9.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;PriceReference filter is not applicable on this module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the fields provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventory thatis currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unitof Measure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdownlist to select a different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehousewhere the item will be released.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rRS number      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Requisition Slip (RS) number where  the extracted details originated. This helps the user easily identify which  Requisition Slip was used as the source of the items shown in the  transaction.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the Issuance,press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 9.1 to 9.6. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line item, select itby clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,or specific instructions related to the Issuance, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf any itemhas insufficient stock, a validation message will be displayed upon clickingSave. Select Yes to proceed with thetransaction or No to cancel. Thisfeature is designed to alert the user of low stock for each item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHowever, ifthe user does not have access to proceed with insufficient stock, the Yes/No button option will not appear,and only the alert will be shown.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Issuance Slip is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to update theinformation as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes to applythem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allIssuance slips will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the Issuance slip associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, Employee or Department.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoseIssuance slips whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All Issuance slipsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Employee:If you want to filter by a specific employee, click the magnifying glass iconto open the employee list window and select the desired employee. If you leaveit empty, all employees will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Department:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific department, or Ifyou leave it empty, all departments will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage, the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, such asgrouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the peISon who posted thetransaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract IS Entry Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract IS Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract IS Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Issuance Slip module. When you clickthis button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as employee details, items,&nbsp;quantities and etc.and creates a new transaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Issuance Slip","topics\\Issuance_Slip_create.htm","   user  CCC_MARIENEL  21  105  2025-12-22T02:57:00Z  2026-02-24T10:02:00Z  7  1057  6031  50  14  7074  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Requisition Slip moduleto Issuance Slip module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Requisition Slip module to theIssuance Slip module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item detailsand quantities, making the delivery process faster, more accurate, and lessprone to errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Issuance Slip from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the employee list, or if you know theemployee’s code, enter it directly in the Employee Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the employee list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Employee from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theEmployee Code in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the EmployeeName inthe space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Employee Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once an employee is selected, the Department field is automatically filledwith the employee’s default department from the Employee module. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, this field isused to categorize the transaction and this is required.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract from Requistion Slip then Extractions of Requisition Slip window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractions ofRequisition Slip window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofrequisition slips, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all theitem details for that requisition slip.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire requisition slip for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the requisition slip.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique requisition slip  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the requisition  slip was created.        \n\r\n\rDepartment      \n\r\n\rDepartment of Employee        \n\r\n\rEmployee Name      \n\r\n\rComplete employee name   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be issued.        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity originally ordered by the  employee.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe Pending Qty  column shows the remaining quantity of the item available for delivery. When  creating an Issuance Slip, these quantities are  automatically converted to the base unit of measure  to ensure consistent and accurate inventory tracking, and to allow  flexibility in case the unit of measure changes upon delivery (e.g., an order  for 3 boxes can be issued as 30 pieces).  \n\r\n\rExample:\n\r  If the pending quantity is 3 boxes  and 1  box = 10 pieces (base unit), the system converts 3  boxes into 30 pieces.         \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Filter by Item Classification: The system only displays requisition slipsthat include at least one-line item with the chosen item classification, andthe bottom grid shows only the line items that match the filtered itemclassification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific requisition slip transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TaggingRequisition Slip for Extraction to Issuance Slip:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Requisition Slip,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a RequisitionSlip, first select the requisition slip in the top grid,then in the bottom grid, either click the X next to each item or enterthe delivery quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.  Proceed to update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section&nbsp;I. Creating an Issuance Slip. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Extraction from Requisition Slip to IS","topics\\Issuance_Slip_extraction_RSIS.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  4  1  2025-12-18T08:47:00Z  2025-12-18T09:04:00Z  3  480  2739  22  6  3213  16.00        Print  130  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing anIssuance Slip / Batch Printing\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Issuance Slip window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allIssuance slips will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the Issuance slip associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, Employee or Department.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoseIssuance slips whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the \"With date range\" checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All Issuance slipsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the \"With daterange\" box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Employee:If you want to filter by a specific employee, click the magnifying glass iconto open the employee list window and select the desired employee. If you leaveit empty, all employees will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Department:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific department, or Ifyou leave it empty, all departments will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the Issuance slips that match the currently set filter criteriabefore printing them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected thecorrect Issuance slips and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall Issuance slips that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Issuance Slipwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing an Issuance Slip","topics\\Issuance_Slip_print.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  1  2025-12-18T08:46:00Z  2026-02-06T10:29:00Z  2  104  599  4  1  702  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the IssuanceSlip \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Issuance Slip from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the issuanceslip.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Issuance Slip","topics\\Issuance_Slip_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  26  480  2025-11-04T04:23:00Z  2025-11-05T06:11:00Z  10  1357  7737  64  18  9076  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rITEM  PRICE REFERENCE   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThismodule is used to manage and maintain different pricing schemes for all itemsin the system. It \n\r\n\rallowsyou to define multiple price lists such as Retail Price, Whole Price,or any other custom price scheme that your company may require. Each pricescheme can also be assigned as a default price reference under the Customermodule, ensuring that thecorrect price is automatically applied during transaction entry.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWithinthis module, Standard and Criteria serve as groupclassifications that help organize and manage your pricing recordsefficiently. Once the price references are set up, they are automatically usedin related transaction modules such as Sales Order, Delivery Receipt,and Sales Invoice, reducing manual entry and preventing pricing errors.This ensures that customers are always charged accurately based on theirassigned pricing scheme.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rInaddition, this module supports defining multiple discount levels and price adjustmentsper item, providing flexibility for implementing special pricing arrangementssuch as promotions, seasonal discounts, or customer-specificdeals.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAddinga Price Reference / Price Scheme\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectItem Price Reference from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inthe left panel, select Standard or Criteria. (e.g. Criteria)\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe title of the price scheme in the Code field\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inthe right panel, add the items that will be included under the new pricingcode. There are multiple ways adding items \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typing code on the grid.\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Itemcode inthe space provided (1);\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the ItemDescription in the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Using your optical mouse, right-clickon the grid. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; select AddItem Entry and the Item list window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen the Item List windowappears:\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You may filter items by ItemClass or Unit.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To include all items, tick the Allcheckbox under Selective.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To include only specific items, untickAll and manually select the desired items from the list.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;After selecting, click OK toconfirm or Cancel to close the window.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Or,select Copyfrom Other Price Reference and thecorresponding window will appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFrom the “Copy FromOther Price Reference Items” window\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the source of the price referencefrom the Copy From dropdown list.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You may filter items by ItemClass or UOM to refine the list.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;By default, the All checkboxis selected, meaning all items from the selected price reference are included.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To copy only specific items, untick Alland select the desired items from the list.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click OK to proceed or Cancelto close the window without copying.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Atthe lower portion of the module, you can find the Extract button.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractionOptions:\n\r\n\rItems\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When theItems option is selected, the system will extract all active items from theItem Master File and display them in the grid.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rPrice Reference\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When thePrice Reference option is selected, the dropdown list beside it becomesenabled.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;From thislist, you can choose an existing price scheme such as Retail Price, WholePrice, or any custom price reference previously defined in the system.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting a price reference and clicking Extract, the system will load allitems along with their existing prices and discount details into the grid. Youcan then review or update the pricing information as needed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncethe items are added to the grid, update the necessary fields:     \n\r\n\rField      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rChoose how the item is sold (e.g., PC, KG, SET).        \n\r\n\rPrice      \n\r\n\rEnter the item’s selling price based on the selected price  reference.        \n\r\n\rDisc 1–5      \n\r\n\r(Optional) Specify up to five discount levels for the  item.        \n\r\n\rAdj      \n\r\n\r(Optional) Apply any additional price adjustments.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button in the Navigation Toolbar to save the record. Click the Cancelbutton to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Edit button toedit the record. Once thechanges are saved, the updated Price scheme will automatically take effect inall succeeding transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Delete button todelete the record. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTwoTypes of Searching:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Search by Price Reference Code\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe left panel then Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of price codes will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting price code from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the PriceReference Code in the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Price Reference Code;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Price Reference Code, click the OK button. The list of items will be displayed on the right panelor in the grid.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Search by Item under selected Pricereference code.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the Price reference code on the left panel.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Grid,then the Findbutton in the Navigation Toolbar\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting price code from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Item ID in the fieldprovided (1);\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the ItemDescription in the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Price Reference Code, click the OK button. The list of items will be displayed on the right panelor in the grid.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Item Price Reference","topics\\Item_Price_Reference.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  118  1117  2025-10-28T02:30:00Z  2025-11-06T06:55:00Z  27  4491  25599  213  60  30030  16.00        Print  120  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version         \n\r\n\rITEMS   \n\r\n\rThis module is where you createand manage all products and other items that the company uses in its dailytransactions. This can include items that you sell to customers, itemsthat you buy from suppliers, raw materials, or even consumable supplies usedinternally.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIn this module, you will record important details such asthe item name, description, category or classification, and unit ofmeasurement. Additional information like pricing and other references may alsobe added so the system can properly recognize and use the item in differentprocesses.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOnce the item is saved, it becomes available throughout thesystem and can be selected when creating Purchase Transactions, Sales Transactions,or Inventory movements. This ensures that the same item details are usedeverywhere, helping keep your data accurate and consistent.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOverall, this module serves as the main storage for all iteminformation, and it is required before any item-related transaction can beprocessed in the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding an Item\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Items from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter theunique&nbsp;Item Code and corresponding Description in theirrespective fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter theabbreviation, If Any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toupload an image for the item: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.1. Clickthe button beside the Picture field to open the Item Photo window.\n\rThis will allow you to attach an image for the selected item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.2. Oncethe Item Photo window appears, click “Load Picture” and browse for theimage file stored on your computer. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.3. Afterselecting the file, the image will be displayed inside the window and linked tothe item record. Click X toclose the Item Photo window.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tick the Auto Generate checkboxif you want the system to automatically create the Item Code.\n\rWhen enabled, the system will generate the Item Code based on the ItemClassification code selected in the Class 1 field, combined with aseries number, upon saving the record.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf you prefer to assign your ownItem Code manually, simply leave the Auto Generate checkbox uncheckedand enter your desired code directly into the Item Code field.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Active checkbox is selected bydefault, which means the item will be available for use in alltransaction modules.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rIf this checkbox is unticked,the item will be deactivated and will no longer appear in the item selectionlist during transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectappropriate Item Type. This field is used to classify whatkind of item you are creating in the system. You can choose the appropriatecategory from the dropdown list. The available options are:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; FinishedGood – A product that is already complete and ready for sale.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; OfficeSupplies – Items used for office operations (e.g., paper, toner,pens).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; RawMaterial – Materials used to manufacture or assemble anotherproduct.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Service– Non-physical items such as labor, repair, or installation services.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the unique Barcode per item, If any. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Having a registered barcode allowsthe system to immediately pull up the item information using a barcode scanner,minimizing manual typing and reducing errors. This is especially useful duringsales, inventory counting, receiving of goods, and other warehouse operationswhere speed and accuracy are important.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;If the item does not have a physicalbarcode yet, you may also assign your own internal barcode number, provided itfollows your company’s coding standard. Otherwise, you may leave this fieldblank for items that do not require barcode identification, such as services ornon-inventory items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Inthe Information section:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Item Classifications,If Any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Item Class fields are used to categorize and group youritems according to your company’s classification structure. These classes serveas additional levels of grouping or tagging that can be used for filtering,reporting, and organizing items within the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can define up to 10classification levels (Class 1 to Class 10), depending on how detailed youwant your item categorization to be. Each class can represent a differentcategory or attribute of the item, such as:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Class 1– Main Category (e.g., Electronics, Furniture, Office Supplies)\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Class 2– Subcategory (e.g., TV Accessories, Chairs, Paper Products)\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Class 3– Brand or Manufacturer\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Class 4– Model, Type, or Specification\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Class 5–10– Additional classifications (e.g., Color, Size, Series, Department, etc.)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can select predefined valuesfrom the dropdown list beside each class field. These values are usually set upin your Item Classification underOther Files module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rProperly assigning itemclassifications helps improve item search, reporting, and inventoryorganization. For example, when generating reports, you can easily filter orsummarize items based on a specific class such as Brand, Category,or Department.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Thesmall button beside each Item Class fields isused to clearthe selected classification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf you have previously selected aclass (for example, under Class 1, Class 2, etc.) and you want to remove orchange it, simply click this button. The selected classification will becleared from the field, allowing you to choose another one or leave it blank.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature is helpful when youneed to correct a wrong classification or update the item’s category withoutredoing the entire record.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Default&nbsp;UOMand Base UOM, this isrequired.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDefaultUOM      orDefault Unit of Measure specifies the standard measurement unit used forthis item in most transactions.\n\rExamples include Piece (pc), Box (box), Dozen (doz), Kilogram (kg), or Meter (m)—dependingon how the item is normally sold, purchased, or stored.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen this item is selected in atransaction (such as Sales, Purchase, or Inventory Adjustment), the system willautomatically use the Default UOM. This ensures consistency and reduces errorswhen recording quantities.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can still change the UOM during atransaction if needed, but setting the Default UOM helps speed up data entryand maintain accuracy in reports.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBaseUOM          or BaseUnit of Measure serves as the smallest or fundamental unit for the item inthe system. It is the reference point used for conversion when an item hasmultiple units of measure.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rForexample:\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; BaseUOM: Piece (pc)\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; OtherUOMs: Box (1 box = 10 pcs), Carton (1 carton = 100 pcs)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAll inventory quantities, costcomputations, and conversions are recorded based on the Base UOM. Setting thiscorrectly is important to ensure accurate stock counts and valuation,especially when your item can be sold or purchased in different units.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Base UOM is usually defined onlyonce when creating the item and should not be changed once transactions existto avoid inconsistencies in reports and inventory balances.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSample Scenario: How Default UOM and Base UOM Work Together\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLet’s say you are adding an itemcalled “Ballpen”.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Base UOM: Piece (pc)– This is the smallest unit of the item that the system recognizes. All stockcounts are stored in pieces.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Default UOM: Box (box)– The item is usually sold or purchased by the box, where 1 box = 10 pieces.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen you record a purchasetransaction for 2 boxes, the system automatically converts it to 20pieces (based on the conversion setup). Inventory records and reports willstill show the total in the Base UOM (pieces) to keep consistency, buttransactions will display the Default UOM (boxes) for convenience.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis setup allows flexibility inhandling items that can be sold, purchased, or stored in different quantitieswhile maintaining accurate stock levels in the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Youcan enter the theoreticalor actual weight per unit (e.g., 2.5 kg per piece). Thisinformation can also be useful when generating reports.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Other available fields: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLastDate Purchased              This field displays the most recent datewhen the item was purchased.\n\r\n\r\n\rIt is automatically updated by the system each time a purchase transactioninvolving this item is recorded.\n\r\n\r\n\rThis helps users track the latest procurement activity and monitor howfrequently the item is being bought.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLastDate Sold                          This field shows the most recent datewhen the item was sold.\n\r\n\r\n\rSimilar to the purchase date, it is automatically updated by the system once asales transaction for this item is processed.\n\r\n\r\n\rThis information helps in analyzing product movement, identifying slow-movingitems, and planning inventory replenishment.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rStockson Hand                         This fielddisplays the current available quantity of the item in the inventory.\n\r\n\r\n\rIt reflects the total number of units that are currently in stock across allwarehouses (if multi-warehouse setup is enabled).\n\r\n\r\n\rThe quantity shown here automatically updates whenever there are sales,purchases, or inventory adjustments. This helps users instantly check if anitem is available before processing a transaction.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotalOrders to Supplier        This field shows the total quantity ofthe item currently ordered from suppliers but not yet received.\n\r\n\r\n\rIt is based on purchase order module in the system.\n\r\n\r\n\rThis helps monitor pending deliveries and assists in inventory planning toavoid overstocking or stockouts.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotalOrders by Customer     This field shows the total quantity ofthe item currently ordered by customers but not yet delivered.\n\r\n\r\n\rThe information shown here is based on data from the Sales Order module.\n\r\n\r\n\rThis helps track customer demand and plan fulfillment schedules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotalUnposted                         This field displays the total quantityfrom transactions that have not yet been posted to the inventory.\n\r\n\r\n\rUnposted transactions (such as pending sales, purchases, or adjustments) arenot yet reflected in the official stock balance.\n\r\n\r\n\rThis indicator helps users ensure that all transactions are reviewed and postedfor accurate reporting.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Particulars, if any. The Particulars may be any additional notes, remarks, ordescriptions related to the item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Inthe SKU section:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe SKU (Stock Keeping Unit) section is used to record the unique codesor item references assigned to the item by different customers or suppliers.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis allows you to maintain a singleinternal item record in your system while keeping track of each customer’s orsupplier’s own item codes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rEach customer or supplier may have adifferent SKU or product reference for the same item. Recording these detailshelps ensure smooth communication and accurate data exchange duringtransactions such as sales, purchase orders, or system integrations.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe table contains the followingcolumns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;CompanyType - Identifies whether the reference code belongs to aCustomer or Supplier.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;CompanyCode - The specific customer or supplier code where the SKU isapplicable.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;ExternalCode - The item code or reference number used by that customer orsupplier for this item.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Company Type (e.g., Customer)\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou already know the Customer’sCode, you may enter it directly in the field provided.If the CompanyCode does not exist, a list of&nbsp;Customers or&nbsp;Supplierswill automatically appear for you to select.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Ways of selecting&nbsp;Customer orSupplier&nbsp;from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type the first few characters of the Code in thefield provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Namein the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the External Code of Item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExample:\n\r\n\rForinstance, your company’s internal code for an item may be 011B BRACKET, whileone of your customers refers to the same item as TV-BRK-65. You can record thatexternal code in the system so it will appear on printed forms such as theDelivery Receipt, Sales Invoice, and other related documents.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toadd another SKU, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeatsteps 11.1 to 11.3.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOrUsing your opticalmouse, right-click on the grid,then select AddItem Entry. A new linewill appear for adding another SKU. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the desired record fordeletion. Using your optical mouse, right-click the record and choose DeleteItem Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Inthe Prices section:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe section is used to define and manage the selling prices ofan item under different pricing schemes.\n\r\n\r\n\rThis allows the system to handle multiple price setups for the same item,depending on the customer, transaction type, or pricing level.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rEach entry in this sectioncorresponds to a specific Price Reference, which represents a pricingscheme — for example, Retail Price, Wholesale Price, DealerPrice, or any custom-defined price level used by your company.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe dropdownlist, and the existing&nbsp;PriceReferences or Price Schemes willappear. Choose from the list if you want to addthis item to an existing Price Reference or Price Scheme.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Indicatesthe unit of measure (UOM) for which theprice is defined (e.g., Piece, Box, Set).The price and discounts will apply to the selected UOM.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe selling price of the item for the selected Price Reference and Unit. Thisis the amount that will automatically appear during sales transactions underthat pricing scheme.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Discount rate up to 5levels. If any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter Adj (Adjustment)for additional price adjustment, If any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toadd another Price, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeatsteps 12.1 to 12.5.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOrUsing your opticalmouse, right-click on the grid,then select AddItem Entry. A new linewill appear for adding another Price. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the desired record fordeletion. Using your optical mouse, right-click the record and choose DeleteItem Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Inthe Packages section:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section is used to define the componentsthat make up an item, both for selling and purchasing purposes.\n\r\n\r\n\rThis feature is useful when an item is sold or bought as a set, bundle, orpackage containing multiple sub-items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Adding components of the item forSelling and Purchase.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou already know the&nbsp;Item Code, you mayenter it directly in the field provided.\n\rIf the Item Code does not exist, a list of available items will automaticallyappear for you to select.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Ways of selecting&nbsp;Item&nbsp;fromthe list \n\r\n\r                              \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Item ID in the fieldprovided (1);\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the ItemDescription in the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe quantity of each component included in the package when selling.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toadd another Component, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard andrepeat steps a to b.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rOrUsing your opticalmouse, right-click on the grid,then select AddItem Entry. A new linewill appear for adding another component. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the desired record fordeletion. Using your optical mouse, right-click the record and choose DeleteItem Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Inthe&nbsp;UOM (Unit of Measurement) section:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section allows you to definethe different measurement units that can be used for an item. Forexample, by piece, box, dozen, or carton.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUOM                  Refers to the Unit ofMeasurement for the item (e.g., PIECE, BOX, DOZEN).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rConversion      Definesthe conversion factor or ratio between the base unit and the specified unit (e.g.,1 BOX = 10 PIECES → Conversion = 10).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rCurrency          Indicates the currency used forpricing (e.g., PHP, USD).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSellingPrice     Shows the selling price for the selected UOM.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rMinSelling       The minimumallowable selling price for that unit.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFOB                    This is the cost that the supplier givesyou. This is automatically updated based on purchases made by the company. Theunit cost is gross of tax.          \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLanded Cost    This includes the freight charges andother additional charges the product might incur. This is gross of tax.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOld FOB            Thisfield is automatically updated whenever the FOB price changes. It reflects the previous FOB cost before the most recent update\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rInvty Cost         This fieldis automatically updated when you run Inventory Costing\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTaxable             Indicates whetherthe item is subject to tax (✔ means taxable, ✖means not taxable).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rVATIncl            Specifiesif the selling price already includes VAT (✔ means VAT is included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toadd another UOM(Unit of Measurement), press the Arrow Downkey on your keyboard. A new line willappear then update the necessary columns.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOrUsing your opticalmouse, right-click on the grid,then select AddItem Entry. A new linewill appear for adding another UOM. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the desired record fordeletion. Using your optical mouse, right-click the record and choose DeleteItem Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. Inthe Warehouse section:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section is where you defineand assign the warehouse where the item is stored. Each item canbe linked to one or more warehouse codes, depending on where it is physicallylocated.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWHCode                       Where the item is stored (e.g.,Manila Warehouse, Main Warehouse). Each code represents a specific warehouselocation or branch.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rMaxLevel                     This is where you canindicate the maximum stock quantity allowed for the item in a specificwarehouse. Setting a maximum level helps the company control overstocking andmaintain proper inventory levels. This field can also be used in reports tomonitor items that have exceeded their maximum stock levels.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rCriticalLevel                This is where you can indicatethe minimum stock quantity allowed for the item before it is considered low instock or needs replenishment. Setting a critical level helps ensure that youcan reorder items on time and avoid stockouts that may affect sales oroperations. This field can also be used in reports to monitor items that arenearing their minimum stock levels.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSlowMoving – Days  Indicates the number of days used toclassify an item as slow-moving. When an item has not been sold or moved withinthis number of days, it will be considered slow-moving in reports.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSlowMoving – Qty     Indicates thequantity threshold that classifies an item as slow-moving. If the item’s stockquantity exceeds this limit without corresponding sales or movement, it will beidentified as slow-moving.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBalance                        This field displays the current availablequantity of the item per Warehouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOrderQty                      This field displays the total quantityof the item per warehouse that has been ordered by customers but not yetdelivered. The information shown here is based on data from the Sales Ordermodule.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rPO Qty                          This field showsthe total quantity of the item per warehouse that has been ordered fromsuppliers but not yet received. The information displayed here is based on datafrom the Purchase Order module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUnposted Qty             This field shows the totalquantity of the item per warehouse from transactions that are not yet posted orfinalized. These quantities are still pending, and therefore the quantity are not yet reflected in the actual inventory balance.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rActive                             Indicates whetherthe item is active and available for use in that warehouse (✔ means active).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDateSold                      This field shows the most recent datewhen the item was sold. It is automatically updated by the system each time asales transaction involving this item is recorded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDatePurchased         This field displays the most recent datewhen the item was purchased. Similar to the Date Sold, it is automaticallyupdated by the system once a purchase transaction for this item is processed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;There are two ways to addwarehouses for the item\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Double-click the WH Codeheader using your optical mouse, and all available warehouse codes will be automaticallyadded to the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Press the Arrow Down key onyour keyboard. A newline will appear for adding another warehouse. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOrUsing your opticalmouse, right-click on the grid,then select AddItem Entry. A new linewill appear for adding another warehouse. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usingyour opticalmouse, right-click on the grid,then select AddItem Entry. A new linewill appear for adding another warehouse.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the desired record fordeletion. Using your optical mouse, right-click the record and choose DeleteItem Entry. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. Inthe Inventory section:\n\r\n\r** not applicable **\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Inthe GL Default section:\n\r\n\r** not applicable **\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19.Click the Edit button toedit the record. If theselected Item is already used in existing transactions, the system willautomatically apply the changes to all related transactions to ensureconsistency and accurate posting. Please be reminded that these changes mayalso affect historical reports since the updated information will be reflectedin previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r20. Click the Delete button todelete. Deletion will only be allowed if the said record has notbeen used in other modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearchingan Item\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of items will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting&nbsp;Item&nbsp;from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Item ID in the fieldprovided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the ItemDescription in the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the screen. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","Items","topics\\Items.htm","&nbsp;  Master Files :\n\r  Customer  Agent  Collector    Supplier    Employee    Items  Other Files     Item Price   Reference      Price Update     Audit Trail     Setup -   Trading    \n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;","Master Files","topics\\Master_Files.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  4  4  2025-10-21T04:08:00Z  2025-10-21T05:30:00Z  1  121  690  5  1  810  16.00        Print  110  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version         \n\r\n\rOther  Files   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Other Files module allows you to set up and manage additional information that will be used throughout the system. Some fields found in master files and transaction modules are user-defined, meaning you can decide what data or classifications will appear in those fields. Through this module, you can create and customize the reference values needed for these user-defined fields, ensuring that the information entered by the users follows a consistent format. This helps standardize data entry across different modules and allows the system to properly categorize and interpret the information based on the options you have configured. By defining these values in advance, the system becomes more flexible and adaptable to your company’s specific requirements.\n\r\n\r                                                                                                                 &nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Other Files","topics\\Other_Files.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  12  21  2025-10-23T02:06:00Z  2025-10-30T14:22:00Z  6  489  2789  23  6  3272  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rCOMPANYGROUP\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section is used for Customers or Suppliers that have multiple branches. Insome cases, one branch may settle the payables of another branch. When thisoccurs, the related Customers/Suppliers should be grouped under the same CompanyGroup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAddinga Company Group\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Company Group. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Company Groups. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the field will be enabled. Enter the Name/Descriptionin the field provided. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record.&nbsp;Click the Cancel button to discard changes made. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew company group will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Edit button to modify therecord. If the selected Company Group is already used in existing transactions,the system will automatically apply the changes to all related transactions toensure consistency and accurate posting. Please be reminded that these changesmay also affect historical reports since the updated information will bereflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearchinga Company group\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of company groups will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Company group from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Company group from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Company groupwill then appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Company Group","topics\\Other_Files_Company_group.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  17  114  2025-10-27T02:05:00Z  2025-10-30T14:24:00Z  10  1057  6031  50  14  7074  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rDOCUMENT LIST\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThissection is used to create and manage the Document IDs that are appliedthroughout the different modules of the system. These document IDs serve asunique references for each transaction and ensure proper identification, tracking,and reporting. They are commonly used in Sales, Purchases, Inventory, Banking,and General Ledger transactions. By setting up the appropriate document codesin this section, users can maintain standardized documentation and streamlinethe processing of financial and inventory-related entries across the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Document ID\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Document List. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Document IDs. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. The Document Listwindow will appear on screen.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Document ID and Description in thefields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tickthe checkbox of Auto Numbered, if any and Indicate the last Document No. for Sales, Purchases, Inventory, Banking, and GeneralLedger transactions. (If the auto column has not been ticked, this field may beleft empty\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe module where the Document IDwill be reflected. Click the dropdownlist to display the available module options and choose theappropriate module where this document will be used (e.g., Sales order,Delivery receipt, Sales invoice and etc.).\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select the GL Book where the Document ID should be posted. Click the dropdown list to displaythe available options and choose the appropriate ledger (e.g., Sales Book,Purchase Book, Cash Receipt , Cash Disbursement andGeneral Ledger) depending on the module selected.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the X marker under the DR/CR(Debit or Credit) column to define the normal balance of the Document ID.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the selected module is A/RSummary Entry and you choose DR (Debit), the system will only allow positivevalues for this document ID.\n\rIf you choose CR (Credit), the system will only allow negative values.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;However, if the selected moduleis A/P Summary Entry, the behavior is the opposite.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\rWhen you select DR (Debit), the system will only accept negativevalues, and if you select CR (Credit), the system will only accept positivevalues.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis setup ensures that thetransaction amount follows the correct accounting treatment based on whether itis related to Accounts Receivable (A/R) or Accounts Payable (A/P).\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tick the checkbox of vatable, ifany.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Tickthe Shared w/ Other Modules, if thedocument ID is used to multiple module. The Document / Module Setup window willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toadd a new line, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard to move to the nextavailable row.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required details in each column according to the information needed for theselected module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete the selected row, clickthe X under the D column. A prompt message will appear for confirmation.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf the Document ID has already beenused in a transaction, the record can no longer be deleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew document ID will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Click the Edit button to modify the record. If the selected Document ID isalready used in existing transactions, the system will automatically apply thechanges to all related transactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting.Please be reminded that these changes may also affect historical reports sincethe updated information will be reflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Click the Delete button to remove the selected record. However, deletion is not advisable if the recordhas already been used in a transaction, as this may affect data integrity andhistorical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Document ID\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of document ID will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Document ID from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the DocumentID inthe field provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Document ID from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Document IDwill then appear on the screen. ","Document List","topics\\Other_Files_Document_List.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  36  121  2025-10-21T06:02:00Z  2025-10-30T14:21:00Z  1  744  4247  35  9  4982  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rBanks\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis sectionis used to record and maintain the list of bank accounts that your company usesfor various financial transactions.\n\r\n\r\n\rThese bank accounts are essential references when performing processes such as CashReceipts, DepositCollections, Cash Disbursements, ClearingIssued Checks, Bank Adjustments, and BankReconciliation.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Bank\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectOther Files from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On the left panel labeled Listof Other Files, click Banks.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Bank Accounts.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter theunique Bank Code and thecorresponding Name/Description inthe fields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tick this checkbox if the account iscompany-owned. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;If the Own Account checkbox is not selected, the bank will only appear in the Cash Receipts module and will be usedas a reference for client-issued checks. However, if the bank is taggedas Own Account, it will still appear in the Cash Receipts module but will also beappear in other modules such as Deposit of Collection,&nbsp;Cash Disbursement, Clearing of IssuedChecks, Bank Adjustment, and Bank Reconciliation for company-relatedtransactions. This allows the system to distinguish between banks used only forreceiving customer payments and those that are officially owned and used by thecompany for disbursements and reconciliation.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tick thecheckbox if you want the check numbers to be generated automatically. Oncechecked, an “Input Check No.” window will appear where you should enter thelast check number that was used. After saving, the system will automaticallycontinue the numbering from that value for all future transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rNote: \n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Make sure the last check number youenter is correct, because the system will continue the sequence from thisnumber going forward.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;This feature application in CashDisbursement module\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the appropriate currency forthe bank account.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe new bank will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Editbutton to modify the record. If the selected Bank is already used in existingtransactions, the system will automatically apply the changes to all relatedtransactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting. Please be remindedthat these changes may also affect historical reports since the updatedinformation will be reflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Delete button to remove the selected record. However, deletion is not advisable if the record hasalready been used in a transaction, as this may affect data integrity andhistorical reports.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Bank\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of banks will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Bank from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the BankCode inthe field provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Bank from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Bank will thenappear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Banks","topics\\Other_Files_files_banks.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  33  51  2025-10-21T07:18:00Z  2025-10-30T14:22:00Z  6  553  3153  26  7  3699  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rCOMPANY CLASS\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThissection is used to record the desired classifications for your customers andsuppliers. This will also be used as a filter options on some reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Company Class onthe list (Class 1 – 5)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Onthe left panel labeled Listof Other Files, click Company Class.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Company Classes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickNew on the Navigation Toolbar\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the field will be enabled. Enter the Name/ Description&nbsp;in the field provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Youcan indicate the Level in the field provided. The systemallows levels 1 to 5 only, so you just need to enter anumber from 1 to 5 depending on the hierarchy or classification of the companyclass.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor example:\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Trading → Level 1\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If you have a sub-class underTrading, it could be Level 2, and so on up to Level 5.\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe new company class will now appearin the list.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Edit button to modify therecord. If the selected Company Class is already used in existing transactions,the system will automatically apply the changes to all related transactions toensure consistency and accurate posting. Please be reminded that these changesmay also affect historical reports since the updated information will bereflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Company Class\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of compant class willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting&nbsp;Company Class&nbsp;from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Company Class from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Company Class willthen appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Company Class","topics\\Other_Files_files_company_class.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  21  22  2025-10-21T08:15:00Z  2025-10-30T14:31:00Z  8  713  4065  33  9  4769  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rCURRENCY\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThissection is used to set up and manage all the currencies that your company willuse in the system. This is helpful when your business deals with foreignclients, suppliers, or bank accounts because it allows the system to recognize andcorrectly apply each currency in transactions. By adding the necessarycurrencies here, the system can automatically convert amounts and keep reportsaccurate, without the need to compute manually.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThissection also allows you to add, updateand monitor exchange rates from timeto time. This feature is useful in cases that exchange rates change quickly.For instance, there is a sudden drop in the value of one currency, and all yourtransactions are based on this currency. If your exchange rate is not updatedyou might be charging your customers higher or lower than the real price.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Currency\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Onthe left panel labeled Listof Other Files, click Currency.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The right panel displays the list ofexisting Currencies.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter the Name/ Description and Rate in the fields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe new currency code will nowappear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpdating Currency Rate\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from themenu to open the module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Onthe left panel labeled Listof Other Files, click Currency.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Choose the currency that you want toupdate.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Edit button on theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the updated exchange rateunder the Rate column.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click Save to apply thechanges. The History column will automatically update with the newinformation.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Currency \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of&nbsp;currencies will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting&nbsp;Currency&nbsp;from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Currency from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Currency willthen appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Currency","topics\\Other_Files_files_currency.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  23  18  2025-10-21T09:29:00Z  2025-10-30T14:31:00Z  5  474  2705  22  6  3173  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rDEPARTMENT\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section is where you enter the listof departments in your company for selection in the PurchaseRequest,&nbsp;Requisition,&nbsp;Issuance Slip and Petty Cashmodules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Department \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SelectOther Filesfrom the Menu andthe module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Onthe left panel labeled List of Other Files, click Department. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Departments.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the field will be enabled. Enter theName / Description in the field provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record.Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew department will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Editbutton to modify the record. If the selected Department is already used inexisting transactions, the system will automatically apply the changes to allrelated transactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting. Please bereminded that these changes may also affect historical reports since theupdated information will be reflected in previously posted transactions\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletion isnot advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as this mayaffect data integrity and historical reports.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Department\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of departments will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting&nbsp;Department&nbsp;from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Department from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Department willthen appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Department","topics\\Other_Files_files_Department.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  18  21  2025-10-22T07:52:00Z  2025-10-30T14:32:00Z  1  625  3567  29  8  4184  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rITEMCLASSIFICATION\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section is where you enter the differentsublevels of item classification. Sublevels help organize your products intosmaller, more specific groups, making it easier to manage and find them. For example,a category like “Electronics” can have sublevels such as “Mobile Phones,”“Laptops,” and “Accessories.”\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAll the information youenter here will automatically appear in the Items module. This ensures thatyour item data is consistent and easy to use across the system. Properlysetting up sublevels helps with organizing inventory, tracking items, andgenerating accurate reports.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;Addingan Item Class to the list\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On the left panel labeled Listof Other Files, click Item Classification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Item Classifications.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter the uniqueCode and the corresponding Name/Description in the fields provided. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You can indicate the Level inthe field provided. The system allows levels 1 to&nbsp;10 only,so you just need to enter a number from 1 to&nbsp;10 depending on the hierarchyor classification of the Item. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew item classification will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Editbutton to modify the record. Ifthe selected Item Classification is already used in existing transactions, thesystem will automatically apply the changes to all related transactions toensure consistency and accurate posting. Please be reminded that these changesmay also affect historical reports since the updated information will bereflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Delete button to remove the selected record. However, deletion is not advisable if the record hasalready been used in a transaction, as this may affect data integrity andhistorical reports.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching an ItemClassification\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of item classification will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ways of selecting Item Classificationfrom the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the ItemClass Code inthe field provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After selecting the Item classificationfrom the search window, click the OK button. The selected Item classification will then appear onthe screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Item Classification","topics\\Other_Files_Item_Classification.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  13  14  2025-10-23T03:35:00Z  2025-10-30T14:25:00Z  6  659  3757  31  8  4408  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rMiscellaneousCharges\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThissection is used to set up and maintain the list of miscellaneous charges thatmay be applied to purchase transactions within the Purchase Invoice module. Thesecharges represent additional costs that are not part of the standard purchaseprice of goods or services, such as freight fees, handling costs, deliverysurcharges, customs duties, brokerage fees, or other similar expenses. Definingthese charges in advance ensures consistency in naming, accounting treatment,and reporting.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rMiscellaneous charges also play an important role in thecomputation of landed cost,particularly for imported or transferred goods. Landed cost represents the true total cost of acquiring an item,which includes not only the purchase price, but also all incidental expensesincurred until the goods reach the warehouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rByproperly defining these miscellaneouscharges in the master setup, the system can accurately distribute and allocatethese costs to the related inventory items during landed cost computation. Thisensures that the item value in inventory reflects its actual acquisition cost,rather than just the supplier invoice price.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a MiscellaneousCharge\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Miscellaneous Charges. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Miscellaneous Charges. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter theMiscellaneous&nbsp;Code and&nbsp;Name / Descriptioninthe fields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew miscellaneous charge will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Editbutton to modify the record. If the selected Miscellaneous Charge is already used in existing transactions, thesystem will automatically apply the changes to all related transactions toensure consistency and accurate posting. Please be reminded that these changesmay also affect historical reports since the updated information will bereflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a MiscellaneousCharge\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of Miscellaneous Charges will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Miscellaneous Charge from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the MiscellaneousCode inthe space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Miscellaneous Charge from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected MiscellaneousCharge will then appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Miscellaneous Charges","topics\\Other_Files_Miscellaneous_Charges.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  19  190  2025-10-23T07:46:00Z  2025-10-30T14:26:00Z  7  750  4279  35  10  5019  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rPayment Type\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section contains the list of predefined payment codes(such as Cash, Cheque, EWT, and other modes of settlement)that are used when recording both collections and disbursements in the system.These payment types determine how a transaction will be treated and reported inthe accounting process.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBy defining the payment type in this module, the system willknow how to categorize the inflow or outflow of funds, which modules it willappear in, and how it will be reflected in bank transactions andreconciliation. The payment types configured here will be selectable intransaction screens such as Cash Receipt, Cash Disbursement, DepositCollection, and Clearing of Issued Cheques, depending on thesettings assigned (i.e., Collect, Check, and Auto Deposit/Bank).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding Payment Type\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Payment Type. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Payment Types. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r At     the lower portion of the module, the fields will be enabled. Enter the Name / Description and Group     in the fields provided. Grouping of     Payment Type is useful in report generation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tick the checkbox for COLLECT and CHECK, if needed\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rCOLLECT                             Indicatesthat this payment mode is used for receiving collections from customers orpayments to suppliers. Once enabled, the payment mode will be reflected in the DepositCollection, Clearing of Issued Cheques, and Bank Reconciliationmodules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rCHECK                                 Specifiesthat the payment mode represents a cheque transaction. When enabled,cheque-related fields such as Cheque Number and Cheque Date willbecome available in the Cash Receipt and Cash Disbursementmodules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the Bank where the collectionwill be automatically deposited, if Any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifan Auto Deposit / Bank is assigned to a payment mode, the system willautomatically tag the selected bank during the Cash Receiptcreation. As a result, the payment is considered already deposited,and it will nolonger appear in the Deposit Collectionmodule for manual depositing.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew payment type will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Editbutton to modify the record. If the selected payment type is already used inexisting transactions, the system will automatically apply the changes to allrelated transactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting. Please bereminded that these changes may also affect historical reports since theupdated information will be reflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as this mayaffect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Payment Type\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of payment type will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Payment Type from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Payment Type from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Payment Typewill then appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Payment Type","topics\\Other_Files_Payment_type.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  13  6  2025-10-24T03:43:00Z  2025-10-30T14:32:00Z  1  583  3328  27  7  3904  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rPettyClassification\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section contains the list of classifications used forpetty cash transactions. These classifications represent the different types ofminor or incidental expenses that are typically disbursed through the company’spetty cash fund, such as small office supplies, transportation allowances, orquick reimbursements.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBy defining the petty cash expense classifications in thismodule, the system will be able to properly categorize and record petty cashdisbursements under the correct expense accounts during posting. Theseclassifications will be available for selection when creating petty cashvouchers or petty cash liquidation entries, ensuring that the nature of eachpetty cash expense is accurately identified for reporting and audit purposes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a PettyClassification\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Petty Classification. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Petty Classifications. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the field will be enabled. Enter the Name/ Description in the field provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rThe new pettyclassification will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Editbutton to modify the record. If the selected petty classification is alreadyused in existing transactions, the system will automatically apply the changesto all related transactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting. Pleasebe reminded that these changes may also affect historical reports since theupdated information will be reflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a PettyClassification\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of petty classification will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Petty Classification from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Petty Classification from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected PettyClassification will then appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Petty Classification","topics\\Other_Files_Petty_Classification.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  15  2025-10-24T03:59:00Z  2025-10-30T14:20:00Z  6  535  3050  25  7  3578  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rTax Codes \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis sectioncontains the list of withholding tax codes that are used when processingtransactions subject to tax deductions, such as Expanded Withholding Tax (EWT)or other government-mandated withholding requirements. These tax codes will beavailable for selection during the creation of transactions in the PurchaseInvoice and AP Summary Entrymodules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOnce a taxcode is applied, the system will automatically compute the correspondingwithholding amount, reduce the Accounts Payable accordingly, and record thewithholding liability without the need for manual calculation. Proper setup oftax codes ensures accurate tax computation, compliance with regulatoryrequirements, and correct posting of withholding obligations for financialreporting.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAddinga Tax code\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Tax code. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing tax codes. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter the Code,Name / Description and Rate in the fields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew tax code will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Edit button to modify the rateof selected tax code. Once the changes are saved, the updated tax rate willautomatically take effect in all succeeding transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Tax Code\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of tax code will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Tax Code from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Tax Code in the fieldprovided (1); \n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Tax Code from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Tax Code willthen appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Tax Codes","topics\\Other_Files_Tax_Codes.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  9  30  2025-10-24T06:18:00Z  2025-10-30T14:27:00Z  6  553  3157  26  7  3703  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rTERMS OF PAYMENT\n\r\n\r\n\rThis section is used to define the allowable payment terms that your companyapplies to both customers and suppliers or vendors. These terms specify theagreed number of days or conditions within which payment must be settled for salesand purchase transactions. Examples include standard terms such as 7 days,15 days, 30 days, or COD (Cash on Delivery).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBy setting up the Terms of Payment in this module, thesystem can automatically determine the due date of an invoice based on thetransaction date and the selected payment term. These terms will be availableduring the creation of customer invoices and supplier bills, ensuringconsistent and accurate computation of payment due dates, aging schedules, andcredit control monitoring.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Term of Payment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Term of Payment. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing terms of payments. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter the Name/ Description and Days in the fields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew term of payment will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Edit button to modify the record. If the selected term is alreadyused in existing transactions, the system will automatically apply the changesto all related transactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting. Pleasebe reminded that these changes may also affect historical reports since theupdated information will be reflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Term\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of Term will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Term from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Term of payment from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Term of paymentwill then appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Terms of Payment","topics\\Other_Files_terms.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  9  30  2025-10-24T07:44:00Z  2025-10-30T14:32:00Z  1  526  2999  24  7  3518  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rTRANSACTION GROUP\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThissection is used to classify the company’s transactions according to their typeor category. It supports up to five levels of transaction grouping, allowingyou to organize transactions from general classifications down to more specificsubcategories for better tracking and reporting.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Transaction Group\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Transaction Group. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Transaction Groups. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter the Name/ Description and Level in the fields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Inthe Levelfield, enter a number from 1 to 5 to represent thehierarchy or classification of the transaction group.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew transaction group will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Editbutton to modify the record. If the selected transaction group is already usedin existing transactions, the system will automatically apply the changes toall related transactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting. Please bereminded that these changes may also affect historical reports since theupdated information will be reflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a TransactionGroup\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of transaction group will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Transaction Group from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Transaction Group from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Transaction Groupwill then appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Transaction Group","topics\\Other_Files_Transaction_Group.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  9  40  2025-10-24T09:02:00Z  2025-10-30T14:33:00Z  1  562  3209  26  7  3764  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rTRANSACTION TYPE\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThissection is used to classify the company’s transactions by their type orcategory. These transactions are grouped based on what module they will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Transaction Type\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Transaction Type. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Transaction Types. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the field will be enabled. Enter the Name/ Description in the field provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew transaction type will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tickthe checkbox(es) in the Transaction Type grid to indicate which modules thisTransaction Type will be used in.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;A/R→ Sales Order, Delivery Receipt, Sales Invoice\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;A/P→ Purchase Request, Purchase Order, Receiving Report, Purchase Invoice\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;C/R→ Cash Receipt\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;C/D→ Cash Disbursement\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Inventory→ Inventory Adjustment, Requisition, Issuance, Stock Requisition, StockTransfer\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Editbutton to modify the record. If the selected transaction type is already used in existingtransactions, the system will automatically apply the changes to all relatedtransactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting. Please be remindedthat these changes may also affect historical reports since the updatedinformation will be reflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a TransactionType\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of transaction type will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Transaction Type from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Transaction Type from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Transaction Typewill then appear on the screen. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Transaction Type","topics\\Other_Files_Transaction_type.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  11  8  2025-10-24T06:55:00Z  2025-10-30T14:33:00Z  1  550  3140  26  7  3683  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rUNIT OF MEASUREMENT\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section is used to define the units of measurement thatwill be assigned to items in the Items module. These units determine how itemquantities will be recorded, displayed, and transacted throughout the system.You may create both base units (e.g., piece, bottle, pack) and bulkunits (e.g., box, case, carton) depending on how the item is stored,purchased, or sold.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rProper setup of units of measure is important to avoidconfusion in inventory handling, especially for items that can be transacted indifferent packaging levels. For example, an item may be purchased by the boxbut sold by the piece, and defining the units of measure correctly ensuresaccurate conversion, costing, and stock tracking.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Unit of Measurement\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Unit of Measurement. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Units of Measurement. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter the Name/ Description and Conversion in the fields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew unit of measurement will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Editbutton to modify the record. Once the changes are saved, the updated conversionwill automatically take effect in all succeeding transactions. Please bereminded that these changes may also affect historical reports.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Unit ofMeasurement\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of units of measurement will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Unit of Measurement from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Unit of Measurement from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected Unit of Measurementwill then appear on the screen. ","Unit of Measurement","topics\\Other_Files_UnitOfMeasurement.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  12  14  2025-10-24T07:26:00Z  2025-10-30T14:33:00Z  1  695  3964  33  9  4650  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rWAREHOUSE\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis section is used to define all warehouses or storagelocations utilized by your company for keeping inventory items. Each warehouseentered here becomes available for selection in the Product module and in all inventory-relatedtransactions. These warehouse records help the system determine where items arestored, transferred, and retrieved during receiving, issuance, and stockmovement processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDefining warehouses properly is important for accurateinventory monitoring, especially when the company maintains multiple storagelocations or branches. This ensures that stock levels are correctly tracked perlocation and that inventory postings reflect the correct warehouse balances.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWarehouses created in this module can also be set as defaultfor all items or manually assigned per item, depending on the company’sinventory setup and control requirements. Once configured, the warehouseinformation will be used in Sales Order,Delivery Receipt, Sales invoice, Purchase Request, Purchase Order, ReceivingReport, Purchase Invoice, Inventory Adjustment, Requisition, Issuance, StockRequisition and Stock Transfermodules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Warehouse\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Other Files from the Menu and the module will open: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;On theleft panel labeled List ofOther Files, click Warehouse. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Theright panel displays the list of existing Warehouses. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;At the lower portion of the module,the fields will be enabled. Enter thewarehouse Code, Name/Description, Group WH and Address in thefields provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Save button to savethe record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUponclick Save button, the validation message will now appear on screen.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Clickthe YES button if you want thiswarehouse to be automatically set as the default warehouse for all items in theItems module. Otherwise, click NO if you prefer to manually assign thewarehouse to each item in Items module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThenew warehouse will now appear in the list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Editbutton to modify the record. If the selected warehouse is already used inexisting transactions, the system will automatically apply the changes to allrelated transactions to ensure consistency and accurate posting. Please bereminded that these changes may also affect historical reports since theupdated information will be reflected in previously posted transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Delete button to remove theselected record. However, deletionis not advisable if the record has already been used in a transaction, as thismay affect data integrity and historical reports. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Warehouse\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of warehouses will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting Warehouse from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the WarehouseCode inthe field provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Name\\Descriptionin the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Name\\Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Warehouse from the search window, click the OK button.The selected Warehouse will thenappear on the screen. ","Warehouse","topics\\Other_Files_Warehouse.htm","        &nbsp;Business Box - SQL       version      PETTY       CASH\n\r\n\r1 . Main Screen\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r2 . \" Other Information \" button\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r    &nbsp;","Petty Cash","topics\\Petty_Cash.htm","        &nbsp;Business Box - SQL       version      PETTY CASH       REPLENISHMENT\n\r\n\r","Petty Cash Replenishment","topics\\Petty_Cash_Replenishment.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  18  389  2025-11-05T06:12:00Z  2025-11-06T07:01:00Z  8  920  5247  43  12  6155  16.00        Print  120  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rPRICE  UPDATE   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Price Update module is used tomodify item pricing by assigning new unit prices, applying discounts, addingadjustments, or setting mark-ups. This feature allows you to maintain full controlover your pricing strategy.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHowto use:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;I.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Price Update from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAsyou can see, the data grid is split into two sections:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Left side: Shows the columns that stay in place soyou can always see them.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Right side: Shows the all of the columns that youcan scroll through horizontally while the left side stays visible.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTomove the split line, use your optical mouse to click the black bar located at thebottom of the screen in this module. Hold the click and drag the bar to yourdesired position, then release it to set the new split location.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;II.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Filter Options\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ItemClass: \n\r\n\rTick the checkbox or click themagnifying glass icon to open the Filter by Item Classification window. Onceclosed, the data grid will automatically display only the items that match theselected classification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;UOM(Unit of Measure): \n\r\n\rTick the checkbox to enable the dropdownlist of available units (e.g., PC, KG). Select the desired UOM to filter theitems accordingly.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PriceReference: \n\r\n\rTickthe checkbox to enable the dropdown list of price references. Select thedesired reference to filter the items accordingly.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;III.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Legend\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Current Pricing Displayed in blue columns, showsexisting price data before any changes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;New Pricing Displayed in green columns, shows thevalues that will be applied, allowing you to compare before finalizing\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;IV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Price Update Options\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Whenthe Update Price option is selected,the fields for entering new pricing values (such as base price, discount percentages,and adjustment amount) are enabled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; When the Mark-up option is selected, the fields for entering mark-up rateand amount are enabled.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;V.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Steps:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe appropriate pricing method (UpdatePrice or Mark-up) based on your intended changes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usingyour optical mouse, double-click the Mark header to tag all items displayed inthe grid. Otherwise, you can tag each item individually by clicking on itscorresponding checkbox. The New Pricing columns will automatically updateaccording to the method you selected.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Youmay also directly enter the new pricing values (such as the base price,discount percentages, and adjustment amount) in the grid. Make sure thecorresponding checkbox is ticked before entering any new values.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toapply the new pricing, click the POSTbutton in the navigation toolbar. A validation message will appear on thescreen.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickYES on the first prompt. A secondconfirmation message will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickYES again to confirm and finalizethe update. The new prices will then be applied to the marked items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rReminder:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Only marked items will be updated.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Beforeposting, double-check all new pricing values to ensure accuracy.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching an Item\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of items will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Waysof selecting&nbsp;Item&nbsp;from the list \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Item ID in the fieldprovided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the ItemDescription in the field provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the field provided (3) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the item from the search window, click the OKbutton. The selected item will be displayed in the data grid. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Price Update","topics\\Price_Update.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  46  238  2026-01-13T05:53:00Z  2026-02-24T09:57:00Z  25  3985  22718  189  53  26650  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Purchase Invoice / PurchaseAdjustment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Type isPurchase Invoice, you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Purchase Invoice is used to record the purchase of goodsor services from a supplier. It serves as the official record of the purchase.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Purchase Adjustment is used only when goods previouslypurchased are returned to the supplier. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know the supplier’scode, enter it directly in the Supplier Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea supplier is selected, the Payable Tofield is automatically updated based on the Supplier Master Files. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Payable To field can be manually edited when necessary. Users may type directly intothis field to specify a different payee name,such as:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Adifferent registered business name\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Abranch name or alternate payee\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Aspecific individual authorized to receive payment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThisflexibility allows users to handle special payment arrangements while stillusing the same supplier record.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Itis automatically filled with the supplier’s address. If the address isdifferent from default address, you can select another address. Click the magnifyingglass icon to see available addresses. If the address is notlisted, you can add it in the Suppliermodule.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTerms field is automatically setbased on the supplier’s default terms. You can change it and select differentterms if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Select Transaction Type, this field is automatically set based on thesupplier’s default transaction type under supplier module. You can change it&nbsp;asneeded or leave it blank.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Itemizeddata Grid, allows youto customize the layout by rearranging the columns according to yourpreference. To do this, click on the column header using your optical mouse, hold the click, and drag the header tothe position you want. Once the column is in the desired location, release theoptical mouse button to set the new position. This feature helps you organizethe grid in a way that makes it easier to view and work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Adding and Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, PriceReference, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in item module,possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the field provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventory thatis currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order –Pending Sales Order - UnpostedQuantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r \n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe Quantity thatshould be received.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; When the Document Type is set to Purchase Invoice, the quantity entered must always be positive. This indicates that itemsare being received into your warehouse from the supplier. The transaction willbe reflected in the accounts payable ledger as anincrease in what the organization owes the supplier, and inventory is increasedaccordingly.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; When the Document Type is set to Purchase Adjustment, the quantity should be negative. This is used when items are beingreturned to the supplier. The negative quantity ensures that the stock isremoved from inventory, and the accounts payable ledger is adjusted to reducethe amount owed to the supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unit ofMeasure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdown list to selecta different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Multiple Unit of Measure (UOMs)should be assigned in the Item module so that youcan select the appropriate UOM when using this module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default FOB (Free on Board) price from the Items moduleis automatically displayed in the Gross Price column. Youmay modify this value or manually enter a purchase price if required. Discounts 1–5 and any adjustments (Adj)can also be applied as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehouse where the receiveditems will be added. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto&nbsp;see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rThis field  displays the final price per unit, which is already net  of discounts and adjustments. This field automatically  computed.         \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal  per item and this field automatically computed.  \n\r\n\rFormula: Qty  x Unit Price         \n\r\n\rLanded Cost      \n\r\n\rTotal cost of a product from  the supplier to its final destination. It represents the true cost of importing  goods, not just the purchase price.        \n\r\n\rVat Incl.      \n\r\n\rWhen  checked, it indicates that the item’s Unit Price already  includes VAT. Otherwise, the price is VAT-exclusive.        \n\r\n\rVAT Rate      \n\r\n\rWhen the Vat Incl. is checked the VAT rate automatically  applied, but users can modify it if the item is tax-exempt or subject to a  different rate.        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s setup  or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rPO No.      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Purchase  Order (PO) number when data is extracted from the Purchase Order module to the Purchase  Invoice module.        \n\r\n\rRR No      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Receiving  Report (RR) number when data is extracted from the Receiving  Report module to the Purchase Invoice  module.        \n\r\n\rREF PI      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Purchase Invoice (PI) number when data is extracted from the Purchase  Invoice data to Purchase adjustment.        \n\r\n\rSN      \n\r\n\rOptional,  enter the corresponding serial number of received items.        \n\r\n\rPackage      \n\r\n\rTo add components to a package item, click the *Add*  button next to the main item and choose the components you want to include   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the PurchaseInvoice, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 12.1to 12.7. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r12.9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line item, select itby clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Select the Expanded Withholding Tax (EWT) code as needed. The system willdisplay the corresponding rate and automatically compute the EWT amount.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,comments, or specific instructions related to the Purchase Invoice,if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Purchase Invoice is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. The Currency/Ratefields are automatically filled using the supplier’s default currency. You maychange these fields if the transaction requires a different currency.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. The highlighted section displays thetransaction values based on the selected currency and their equivalent amounts inPhilippine Peso (PHP). This allows the user to view both the original currencyvalues and their converted peso amounts side by side, ensuring accuracy inpricing, reporting, and accounting. You may also apply discount amount oradjustments as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Clickingthe magnifying glass beside the Applied Amount field will display a promptindicating that the transaction is still unposted.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r20. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21. Click the Post buttonin the Navigation Toolbar thatlocated at the top of the window. And the Batch Posting window willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID:You can set Document ID to All, which means all transactions willbe included without restriction based on their unique identifiers. However, ifyou want to focus on specific transactions, you can select a particularDocument ID, allowing the system to retrieve and display only the purchaseinvoice or purchase adjustment associated with that identifier, while stillapplying any other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields let you specify thenumeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example:From 1 To 50 — means only those purchaseinvoices or purchase adjustment whose document number is between 1 and50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange:Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is not checked. This meansthe date range filter will be ignored. All transactions matching the Document IDand Document Range will be included, regardless of their date. If you want tofilter by date, you must check the &quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier: If you want to filter by a specificsupplier, click the magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list window andselect the desired supplier. If you leave it empty, all suppliers will beincluded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match your selectedcriteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotalField: Displays the total amount of alltransactions that are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOKto proceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be includedin the posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Once the transaction has been posted, itis considered final and cannot be edited or deleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22. Once the transaction is posted, theMagnifying Glass button (Applied Amount) can be used. Click the magnifying glass button and Payment / Application window willappear on screen. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDividedinto three sections:\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; View Payments – Displays payments made in the Cash Disbursement module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; View Application Breakdown – Displays the breakdown of offsets made inthe Accounts Payable Application module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Generate CM Application – Allowsyou to apply or offset the current transaction against a CM/DM transaction.Once applied, it will be reflected in the ViewApplication Breakdown section and in the AccountsPayable Application module \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Enter the date and reason forcancellation, then click OK toconfirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOtherInformation Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; TransactionGroups (up to 5 dropdown list) - This section allows you to categorizeor group transactions for reporting or organizational purposes. You may selectvalues from the dropdown lists as defined in your system setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; CustomFiles (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; TransactionPosting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted – Displays the date and time whenthe transaction was officially posted to the system.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User – Indicates the username of theperson who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rImportation Charges:\n\r\n\r25. Click Importation Charge Button, If needed. Youcan add the miscellaneous charge if the transaction is not yet posted.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Two ways of adding Misc. Charge \n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Extractionfrom Cash Disbursement– Enter the LC number and click the Extract CV button. The correspondingdetails will be displayed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rEnsure thatthe LC number entered here matches the LC number in Cash Disbursement. If theydo not match, the details will not be extracted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Manually Adding: \n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;pressthe Arrow Down key on your keyboard then the new line will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe preferred Misc. Charge code.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe corresponding charged amount \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26. To delete a charge, the misc. chargecode column must not be empty. Any charge with a zero amount will beautomatically removed when you close this window.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r27. Enter the total dollar amount in the LCValue field and the corresponding LC Rate. You may change the LC Rate ifneeded, and the currency rate on the main screen will be updated accordingly. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r28. Update other fields if needed. Thesefields have no effect on the transaction but can be used for report generation asrequired.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract Purchase Invoice Entry Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r29. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract Purchase Invoice EntryButton, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract Purchase Invoice Entry button isused to copy or duplicate the current transaction under Purchase Invoicemodule. When you click this button, the system automatically extracts allinformation from the existing transaction —such as supplier details, items,quantities, prices, and etc... and creates a new transaction entry with thesame details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Purchase Invoice / Adjustment","topics\\Purchase_Invoice_and_Adjustment_creating.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  6  72  2026-01-21T08:23:00Z  2026-02-24T09:58:00Z  7  980  5591  46  13  6558  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Purchase Invoice toPurchase Adjustment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis process is used to correct ormodify purchase transactions by referencing the original Purchase Invoice. Itis commonly applied when items need to be returned to the supplier due todefects, damages, or incorrect orders. By extracting details directly from theoriginal invoice, this process ensures accurate updating of inventory andfinancial records, minimizes errors, and provides proper documentation foraudits and supplier follow-up.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingReceiving Report to Return Slip:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheDocument Type should be PurchaseAdjustment.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know thesupplier’s code, enter it directly in the Supplier Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usingoptical mouse, right-click anywhere withinthe module and choose Extract PurchaseInvoice for Returns then Extractionsof Purchase Invoice window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractions ofPurchase Invoice window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofpurchase invoice, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all theitem details for that purchase invoice.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire receiving report for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the purchase invoice.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique purchase invoice  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate when the purchase  invoice made.        \n\r\n\rSupplier      \n\r\n\rCode of the supplier  who delivered the items        \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal amount of  purchase invoice.    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rReturn Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity of the item that should be  returned to the supplier.        \n\r\n\rDelivered Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity of the item received from the  supplier.        \n\r\n\rRemaining Returns       \n\r\n\rShows the remaining quantity  of the item available for return. When creating a Purchase Adjustment, these  quantities are automatically converted to the base unit of measure to ensure  accurate inventory tracking. This also allows flexibility if the unit of  measure changes on return.  \n\r\n\rExample: If 3 boxes are pending return and 1  box = 10 pieces, the system converts 3 boxes into 30 pieces.        \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rConv      \n\r\n\rItem conversion        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDetailed description of the item.        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rPurchase price per unit of the item.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Purchase Invoice transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging of Purchase Invoice forextractions:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Purchase Invoice,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Purchase Invoice, first select theinvoice in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either click the Xnext to each item or enter the return quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAs you cansee, when the extraction window is closed, the system automatically converts thequantity to a negative value. This indicates that the items are being returnedto the supplier, ensuring that inventory records are adjusted correctly andreflect the reduction in stock.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Whena Purchase Adjustment is posted, the amount payable to the supplier is reduced,and inventory is adjusted accordingly.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I. Creating a Receiving Report / Return.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","VI. Extraction Purchase Invoice to Purchase Adjustment","topics\\Purchase_Invoice_and_Adjustment_extraction_PIPA.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  15  52  2026-01-15T08:10:00Z  2026-02-24T09:57:00Z  7  997  5687  47  13  6671  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Purchase Order moduleto Purchase Invoice module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Purchase Order module to thePurchase Invoice module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item detailsand quantities, making the delivery process faster, more accurate, and lessprone to errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingPurchase Order to Purchase Invoice: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheDocument Type should be PurchaseInvoice.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know thesupplier’s code, enter it directly in the Supplier Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usingoptical mouse, right-click anywhere withinthe module and choose Extract fromPurchase Order then Extraction ofPurchase Order window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extraction ofPurchase Order window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofpurchase orders, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all the itemdetails for that purchase order.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire purchase order for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the purchase order.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique purchase order  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the purchase order  was created.        \n\r\n\rSupplier      \n\r\n\rCode of the supplier.        \n\r\n\rPayable To       \n\r\n\rRefers to the person  or company that will receive the payment for the Purchase Order.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be received.        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity entered in purchase order.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe Pending Qty  column shows the remaining quantity of the item available for receiving. When  creating a Receiving report, these  quantities are automatically converted to the base unit of  measure to ensure consistent and accurate inventory tracking,  and  to allow flexibility in case the unit of measure changes upon delivery (e.g.,  an order for 3 boxes can be received as 30 pieces).  \n\r\n\rExample:  If the pending quantity is 3 boxes  and 1  box = 10 pieces (base unit), the system converts 3  boxes into 30 pieces.         \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rConv      \n\r\n\rConversion quantity based on the  Purchase Order module.        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Filter by Item Classification: The system only displays purchaseorders that include at least one-line item with the chosen item classification,and the bottom grid shows only the line items that match the filtered itemclassification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Purchase Order transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Purchase Orders for Extractionto PI:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Purchase Order,click the X next to the Doc.ID in thetop grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Purchase Order, first select thepurchase order in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either clickthe X next to each item or enter the delivered quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Whena Purchase Invoice is posted, the transaction will be reflectedin the supplier ledger as an increase in what the organization owes thesupplier, and inventory is increased accordingly.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the section I. Creating a PurchaseInvoice / Adjustment. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Extraction from Purchase Order","topics\\Purchase_Invoice_and_Adjustment_extraction_POPI.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  8  28  2026-01-15T09:12:00Z  2026-02-24T09:57:00Z  8  1008  5751  47  13  6746  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Receiving Report moduleto Purchase Invoice module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Receiving Report module to thePurchase Invoice module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item detailsand quantities, making the delivery process faster, more accurate, and lessprone to errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingReceiving Report to Purchase Invoice: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheDocument Type should be PurchaseInvoice.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know thesupplier’s code, enter it directly in the Supplier Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usingoptical mouse, right-click anywhere withinthe module and choose Extract fromReceiving Report then Extraction ofReceiving Report window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extraction ofReceiving Report window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofreceiving reports, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all theitem details for that receiving report.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire receiving report for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the receiving report.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique receiving report  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the receiving  report was created / received.        \n\r\n\rSupplier      \n\r\n\rCode of the supplier.        \n\r\n\rReceived from       \n\r\n\rRefers to the supplier  who delivered the received items.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be received.        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity entered in purchase order.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe Pending Qty  column shows the remaining quantity of the item available for invoicing. When  creating a Purchase  Invoice, these quantities are automatically converted to the base  unit of measure to ensure consistent and to allow flexibility  if the unit of measure changes on the invoice (e.g., receiving 3 boxes but  invoicing 30 pieces).  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rExample:\n\r  If the pending quantity is 3 boxes  and 1  box = 10 pieces (base unit), the system converts 3  boxes into 30 pieces.         \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rConv      \n\r\n\rConversion quantity based on the  Receiving report module.        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Filter by Item Classification: The system only displays receivingreports that include at least one-line item with the chosen itemclassification, and the bottom grid shows only the line items that match thefiltered item classification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific receiving transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Receiving Report for Extractionto PI:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Receiving Report,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Receiving Report, first select thereceiving report in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either clickthe X next to each item or enter the invoice quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Whena PurchaseInvoice is posted, the transaction increases the balance in theSupplierledger. Inventory quantities are not updatedin this scenario because the process follows Receiving Report (RR)to Purchase Invoice (PI), and inventory was already updatedwhen the Receiving Report was posted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I. Creating a PurchaseInvoice / Adjustment. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","V. Extraction from Receiving Report","topics\\Purchase_Invoice_and_Adjustment_extraction_RRPI.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  4  2026-01-15T07:00:00Z  2026-01-15T08:08:00Z  1  480  2741  22  6  3215  16.00        Print  160  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Purchase Invoice or PurchaseAdjustment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Purchase Invoice window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID:You can set Document ID to All, which means all transactions willbe included without restriction based on their unique identifiers. However, ifyou want to focus on specific transactions, you can select a particularDocument ID, allowing the system to retrieve and display only the purchaseinvoice or purchase adjustment associated with that identifier, while stillapplying any other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields let you specify thenumeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example:From 1 To 50 — means only those purchaseinvoices or purchase adjustment whose document number is between 1 and50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange:Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is not checked. This meansthe date range filter will be ignored. All transactions matching the DocumentID and Document Range will be included, regardless of their date. If you wantto filter by date, you must check the &quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier: If you want to filter by a specificsupplier, click the magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list window andselect the desired supplier. If you leave it empty, all suppliers will beincluded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view a previewof the transactions that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correcttransactions and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall transactions that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Purchase Invoice window.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing a Purchase Invoice / Adjustment","topics\\Purchase_Invoice_and_Adjustment_printing.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  6  2  2026-01-15T06:57:00Z  2026-02-06T10:30:00Z  2  121  695  5  1  815  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the PurchaseInvoice or Purchase Adjustment \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the PurchaseInvoice or Purchase Adjustment .\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II.Searching for a Transaction in the Purchase Invoice / Adjustment","topics\\Purchase_Invoice_and_Adjustment_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  3  11  2026-01-12T11:10:00Z  2026-01-12T11:22:00Z  1  112  639  5  1  750  16.00        Print  180  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rPURCHASE INVOICE    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe PurchaseInvoice serves as the official request for paymentand provides detailed information on what was supplied, at what cost, and underwhich terms. It acts as a financial and legal document, supporting both thesupplier’s claim for payment and the organization’s accounting and auditingrecords.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHowa Purchase Invoice is created depends on the system setup. In some setups, theprocess goes from Purchase Order → Receiving Report → Purchase Invoice,making sure that everything ordered is received before payment. In other setup,the Purchase Invoice can be generated directly from the Receiving Reportor even straight from the Purchase Order, which can make the processfaster and simpler.","Purchase Invoice / Purchase Adjustment","topics\\Purchase_Invoice_and_Purchase_Adjustment.htm","\n\r\n\r                 Purchase :\n\r  Purchase   Request     Purchase Order     Receiving   Report / Return       Purchase Invoice / Purchase   Adjustment        AP Summary   Entry      Accounts   Payable Application    \n\r","Purchase","topics\\Purchase_menu.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  3  1  2026-01-12T11:05:00Z  2026-01-12T11:22:00Z  1  107  611  5  1  717  16.00        Print  180  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rPURCHASE ORDER   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAPurchase Order (PO) is an official document issued by an organization toa supplier or vendor to formally order goods, materials, or services. Unlike aPurchase Request, which is an internal document requesting approval for apurchase, the Purchase Order is a legal document that confirms the purchaseand serves as a binding agreement between the buyer and the supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThePO specifies exactly what is being purchased, the quantity, price, delivery instructions,and other terms and conditions. It serves as a key communication tool betweenthe purchasing organization and suppliers, ensuring clarity, accountability,and control throughout the procurement process.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Purchase Order","topics\\Purchase_Order.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  28  118  2026-01-07T08:16:00Z  2026-02-24T09:54:00Z  19  3139  17895  149  41  20993  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Purchase Order \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Order from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know the supplier’scode, enter it directly in the Supplier code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea supplier is selected, the Payable Tofield is automatically updated based on the Supplier Master Files. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Payable To field can be manually edited when necessary. Users may type directly intothis field to specify a different payee name,such as:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Adifferent registered business name\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Abranch name or alternate payee\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Aspecific individual authorized to receive payment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThisflexibility allows users to handle special payment arrangements while stillusing the same supplier record.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheBillTo field is automatically appearwith the registeredcompany name configured in the system. This default informationrepresents the company that will be billed by the supplierfor the Purchase Order.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlthoughthe system provides a default value, the Bill To field can be changed by the userwhen required. This allows flexibility in cases where billing needs to bedirected to a different company entity, branch, or billing addresswithin the organization.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enter the delivery addressor click the magnifying glass to select the warehouse address in the DeliverTo field where the ordered items will be sent by the supplier.This information guides the supplier on the exact location forshipment or delivery of the goods listed in the Purchase Order.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTheaddress entered in this field serves as the official deliverydestination and will appear on the Purchase Order provided tothe supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If theDocument ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number as needed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterorder date on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTerms field is automatically setbased on the supplier’s default terms. You can change it and select differentterms if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. The TransactionType field is automatically filled based on the supplier’s defaulttransaction type. However, you may leave it blank or choose a differenttransaction type when using this module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Itemizeddata Grid, allows youto customize the layout by rearranging the columns according to yourpreference. To do this, click on the column header using your optical mouse, hold the click, and drag the header tothe position you want. Once the column is in the desired location, release theoptical mouse button to set the new position. This feature helps you organizethe grid in a way that makes it easier to view and work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Adding and Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r12.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, PriceReference, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the fields provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterrequired quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unitof Measure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdownlist to select a different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default FOB price from the Items module isautomatically displayed in the Gross Price column. Youmay modify this value or manually enter a purchase price if required. Discounts 1–5 and any adjustments (Adj)can also be applied as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehousewhere the ordered item will be added. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rThis field  displays the final price per unit, which is already net  of discounts and adjustments. This field automatically  computed.         \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal  per item and this field automatically computed.  \n\r\n\rFormula: Qty  x Unit Price         \n\r\n\rVat Incl.      \n\r\n\rWhen  checked, it indicates that the item’s Unit Price already  includes VAT. Otherwise, the price is VAT-exclusive.        \n\r\n\rVAT Rate      \n\r\n\rWhen the Vat Incl. is checked the VAT rate automatically  applied, but users can modify it if the item is tax-exempt or subject to a  different rate.        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rServed Qty      \n\r\n\rShows how many units of the ordered item have already been  delivered or fulfilled. This field updates automatically when a Receiving Report (RR) or Purchase Invoice (PI) is processed  against the order.  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rThe quantity is automatically converted to the base unit.  For example, if the conversion rate is 10 and the quantity is 3, the served  quantity will be 30 upon extraction to RR or PI.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rPR      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Purchase Request (PR) number where the extracted details originated. This  helps the user easily identify which Purchase Request was used as the source  of the items shown in the transaction.        \n\r\n\rD button      \n\r\n\rClick the D button to see which module the item has been extracted to        \n\r\n\rPackage      \n\r\n\rTo add components to a package item, click the *Add* button  next to the main item and choose the components you want to include   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the PurchaseOrder, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 12.1to 12.7. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line item, select itby clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,comments, or specific instructions related to the Purchase Order,if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Purchase Order is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. The highlighted section displays thetransaction values based on the selected currency and their equivalent amountsin Philippine Peso (PHP). This allows the user to view both the originalcurrency values and their converted peso amounts side by side, ensuringaccuracy in pricing, reporting, and accounting. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;The Currency/Rate fields are automaticallyfilled using the supplier’s default currency. You may change these fields ifthe transaction requires a different currency.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allpurchase orders will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the purchase order associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosepurchase order whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All purchase ordersmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier:If you want to filter by a specific supplier, click the magnifying glass iconto open the supplier list window and select the desired supplier. If you leaveit empty, all suppliers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rTotal Field: Displays the total amount of alltransactions that are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r20. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on prompt message , the Canceldocument window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window will open,this window provides additional details related to the transaction, such asgrouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields for additionalinformation not covered by the standard fields. You can input specific databased on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person who performedthe cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract PO Entry Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract&nbsp;PO Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract&nbsp;PO Entry button is used tocopy or duplicate the current transaction under Purchase Order module. When youclick this button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as supplier details, items, quantities, prices, andetc. and creates a new transaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Purchase Order","topics\\Purchase_Order_creating.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  13  87  2026-01-08T07:35:00Z  2026-02-24T09:55:00Z  8  956  5452  45  12  6396  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Purchase Request moduleto Purchase Order module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Purchase Request module to thePurchase Order module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item detailsand quantities, more accurate, and less prone to errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingPurchase Request to Purchase Order: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectPurchase Order from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifying glass icon to openthe supplier list, or if you know the supplier’s code, enter it directly in theSuppliercode field. If the code does not exist, the supplier list willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract from Purchase Request then Extractions of Purchase Request window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractions ofPurchase Request window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofpurchase requests, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all theitem details for that purchase request.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the entire purchase  request for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the purchase request.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique purchase request  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the purchase  request was created.        \n\r\n\rDepartment      \n\r\n\rDepartment of Employee        \n\r\n\rEmployee Name      \n\r\n\rComplete employee name   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity to be ordered from the  supplier        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity originally ordered by the  employee.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe  Pending  Qty column shows the remaining quantity ordered by the  employee. These quantities are automatically converted to the base unit of  measure to ensure accurate and consistent inventory tracking, and to allow  flexibility if the unit of measure changes when ordering from the supplier (for example, an employee may request 3  boxes, but the purchaser can place the order as 30 pieces).  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rExample:  If the pending quantity is 3 boxes  and 1  box = 10 pieces (base unit), the system converts 3  boxes into 30 pieces.         \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To filter the data, select thecheckboxes next to the following filters and click the Requerybutton:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Item Classification: The system only displays Purchaserequest that include at least one-line item with the chosen itemclassification, and the bottom grid shows only the line items that match thefiltered item classification.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Department:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific department, or If youleave it empty, all departments will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee:If you want to filter by a specific employee, click the magnifying glass iconto open the employee list window and select the desired employee. If you leaveit empty, all employees will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Purchase Request transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Purchase Request for Extractionto Purchase Order:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Purchase Request,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Purchaser Request, first select thepurchase request in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either clickthe X next to each item or enter the order quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proceed to update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Post buttonin the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I.Creating a Purchase Order\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Extraction from Purchase Request","topics\\Purchase_Order_extraction_PRPO.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  7  18  2026-01-08T09:20:00Z  2026-02-24T09:55:00Z  4  465  2651  22  6  3110  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extraction from Sales Order to PurchaseOrder\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Order from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know thesupplier’s code, enter it directly in the Supplier code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usingoptical mouse, right-click anywhere withinthe module and choose Extract from SalesOrder then Search Document Number windowwill appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.1. Enter the document number in spaceprovided. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Youcan extract the same sales order number as many times as needed. The extractionis used only to pull the item details linked to the sales order. This helpsensure that the correct items are selected and prevents accidental selection ofincorrect items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields such quantity, remarks and etc..\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Post buttonin the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the&nbsp;I.Creating a Purchase Order.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","V. Extraction from Sales Order","topics\\Purchase_Order_extraction_SOPO.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  7  7  2026-01-08T04:07:00Z  2026-01-15T07:45:00Z  3  457  2610  21  6  3061  16.00        Print  160  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Purchase Order \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Purchase Order window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allpurchase orders will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the purchase order associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosepurchase order whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All purchase ordersmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier:If you want to filter by a specific supplier, click the magnifying glass iconto open the supplier list window and select the desired supplier. If you leaveit empty, all suppliers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the purchase orders that match the currently set filter criteriabefore printing them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected thecorrect purchase orders and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall order slips that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Purchase Orderwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r","III. Printing a Purchase Order","topics\\Purchase_Order_print.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  0  2026-01-08T04:06:00Z  2026-02-06T10:31:00Z  2  105  604  5  1  708  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the PurchaseOrder\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Order from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the PurchaseOrder.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Purchase Order","topics\\Purchase_Order_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  2  1  2026-01-12T11:04:00Z  2026-01-12T11:05:00Z  1  74  428  3  1  501  16.00        Print  180  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rPURCHASE REQUEST   \n\r\n\rAPurchaseRequest (PR) is an official internal document used within anorganization to request the acquisition of goods, materials, or services. Itserves as the first step in the procurement process and ensures that allpurchases are properly documented, justified, and approved before any spendingoccurs. The PR provides a standardized method for requesting items, helpsmaintain budgetary control, and ensures transparency in the purchasingworkflow.","Purchase Request","topics\\Purchase_Request.htm","   user  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  16  48  2025-12-23T09:37:00Z  2026-02-24T09:53:00Z  17  2623  14955  124  35  17543  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Purchase Request \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Request from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the employee list, or if you know the employee’scode, enter it directly in the Employee Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the employee list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Employee from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theEmployee Code in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the EmployeeName inthe space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Employee Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once an employee is selected, the Department field is automaticallyfilled with the employee’s default department from the Employee module. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, if applicable.This field is used to categorize the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Itemized data Grid, allows you to customize the layout byrearranging the columns according to your preference. To do this, click on thecolumn header using your optical mouse, hold theclick, and drag the header to the position you want. Once the column is in thedesired location, release the optical mouse button to set the new position.This feature helps you organize the grid in a way that makes it easier to viewand work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addingand Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r9.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;PriceReference filter is not applicable on this module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the fields provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unitof Measure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdownlist to select a different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehousewhere the item will be added.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field automatically  shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rServed Qty      \n\r\n\rShows how many units of the item have already been issued  or fulfilled. This field updates automatically when a Purchase Order (PO) is processed against the Purchase Request.  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rThe quantity is automatically converted to the base unit.  For example, if the conversion rate is 10 and the quantity is 3, the served  quantity will be 30 upon extraction to IS..        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rD button      \n\r\n\rClick the D button to see which module the item has been extracted to        \n\r\n\rPackage      \n\r\n\rTo add components to a package item, click the *Add* button  next to the main item and choose the components you want to include   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the PurchaseRequest, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 9.1to 9.6. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line item, select itby clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,or specific instructions related to the purchase request,if needed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Purchase Request is saved. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allpurchase requests will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the purchase request associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, Employee or Department.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosepurchase requests whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All purchaserequests matching the Document ID and Document Range will be included,regardless of their date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the&quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Employee:If you want to filter by a specific employee, click the magnifying glass iconto open the employee list window and select the desired employee. If you leaveit empty, all employees will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Department:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific department, or Ifyou leave it empty, all departments will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage, the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract PR Entry Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract PR Entry Button, ifneeded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract PR Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Purchase Request module. When youclick this button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as employee details, items, quantities and etc. andcreates a new transaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Purchase Request","topics\\Purchase_Request_creating.htm","   user  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  6  64  2025-12-23T12:48:00Z  2026-02-24T09:54:00Z  5  646  3683  30  8  4321  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extraction from Requisition Slip\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Request from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the employee list, or if you know the employee’scode, enter it directly in the Employee Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the employee list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Employee from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theEmployee Code in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the EmployeeName inthe space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Employee Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once an employee is selected, the Department field is automaticallyfilled with the employee’s default department from the Employee module. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, if applicable.This field is used to categorize the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usingoptical mouse, right-click anywhere withinthe module and choose Extract fromRequisition Slip then SearchDocument Number window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.1. Enter the document number in spaceprovided. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Youcan extract the same requisition number as many times as needed. The extractionis used only to pull the item details linked to the requisition. This helps ensurethat the correct items are selected and prevents accidental selection ofincorrect items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields such quantity, remarks and etc..\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the&nbsp;I.Creating a Purchase Request. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Extraction from Requisition Slip","topics\\Purchase_Request_extraction_RSPR.htm","   user  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  8  5  2025-12-23T13:58:00Z  2026-02-24T09:54:00Z  4  473  2702  22  6  3169  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extraction from Sales Order\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Request from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the employee list, or if you know the employee’scode, enter it directly in the Employee Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the employee list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Employee from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theEmployee Code in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the EmployeeName inthe space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Employee Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usingoptical mouse, right-click anywhere withinthe module and choose Extract fromRequisition Slip then SearchDocument Number window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.1. Enter the document number in spaceprovided. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Youcan extract the same sales order number as many times as needed. The extractionis used only to pull the item details linked to the sales order. This helpsensure that the correct items are selected and prevents accidental selection ofincorrect items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields such quantity, remarks and etc..\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Post buttonin the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the&nbsp;I.Creating a Purchase Request.","V. Extraction from Sales Order","topics\\Purchase_Request_extraction_SOPR.htm","   user  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  8  2025-12-23T11:05:00Z  2026-01-08T10:39:00Z  3  487  2777  23  6  3258  16.00        Print  180  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Printing a PurchaseRequest\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Purchase Request window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allpurchase requests will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the purchase request associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, Employee or Department.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosepurchase requests whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the \"With date range\" checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All purchaserequests matching the Document ID and Document Range will be included,regardless of their date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the\"With date range\" box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Employee:If you want to filter by a specific employee, click the magnifying glass iconto open the employee list window and select the desired employee. If you leaveit empty, all employees will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Department:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific department, or Ifyou leave it empty, all departments will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view a previewof the purchase requests that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correctpurchase requests and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall purchase requests that match the currently set filter criteria to theprinter.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Purchase Requestwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing a Purchase Request","topics\\Purchase_Request_print.htm","   user  CCC_MARIENEL  7  3  2025-12-23T11:04:00Z  2026-02-06T10:31:00Z  2  107  613  5  1  719  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the PurchaseRequest\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Purchase Request from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the PurchaseRequest.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Purchase Request","topics\\Purchase_Request_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  2  0  2026-01-12T11:07:00Z  2026-01-12T11:08:00Z  1  94  540  4  1  633  16.00        Print  180  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rRECEIVING REPORT   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAReceivingReport (RR), is an internal document used to recordthe receipt of goods or services delivered by a supplier. Itserves as a verification tool to confirm that the items ordered through aPurchase Order (PO) have been delivered, inspected, and accepted in accordancewith the specifications outlined in the PO.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Receiving Report is an essentialpart of the procurement and inventory management process. It ensures that theorganization receiveswhat it paid for, in the correct quantity and quality, andserves as the basis for payment processing and inventory updates.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Receiving Report / Return","topics\\Receiving_Report_or_Return.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  27  130  2026-01-09T06:46:00Z  2026-02-24T09:55:00Z  18  3072  17512  145  41  20543  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Receiving Report and Return \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Receiving Report fromthe Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Type is Receiving Report, you can change it asneeded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Receiving Report (items received from supplier, inventoryincreases)\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Return Slip (items returned to supplier, inventorydecreases)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the supplier list, or if you know thesupplier’s code, enter it directly in the Supplier Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the supplier list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Aftera supplier is selected, the system automatically fills the ReceivedFrom field with the supplier’s full name as recorded in theSupplier module. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTheReceivedFrom field remains editable at all times as long the receivingreport module is not yet posted. Users may update or manually enter analternative name when required by operational circumstances, such as when itemsare delivered by a supplier’s branch location, an authorized representative, ora third-party logistics provider.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAnymodifications made to the Received From fieldaffect only the current transaction and do not modify the supplier’s masterdata in the Supplier module. This approach ensures accurate documentation ofreceiving details while preserving the integrity and reliability of supplierinformation for reporting and audit purposes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta preferred Document ID from thedropdown list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date isautomatically set to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:  The Document Datemay represent different events depending on the document type. For a ReceivingReport, the Document Date reflects the date the items were received from thesupplier. For a Return Slip, the Document Date represents the date the itemsare being returned to supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe ReferenceNo., such as the supplier’s Delivery Receipt or Sales Invoicenumber or any received document from supplier, to serve as a supportingdocument reference for the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTransaction Type field is automaticallyfilled based on the supplier’s default transaction type. However, you may leaveit blank or choose a different transaction type when using this module.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Itemizeddata Grid, allows youto customize the layout by rearranging the columns according to yourpreference. To do this, click on the column header using your optical mouse, hold the click, and drag the header tothe position you want. Once the column is in the desired location, release theoptical mouse button to set the new position. This feature helps you organizethe grid in a way that makes it easier to view and work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Adding and Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r11.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification,  Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;PriceReference filter is not applicable on this module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the field provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe quantitythat should be received.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen the DocumentType is set to Receiving Report,the quantity entered must be a positivevalue, indicating that items are being received and added to the warehouseinventory.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOn the other hand, if the Document Type is set to ReturnSlip, the quantity entered must be a negativevalue. This represents items being returned to the supplier and ensures thatthe corresponding quantity is deducted from the inventory balance.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unit ofMeasure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdown list to selecta different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehouse where the items willbe received and recorded. It is important to choose the correct warehouse, asthis determines the specific stock location that will be updated when theReceiving Report is posted.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto&nbsp;see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rServed Qty      \n\r\n\rShows how many delivered items have already extracted to  Purchase Invoice. This field updates automatically when a Receiving Report  (RR) extracted to Purchase Invoice (PI).  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rThe quantity is automatically converted to the base unit.  For example, if the conversion rate is 10 and the quantity is 3, the served  quantity will be 30 upon extraction to PI.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rPO No.      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Purchase Order (PO) number where the extracted details originated. This helps  the user easily identify which Purchase Order was used as the source of the items  shown in the transaction.        \n\r\n\rRR No      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Receiving Report (RR) number where the extracted details came from. This is  used when performing “Extracts  Receiving Report for Returns”, allowing the user to quickly trace the  specific RR that served as the source of the return details.        \n\r\n\rSN      \n\r\n\rOptional,  enter the serial number of items received.        \n\r\n\rD button      \n\r\n\rClick the D button to see which module the item has been extracted to        \n\r\n\rPackage      \n\r\n\rTo add components to a package item, click the *Add* button  next to the main item and choose the components you want to include   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the ReceivingReport module, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeatsteps 14.1 to 14.8. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse, selectany column on the grid except the ItemCode column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line item, select itby clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12.&nbsp; Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,comments, or specific instructions related to the Receiving Report,if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Receiving report module is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to update theinformation as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes to applythem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You canset DocumentID to All, which means allreceiving reports and/or return slips will be included, without restrictionbased on their unique identifiers. However, if you want to focus on specifictransactions, you can select a particular Document ID. This willallow the system to retrieve and display only the receiving or returnassociated with that identifier, while still applying any other filters you mayhave set, such as Document Range, Date Range,or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post. (Example: From 1To 50 — only receiving reports and/or return slips withdocument numbers between 1 and 50 will be included.)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Noticethat the “Withdate range” checkbox is not checked. This means the date rangefilter will be ignored. All receiving reports and/or return slips that matchthe DocumentID and Document Range will beincluded, regardless of their date. If you want to filter by date, you mustcheck the “Withdate range” box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier:If you want to filter by a specific supplier, click the magnifying glass iconto open the supplier list window and select the desired supplier. If you leaveit empty, all suppliers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Whena Receiving Report or Return Slip is posted, the system automatically updatesthe inventory, ensuring that stock levels remain accurate and up-to-date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Youcannot cancel a Receiving Report (RR) if it has been fully extracted to aPurchase Invoice or Return Slip.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;UponCancellation: Ifthe DocumentType is Receiving Report, theitem quantities are automatically deducted from the InventoryStock Card. However, if the Document Typeis Return Slip, the itemquantities are automatically added back to the InventoryStock Card.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifthe workflow is a Purchase Order extracted to the Receiving Report module,cancelling the Receiving Report (RR) will also restore thequantities back to the Purchase Order.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. Click Other Information button, if needed. And the Other Information window will open, this window providesadditional details related to the transaction, such as grouping, custom fields,posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This section allowsyou to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Fields (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.","I. How to use Receiving Report / Return","topics\\Receiving_Report_or_Return_creating.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  12  77  2026-01-12T04:11:00Z  2026-02-24T09:56:00Z  8  987  5628  46  13  6602  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Purchase Order moduleto Receiving Report module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Purchase Order module to theReceiving report module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering itemdetails and quantities, making the delivery process faster, more accurate, andless prone to errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingPurchase Order to Receiving Report: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectReceiving Report from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The DocumentType should be Receiving Report.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifying glass icon to open thesupplier list, or if you know the supplier’s code, enter it directly in the SupplierCode field. If the code does not exist, the supplier list willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract from Purchase Order then Extractions of Purchase Order window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractions ofPurchase Order window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofpurchase orders, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all the itemdetails for that purchase order.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire purchase order for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the purchase order.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique purchase order  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the purchase order  was created.        \n\r\n\rSupplier      \n\r\n\rCode of the supplier.        \n\r\n\rPayable To       \n\r\n\rRefers to the person  or company that will receive the payment for the Purchase  Order.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be received.        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity entered in purchase order.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe Pending Qty  column shows the remaining quantity of the item available for receiving. When  creating a Receiving report, these  quantities are automatically converted to the base unit of  measure to ensure consistent and accurate inventory tracking,  and  to allow flexibility in case the unit of measure changes upon delivery (e.g.,  an order for 3 boxes can be received as 30 pieces).  \n\r\n\rExample:\n\r  If the pending quantity is 3 boxes  and 1  box = 10 pieces (base unit), the system converts 3  boxes into 30 pieces.         \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.        \n\r\n\rConv      \n\r\n\rConversion quantity based on the Purchase  Order module.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Filter by Item Classification: The system only displays purchaseorders that include at least one-line item with the chosen item classification,and the bottom grid shows only the line items that match the filtered itemclassification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Purchase Order transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Purchase Orders for Extractionto RR:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Purchase Order,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Purchase Order, first select thepurchase order in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either clickthe X next to each item or enter the delivered quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Whena Receiving Report is posted, the system automatically updates the inventory byadding the received quantities, ensuring that stock levels remain accurate andup-to-date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I. Creating a Receiving Report / Return.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Extraction from Purchase Order","topics\\Receiving_Report_or_Return_extraction_PORR.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  12  55  2026-01-12T09:21:00Z  2026-02-24T09:56:00Z  7  967  5515  45  12  6470  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Receiving Report toReturn Slip \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis process makes it easy to returnitems listed on a Receiving Report back to the supplier. By using the originalreport as a reference, you can be sure the right items and quantities arereturned, while keeping inventory records accurate. It also helps preventmistakes, ensures proper documentation, and makes it clear for auditing orsupplier follow-up. Overall, it simplifies the return process and keepseverything organized.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingReceiving Report to Return Slip:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectReceiving Report from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The DocumentType should be Return Slip.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifying glass icon to open thesupplier list, or if you know the supplier’s code, enter it directly in the SupplierCode field. If the code does not exist, the supplier list willappear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Supplier from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract Receiving Report for Returns then Extractions of Receiving Report window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractions ofReceiving Report window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofreceiving report, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all theitem details for that receiving report.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire receiving report for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the receiving report.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique receiving report  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate when the items were  received.        \n\r\n\rSupplier      \n\r\n\rCode of the supplier  who delivered the items   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rReturn Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity of the item that should be  returned to the supplier.        \n\r\n\rDelivered Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity of the item received from the  supplier.        \n\r\n\rRemaining Returns       \n\r\n\rShows the remaining quantity  of the item available for return. When creating a Return Slip, these  quantities are automatically converted to the base unit of measure to ensure  accurate inventory tracking. This also allows flexibility if the unit of  measure changes on return.  \n\r\n\rExample: If 3 boxes are pending return and 1  box = 10 pieces, the system converts 3 boxes into 30 pieces.        \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDetailed description of the item.        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rPurchase price per unit of the item.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Receiving Report transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Receiving Report for Extraction toReturn Slip:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Receiving Report,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Receiving Report, first select thereceiving report in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either clickthe X next to each item or enter the return quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAs you cansee, when the extraction window is closed, the system automatically convertsthe quantity to a negative value. This indicates that the items are beingreturned to the supplier, ensuring that inventory records are adjustedcorrectly and reflect the reduction in stock.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Whenthe Return Slip is posted, the system automatically reduces the correspondingquantities in inventory, ensuring that stock levels are updated accurately.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I. Creating a Receiving Report / Return.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","V. Extraction Receiving Report to Return Slip","topics\\Receiving_Report_or_Return_extraction_RRRS.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  6  9  2026-01-09T10:07:00Z  2026-01-15T07:46:00Z  3  484  2760  23  6  3238  16.00        Print  160  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Receiving Report \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Receiving Report window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You canset DocumentID to All, which means allreceiving reports and/or return slips will be included, without restrictionbased on their unique identifiers. However, if you want to focus on specifictransactions, you can select a particular Document ID. This willallow the system to retrieve and display only the receiving or returnassociated with that identifier, while still applying any other filters you mayhave set, such as Document Range, Date Range,or Supplier.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post. (Example: From 1To 50 — only receiving reports and/or return slips withdocument numbers between 1 and 50 will be included.)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Noticethat the “Withdate range” checkbox is not checked. This means the date rangefilter will be ignored. All receiving reports and/or return slips that matchthe DocumentID and Document Range will beincluded, regardless of their date. If you want to filter by date, you mustcheck the “Withdate range” box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Supplier:If you want to filter by a specific supplier, click the magnifying glass icon toopen the supplier list window and select the desired supplier. If you leave itempty, all suppliers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the receiving reports and/or return slips that match the currentlyset filter criteria before printing them. This is useful for verifying that youhave selected the correct documents and that the printed output will be asexpected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall receiving reports and/or return slips that match the currently set filtercriteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Receiving reportwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing a Receiving Report / Return","topics\\Receiving_Report_or_Return_printing.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  5  2026-01-09T10:06:00Z  2026-02-06T10:31:00Z  2  116  666  5  1  781  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the ReceivingReport or Return Slip\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Receiving Report fromthe Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the Receivingreport or Return Slip.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II.Searching for a Transaction in the Receiving Report / Return","topics\\Receiving_Report_or_Return_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  3  1  2025-12-16T08:39:00Z  2025-12-16T08:49:00Z  1  63  364  3  1  426  16.00        Print  120  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rREQUISITION SLIP   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Requisition Slip is used to formallyrequest items or services within the company. It allows departments to submittheir needs in an organized and standardized way, such as requests for office supplies,company products, or other required materials. Each requisition slip includesimportant details like the item description, quantity, purpose, and therequesting department.","Requisition Slip","topics\\Requisition_Slip.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  35  194  2025-12-11T09:11:00Z  2026-02-24T10:01:00Z  18  2737  15603  130  36  18304  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Requisition Slip \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Requisition Slip from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the employee list, or if you know the employee’scode, enter it directly in the Employee Code field. Ifthe code does not exist, the employee list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Employee from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theEmployee Code in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the EmployeeName inthe space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Employee Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once an employee is selected, the Department field is automatically filledwith the employee’s default department from the Employee module. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, if applicable.This field is used to categorize the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Itemized data Grid, allows you to customize the layout byrearranging the columns according to your preference. To do this, click on thecolumn header using your optical mouse, hold theclick, and drag the header to the position you want. Once the column is in thedesired location, release the optical mouse button to set the new position.This feature helps you organize the grid in a way that makes it easier to viewand work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addingand Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r9.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification,Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;PriceReference filter is not applicable on this module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the fields provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unitof Measure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdownlist to select a different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehousewhere the item will be released.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field automatically  shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rServed Qty      \n\r\n\rShows how many units of the item have already been issued  or fulfilled. This field updates automatically when an Issuance Slip (IS) is processed against the  requisition.  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rThe quantity is automatically converted to the base unit.  For example, if the conversion rate is 10 and the quantity is 3, the served  quantity will be 30 upon extraction to IS..        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rD button      \n\r\n\rClick the D button to see which module the item has been extracted to   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the Requisition,press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 9.1 to 9.6. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line item, select itby clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,or specific instructions related to the requisition,if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Requisition Slip is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to update theinformation as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes to applythem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allrequisition slips will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the requisition slip associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, Employee or Department.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoserequisition slips whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All requisition slipsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Employee:If you want to filter by a specific employee, click the magnifying glass icon toopen the employee list window and select the desired employee. If you leave itempty, all employees will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Department:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific department, or Ifyou leave it empty, all departments will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage, the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in your systemsetup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract RS Entry Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract RS Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract RS Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Requisition Slip module. When youclick this button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as employee details, items, quantities and etc... andcreates a new transaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Requisition Slip","topics\\Requisition_slip_Creating_a_Requisition_Slip.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  7  155  2025-12-16T05:57:00Z  2025-12-18T06:32:00Z  3  487  2776  23  6  3257  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Requisition Slip / BatchPrinting\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Requisition Slip window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allrequisition slips will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the requisition slip associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, Employee or Department.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoserequisition slips whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All requisitionslips matching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardlessof their date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;Withdate range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Employee:If you want to filter by a specific employee, click the magnifying glass iconto open the employee list window and select the desired employee. If you leaveit empty, all employees will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Department:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific department, or Ifyou leave it empty, all departments will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the requisition slips that match the currently set filter criteriabefore printing them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected thecorrect requisition slips and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall requisition slips that match the currently set filter criteria to theprinter.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Requisition Slipwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing a Requisition Slip","topics\\Requisition_slip_print.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  7  20  2025-12-16T05:36:00Z  2026-02-06T10:29:00Z  2  107  613  5  1  719  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the RequisitionSlip \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Requisition Slip from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the requisitionslip.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Requisition Slip","topics\\Requisition_Slip_Searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  14  248  2025-11-19T07:27:00Z  2025-11-25T10:09:00Z  1  108  617  5  1  724  16.00        Print  120  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rSALES INVOICE   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTheSales Invoice (SI) module is used to record the final and officialbilling issued to a customer once goods or services have been delivered. Itserves as the company’s formal proof ofsale and is used to update accounting records, customer balances, andinventory (depending on your workflow).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rInaddition to standard Sales Invoices, this module can also be used to record pull-outtransactions from customers, depending on the selected Document Type.When the user selects a document type intended for Sales Adjustment, thesystem processes the transaction differently: items are treated as returns,deducted from the customer\'s ledger, and added back to warehouse inventory\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Sales Invoice / Sales Adjustment","topics\\Sales_Invoice.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  7  4  2025-11-20T08:56:00Z  2026-04-23T07:27:00Z  2  462  2639  21  6  3095  16.00        Print  170  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Sales Invoice / BatchPrinting\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBefore proceeding with printing, makesure to perform a search to retrieve the necessary Sales Invoice data. Only thedetails currently displayed on the module will be included in the printout, soit is important to ensure that the correct record is loaded before printing.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Sales Invoice window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which includes all receipts without restricting them by theirunique identifiers. If you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to print onlythe receipts associated with that identifier, while still applying any otherfilters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosereceipts whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All receiptsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the receipts that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correctreceipts and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall receipts that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Sales Invoicewindow.","III. Printing a Sales Invoice & Sales Adjustment","topics\\Sales_invoice_Batch_Printing.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  47  247  2025-11-20T08:50:00Z  2026-02-24T09:51:00Z  24  3980  22691  189  53  26618  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Sales Invoice\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Sales Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Type is SalesInvoice, you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Sales Invoice is used to bill a customer for goods orservices that have been delivered. It represents the official record of the sale,updates the customer’s balance, and, if applicable, adjusts inventory toreflect the items sold. This is the standard transaction used whenever thecompany completes a sale and needs to record it in the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Sales Adjustment, is used only when there is a return ofgoods from a previous sale. This type of transaction ensures that returneditems are properly documented and that all related records are updatedaccurately. When a Sales Adjustment is entered, the system automaticallyupdates the Customer ledger toreduce the customer’s balance for the returned goods and adjusts the Inventory ledger to return the items tostock.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the customer list, or if you know thecustomer’s code, enter it directly in the Customer field. If thecode does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea customer is selected, the Bill Tofield is automatically updated based on the customer information. The firstline shows the customer’s full name, and the second line displays the default billingaddress. You can change or type directly in this field ifyou need to specify a different name or billing address. This is useful whenthe transaction needs to be billed to a branch, department, or another contactperson.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheDeliverTo field shows where the items will be sent. It isautomatically filled with the customer’s default delivery address. If thedelivery location is different from default delivery address, you can selectanother address. Click the magnifying glass icon tosee available addresses. If the address is not listed, you can add it in the Customermodule.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Indicatethe Reference ID &amp; Number, ifneeded. The Reference Number is a free-text field.It’s used to store a number or code that refers to something outsidethe system’s own numbering scheme.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ByDefault, the Document Date is automaticallyset to the current date, however you can change it as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTerms field is automatically setbased on the customer’s default terms. You can change it and select differentterms if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Select Transaction Type, this field is automatically set based on thecustomer’s default transaction type under customer module. You can changeit&nbsp;as needed or leave it blank.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. The BaseArea field is automatically set based on the customer’s default base areaspecified in the delivery address. If the address is changed, the Base Areawill update according to the default base area of the new address. You may alsomanually select a different Base Area if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Indicate the P.O. Number, if any.The P.O. Number will come from your customer.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Itemizeddata Grid, allows youto customize the layout by rearranging the columns according to yourpreference. To do this, click on the column header using your optical mouse, hold the click, and drag the header tothe position you want. Once the column is in the desired location, release theoptical mouse button to set the new position. This feature helps you organizethe grid in a way that makes it easier to view and work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Adding and Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, PriceReference, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in item module,possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the field provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventory thatis currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe Quantity thatshould be delivered.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;SalesInvoice: When theDocument Type is set to Sales Invoice, the quantity entered must alwaysbe positive.This indicates that items are being released from your warehouse and deliveredto the customer. The transaction will also be reflected in the customer’sledger as an increase in what they owe.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;SalesAdjustment : When the Document Type is set to Sales Adjustment,the quantity should be negative. This is usedwhen items are being returned or taken back from the customer. The negativequantity ensures that the stock is added back to your inventory,and the customer’sledger is adjusted accordingly, reducing their balance.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unit ofMeasure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdown list to selecta different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Multiple Unit of Measure (UOMs)should be assigned in the Item module so that youcan select the appropriate UOM when using this module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe customer has a default price reference set in the system, thisfield will be automatically filled in—provided that the selected item isincluded under the same price reference. If the item is not includedin the default price reference, this field will remain blank. Or select the price reference, if needed. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheGross Price, Discount 1-5 and adjustment(adj) fields will automatically update according to the chosen pricereference. If no price reference is selected, the fields will use the defaultUOM (Unit of Measurement) pricing value from the Items module. You can stillmanually adjust the pricing value if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehouse where the items willbe released. Choosing the correct warehouse is important because it determineswhich stock location will be deducted once the Sales Invoice is posted. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto&nbsp;see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rThis field  displays the final price per unit, which is already net  of discounts and adjustments. This field automatically  computed.         \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal  per item and this field automatically computed.  \n\r\n\rFormula: Qty  x Unit Price         \n\r\n\rVat Incl.      \n\r\n\rWhen  checked, it indicates that the item’s Unit Price already  includes VAT. Otherwise, the price is VAT-exclusive.        \n\r\n\rVAT Rate      \n\r\n\rWhen the Vat Incl. is checked the VAT rate automatically  applied, but users can modify it if the item is tax-exempt or subject to a  different rate.        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rFree      \n\r\n\rIndicates  whether the item is given as a free item (zero-price)  as part of a promotion or bundle. When checked, the system will automatically  set the amount to zero but still record the quantity for tracking purposes.        \n\r\n\rOS No.      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Sales  Order (SO) number when data is extracted from the Sales  Order module to the Sales Invoice module.        \n\r\n\rDR No      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Delivery  Receipt (DR) number when data is extracted from the Delivery  Receipt module to the Sales Invoice module.        \n\r\n\rSI No      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Sales Invoice (SI) number when data is extracted from the Sales  Invoice data to Sales adjustment.        \n\r\n\rSN      \n\r\n\rOptional,  enter the serial number of items that should be released        \n\r\n\rPackage      \n\r\n\rTo add components to a package item, click the *Add*  button next to the main item and choose the components you want to include   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the SalesInvoice, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 14.1to 14.8. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.10. To delete a line item, select it by clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. The Currency/Ratefields are automatically filled using the customer’s default currency. You maychange these fields if the transaction requires a different currency.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. When you select a customer, the Default Agent assigned to that customerwill automatically appear in the Agent field. This information is based on thesetup defined in the customer module. If necessary, you can change or replacethe default agent by selecting another one from the dropdown list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Enter the appropriate date in the Delivery Date field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentDate: The officialdate on the Sales Invoice. This is what the system uses to update Customer andinventory ledger.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DeliveryDate: The actualdate the customer receives the items. This does not affect customer andinventory ledger but helps track deliveries for reporting.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. If the selected customer has a Default Price Reference, it willautomatically appear in the corresponding field. This setting determines whichprice scheme or reference will be used when entering items in the SalesInvoice. You can change the price reference at any time before adding items byselecting another available option from the dropdown list. This allowsflexibility when a customer qualifies for a different price list or when aspecific price scheme needs to be applied for special transactions.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. If the customer has a Default Discount Rate, the system willautomatically display up to five (5) discount levels in the discount fields.These discount values are retrieved from the customer module and serve as theinitial discount setup for the transaction. You may edit these discount ratesbased on the customer’s agreement or promotional offers, or set them to zero ifno discount applies. This ensures that pricing adjustments are properlyreflected in the Sales Invoice before finalizing the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen the userclicks the updatebutton (),each item’s discounts are updated based on the document discount percentages.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r20. Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,comments, or specific instructions related to the Sales Invoice,if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Sales Invoice is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22. The highlighted section displays thetransaction values based on the selected currency and their equivalent amountsin Philippine Peso (PHP). This allows the user to view both the originalcurrency values and their converted peso amounts side by side, ensuringaccuracy in pricing, reporting, and accounting. You may also apply discountamount or adjustments as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf any itemhas insufficient stock, a validation message will be displayed upon clickingSave. Select Yes to proceed with thetransaction or No to cancel. Thisfeature is designed to alert the user of low stock for each item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHowever, ifthe user does not have access to proceed with insufficient stock, the Yes/No button option will not appear,and only the alert will be shown.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allreceipts will be included without restriction based on their unique identifiers.However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you can select aparticular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and display only thereceipts associated with that identifier, while still applying any otherfilters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosereceipts whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All receiptsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless of theirdate. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotal Field: Displays the total amount of alltransactions that are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOKto proceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be includedin the posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r27. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button in theNavigation toolbar. A confirmation message may appear—click Yes to cancel the record or No to abort the cancellation. This helps prevent accidental cancellation ofimportant data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage and Cancel document windowwill appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r28. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields for additionalinformation not covered by the standard fields. You can input specific databased on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract SI Entry Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r29. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract SI Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract SI Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Sales Invoice module. When you clickthis button, the system automatically extracts all information from the existingtransaction—such as customer details and creates a new transaction entry withthe same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Sales Invoice & Sales Adjustment","topics\\Sales_Invoice_direct_si.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  16  10  2025-11-24T10:29:00Z  2026-02-24T09:51:00Z  7  852  4857  40  11  5698  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractionsfrom Delivery Receipt module to Sales Invoice module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Delivery Receipt module to the SalesInvoice module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item details andquantities, making the delivery process faster, more accurate, and less proneto errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingDelivery Receipt to Sales Invoice: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectSales Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The DocumentType should be Sales Invoice.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifying glass icon to openthe customer list, or if you know the customer’s code, enter it directly in theCustomerfield. If the code does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract from Delivery Receipt then Extractions of Delivery Receipt window will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractionsof&nbsp;Delivery Receipt&nbsp;window has two main sections: the top gridshows a list of delivery receipts, and when you select one, the bottom griddisplays all the item details for that delivery receipt.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire sales order for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the delivery receipt.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique delivery receipt  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the delivery  receipt was created.        \n\r\n\rCustomer      \n\r\n\rCode of the customer.        \n\r\n\rPO Number      \n\r\n\rCustomer’s purchase  order number.        \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal value of the  sales order.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be extracted to sales  invoice.        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity originally delivered by the  customer.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe  Pending Qty column shows the remaining quantity of the item that is  available for sales invoice. When creating a sales invoice, these quantities  are automatically converted to the base unit of measure.  \n\r\n\rExample:  \n\r   If       the pending quantity is 3 boxes and 1 box = 10 pieces (base unit), the       system will convert 3 boxes → 30 pieces for the delivery document. \n\r    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;        \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rUnit price based on delivery receipt   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific&nbsp;Delivery Receipt&nbsp;transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging&nbsp;Delivery&nbsp;Receipt&nbsp;forExtraction to SI:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Delivery Receipt,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid.&nbsp;All corresponding items in the bottom grid willautomatically be selected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Delivery Receipt, first select thedelivery receipt in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either clickthe X next to each item or enter the delivery quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ScrollUp to view all extracted items, and proceed to update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.  Click the Postbutton in theNavigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I.Creating a Direct Sales Invoice.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Extraction from DR to SI","topics\\Sales_Invoice_extraction_DRSI.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  17  19  2025-11-20T09:41:00Z  2026-02-24T09:51:00Z  7  882  5031  41  11  5902  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rVI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extraction SI for Returns (SalesAdjustment)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows you to pull itemsdirectly from a Sales Invoice into a Sales Adjustment transaction. Itsimplifies the process of handling returns or adjustments while ensuring thatboth inventory records and customer ledgers remain accurate and up-to-date.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingSales Invoice to Sales Adjustment : \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectSales Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select&nbsp;Sales Adjustment&nbsp;inDocument Type field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifying glass icon to openthe customer list, or if you know the customer’s code, enter it directly in theCustomerfield. If the code does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract SI&nbsp;for returns then Extractions of&nbsp;Sales Invoice windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractionsof&nbsp;Sales Invoice&nbsp;window has two main sections: the top grid showsa list of Sales Invoices, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays allthe item details for that Sales Invoice.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire Sales Invoice for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the Sales Invoice.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique Sales Invoice  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the Sales Invoice  was created.        \n\r\n\rCustomer      \n\r\n\rCode of the customer.        \n\r\n\rPO Number      \n\r\n\rCustomer’s purchase  order number.        \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal value of the  Sales Invoice.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rReturns Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be returned.        \n\r\n\rDelivered Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity delivered to customer.        \n\r\n\rRemaining Returns Qty       \n\r\n\rThe  Remaining Returns Qty column shows how many units of an item are still  eligible for return. When creating a&nbsp;sales adjustment&nbsp;transaction,  the system automatically converts these quantities into their base unit of  measure.  \n\r\n\rExample:  \n\r   If       the remaining quantity is 3 boxes, and 1 box = 10 pieces       (base unit),\n\r       the system will convert it to:\n\r       3 boxes → 30 pieces in the delivery document. \n\r    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;        \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rUnit price based on Sales Invoice   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Sales Invoice transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Sales Invoice to SalesAdjustment:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Sales Invoice, clickthe X next to the Doc.ID in the topgrid.&nbsp;All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Sales Invoice, first select theSales Invoice in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either click theX button next to each item or enter the return quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; If the Sales Invoice (SI) has been fullyextracted to the Sales Adjustment or is already fully paid, it will no longerappear in the Extractions window. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once the Extractions of Sales Invoice window is closed, the quantity willappear as negative. Click Scroll Up to view all extracted items, and proceed toupdate the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I.Creating a Direct Sales Invoice.","VI. Extraction SI for Returns ( Sales Adjustment)","topics\\Sales_Invoice_extraction_SISA.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  12  37  2025-11-24T10:52:00Z  2026-02-24T09:51:00Z  9  915  5220  43  12  6123  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractionsfrom Sales Order module to Sales Invoice module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Sales Order module to the SalesInvoice module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item details and quantities,making the delivery process faster, more accurate, and less prone to errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtractingSales order to Sales Invoices: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SelectSales Invoice from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the New button inthe Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The DocumentType should be Sales Invoice.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the magnifying glass icon to openthe customer list, or if you know the customer’s code, enter it directly in theCustomerfield. If the code does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract from Sales Order thenExtractions of Sales Order window will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractions ofSales Order window has two main sections: the top grid shows a list ofsales orders, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all the itemdetails for that sales order.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire sales order for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the sales order.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique sales order  number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the sales order  was created.        \n\r\n\rCustomer      \n\r\n\rCode of the customer.        \n\r\n\rPO Number      \n\r\n\rCustomer’s purchase  order number.        \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal value of the  sales order.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be extracted to sales  invoice.        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity originally delivered by the  customer.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe  Pending Qty column shows the remaining quantity of the item that is  available for sales invoice. When creating a sales invoice, these quantities  are automatically converted to the base unit of measure.  \n\r\n\rExample:  \n\r   If       the pending quantity is 3 boxes and 1 box = 10 pieces (base unit), the       system will convert 3 boxes → 30 pieces for the delivery document. \n\r    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;        \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rUnit price based on sales order        \n\r\n\rQty in Base      \n\r\n\rQuantity converted to the  smallest/base unit.        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rConversion quantity based on the Sales  Order module.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Filter by Item Classification: The system only displays sales ordersthat include at least one-line item with the chosen item classification, andthe bottom grid shows only the line items that match the filtered itemclassification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific Sales Order transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tagging Sales Orders for Extraction toSI:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Sales Order, clickthe X next to the Doc.ID in the topgrid.&nbsp;All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Sales Order, first select the salesorder in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either click the Xnext to each item or enter the delivery quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ScrollUp to view all extracted items, and proceed to update the required fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.  Click the Postbutton in theNavigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section I.Creating a Direct Sales Invoice.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","V. Extraction From SO to SI","topics\\Sales_Invoice_extraction_SOSI.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  10  6  2025-11-20T08:52:00Z  2026-02-06T10:31:00Z  2  410  2341  19  5  2746  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the SalesInvoice\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen you openthe Sales Invoice module, you’llnotice that the screen is blank bydefault and no transaction details are displayed. This is intentional anddesigned to keep the system running smoothly, especially in businesses with alarge volume of transactions. If the system tried to load all Sales Invoicesautomatically, it could become slow, unresponsive, or even freeze due to thelarge amount of data. By starting with a blank screen, the system avoids theseperformance issues. You can easily view the records you need by using thesearch or filter options, which only retrieve specific transactions rather thanloading everything at once. This approach ensures faster response times and asmoother overall experience when working with the Sales module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTo view or retrieve an existing SalesInvoice record:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Search Option window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters toretrieve the desired Sales Invoice transactions.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means allreceipts will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the receipts associated with that identifier, while still applying anyother filters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to search (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosereceipts whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All receiptsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the OK button. The system will then display all Sales Invoices thatmatch the filters you selected.\n\r\n\r","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Sales Invoice & Sales Adjustment","topics\\Sales_Invoice_searching.htm","\n\r\n\r               Sales :\n\r  Quotation&nbsp;  Sales Order  Delivery Receipt /   Pull out  Sales Invoice / Sales   Adjustment  AR Summary   Entry  Accounts Receivables   Application\n\r","Sales","topics\\Sales_menu.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  105  1295  2025-11-06T07:02:00Z  2025-11-21T06:58:00Z  1  131  750  6  1  880  16.00        Print  120  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rSALES ORDER   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Sales Order (SO) moduleis used to record and manage all customer orders before any items are deliveredor billed. It acts as the starting point of the sales process, where you enter thecustomer’s requested items, quantities, pricing, and other important details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rCreatinga Sales Order does not yet record a sale and does not reduce yourinventory, because no items have been delivered. It only serves as a guidefor the next steps in your sales process.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTheSales Order helps you:\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitor all customer orders that arestill pending\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Prepare the items needed forupcoming deliveries\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reserveor allocate stocks for specific customers\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Speed up the creation of DeliveryReceipts (DR) or Sales Invoices (SI)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOncethe order is confirmed and ready, you can easily convert the Sales Order into aDR or SI without re-encoding the details.","Sales Order","topics\\Sales_Order.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  45  77  2025-11-20T10:23:00Z  2026-02-24T09:48:00Z  25  3596  20500  170  48  24048  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Sales Order \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Sales Order from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe magnifying glass icon to open the customer list, or if you know the customer’scode, enter it directly in the Customer field. If thecode does not exist, the customer list will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWays of selecting Customer from the list\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of theCode in the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncea customer is selected, the Bill Tofield is automatically updated based on the customer information. The firstline shows the customer’s full name, and the second line displays the defaultbilling address. You can change or type directlyin this field if you need to specify a different name or billing address. Thisis useful when the order needs to be billed to a branch, department, or anothercontact person.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheDeliverTo field shows where the ordered items will be sent. It isautomatically filled with the customer’s default delivery address. If thedelivery location is different from default delivery address, you can selectanother address. Click the magnifying glass icon tosee available addresses. If the address is not listed, you can add it in the Customermodule.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;EnterOrder date on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTerms field is automatically setbased on the customer’s default terms. You can change it and select differentterms if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheTransaction Type field isautomatically filled based on the customer’s default transaction type. However,you may leave it blank or choose a different transaction type when using thismodule.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. The BaseArea field is automatically set based on the customer’s default base areaspecified in the delivery address. If the address is changed, the Base Areawill update according to the default base area of the new address. You may alsomanually select a different Base Area if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Indicate the P.O. Number, if any.The P.O. Number will come from your customer.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Itemizeddata Grid, allows youto customize the layout by rearranging the columns according to yourpreference. To do this, click on the column header using your optical mouse, hold the click, and drag the header tothe position you want. Once the column is in the desired location, release theoptical mouse button to set the new position. This feature helps you organizethe grid in a way that makes it easier to view and work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. Adding and Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r13.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, PriceReference, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the fields provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterquantity orderedby the customer.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unitof Measure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdownlist to select a different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe customer has a default price reference set in the system,this field will be automatically filled in—provided that the selected item isincluded under the same price reference. If the item is not includedin the default price reference, this field will remain blank. Or select the price reference, if needed. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TheGross Price, Discount 1-5 and adjustment(adj) fields will automatically update according to the chosen pricereference. If no price reference is selected, the fields will use the defaultUOM (Unit of Measurement) pricing value from the Items module. You can stillmanually adjust the pricing value if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Warehousewhere the ordered item will be released. This helps ensure inventory isaccurate and prevents errors during order fulfillment.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rUnit Price      \n\r\n\rThis field  displays the final price per unit, which is already net  of discounts and adjustments. This field automatically  computed.         \n\r\n\rAmount      \n\r\n\rTotal  per item and this field automatically computed.  \n\r\n\rFormula: Qty  x Unit Price         \n\r\n\rVat Incl.      \n\r\n\rWhen  checked, it indicates that the item’s Unit Price already  includes VAT. Otherwise, the price is VAT-exclusive.        \n\r\n\rVAT Rate      \n\r\n\rWhen the Vat Incl. is checked the VAT rate automatically  applied, but users can modify it if the item is tax-exempt or subject to a  different rate.        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rServed Qty      \n\r\n\rShows how many units of the ordered item have already been  delivered or fulfilled. This field updates automatically when a Delivery Receipt (DR) or Sales Invoice (SI) is processed  against the order.  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rThe quantity is automatically converted to the base unit.  For example, if the conversion rate is 10 and the quantity is 3, the served  quantity will be 30 upon extraction to DR or SI.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rFree      \n\r\n\rIndicates  whether the item is given as a free item (zero-price)  as part of a promotion or bundle. When checked, the system will automatically  set the amount to zero but still record the quantity for tracking purposes.        \n\r\n\rSN      \n\r\n\rOptional,  enter the serial number of items that should be released        \n\r\n\rD button      \n\r\n\rClick the D button to see which module the item has been extracted to        \n\r\n\rPackage      \n\r\n\rTo add components to a package item, click the *Add*  button next to the main item and choose the components you want to include   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the Sales Order,press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 13.1 to 13.8.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13.10. To delete a line item, select it by clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. When you select a customer, the Default Agent assigned to that customerwill automatically appear in the Agent field. This information is based on thesetup defined in the customer module. If necessary, you can change or replacethe default agent by selecting another one from the dropdown list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. If the selected customer has a Default Price Reference , it will automatically appear inthe corresponding field. This setting determines which price scheme orreference will be used when entering items in the Sales Order. Before addingitems, you can change the price reference by selecting another available fromthe dropdown list. This allows flexibility when a customer qualifies for adifferent price list or when a specific price scheme needs to be applied forspecial transactions.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. If the customer has a Default Discount Rate, the system willautomatically display up to five (5) discount levels in the discount fields.These discount values are retrieved from the customer module and serve as theinitial discount setup for the transaction. You may edit these discount ratesbased on the customer’s agreement or promotional offers, or set them to zero ifno discount applies. This ensures that pricing adjustments are properlyreflected in the Sales Order before finalizing the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rWhen the userclicks the updatebutton (),each item’s discounts are updated based on the document discount percentages.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17.&nbsp; Use the Remarks field to enter additional notes,comments, or specific instructions related to the Sales Order,if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r18. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Sales Order is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r19. Enter the appropriate date in the Delivery Date field to specify when theordered items are expected to be delivered. Make sure the delivery date alignswith the customer’s request or the company’s standard delivery timeline.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r20. The highlighted section displays thetransaction values based on the selected currency and their equivalent amountsin Philippine Peso (PHP). This allows the user to view both the originalcurrency values and their converted peso amounts side by side, ensuringaccuracy in pricing, reporting, and accounting. You may also apply discountamount or adjustments as needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;The Currency/Rate fields are automaticallyfilled using the customer’s default currency. You may change these fields ifthe transaction requires a different currency.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r21. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf the item(s)have insufficient stock, a validation message will be displayed upon clicking Save. Select Yes to proceed with the transaction, or No to cancel. This feature is designed to alert the user of lowstock, but it does not affect inventory reports.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r22. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r23. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means all orderslips will be included without restriction based on their unique identifiers.However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you can select aparticular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and display only theorder slip associated with that identifier, while still applying any otherfilters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoseorder slips whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All order slipsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotal Field: Displays the total amount of alltransactions that are currently checked.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r24.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r25. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage , the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r26. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract SO Entry Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r27. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract SO Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract SO Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Sales Order module. When you clickthis button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as customer details and creates a new transactionentry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.","I. How to use Sales Order","topics\\Sales_Order_create.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  7  7  2025-11-20T10:26:00Z  2026-02-06T10:32:00Z  2  409  2337  19  5  2741  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the SalesOrder \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rWhen you openthe Sales Order module, you’llnotice that the screen is blank bydefault and no transaction details are displayed. This is intentional anddesigned to keep the system running smoothly, especially in businesses with alarge volume of transactions. If the system tried to load all sales ordersautomatically, it could become slow, unresponsive, or even freeze due to thelarge amount of data. By starting with a blank screen, the system avoids theseperformance issues. You can easily view the records you need by using thesearch or filter options, which only retrieve specific transactions rather thanloading everything at once. This approach ensures faster response times and asmoother overall experience when working with the Sales module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTo view or retrieve an existing SalesOrder record:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Search Option window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters toretrieve the desired Sales Order transactions.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means all orderslips will be included without restriction based on their unique identifiers.However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you can select aparticular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and display only theorder slip associated with that identifier, while still applying any otherfilters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to search (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoseorder slips whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All order slipsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the OK button. The system will then display all sales orders that matchthe filters you selected.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Sales Order","topics\\Sales_Order_find.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  6  7  2025-11-20T10:26:00Z  2025-11-25T02:58:00Z  2  463  2645  22  6  3102  16.00        Print  120  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Sales Order / Batch Printing\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rBefore proceeding with printing, makesure to perform a search to retrieve the necessary Sales Order data. Only thedetails currently displayed on the module will be included in the printout, so itis important to ensure that the correct record is loaded before printing.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the Order Slip window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templatesavailable, you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select theform you want to use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure thatyour printed report displays the proper layout, includes all the necessaryfields, and follows the intended formatting, so that the output matches yourrequirements accurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which includes all order slips without restricting them bytheir unique identifiers. If you want to focus on specific transactions, youcan select a particular Document ID, allowing the system to print onlythe order slip associated with that identifier, while still applying any otherfilters you may have set, such as DocumentRange, Date Range, or Customer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thoseorder slips whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All order slipsmatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Customer:If you want to filter by a specific customer, click the magnifying glass iconto open the customer list window and select the desired customer. If you leaveit empty, all customers will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the order slips that match the currently set filter criteria beforeprinting them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected the correctorder slips and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall order slips that match the currently set filter criteria to the printer.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Order Slipwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing a Sales Order /Batch Printing","topics\\sales_order_print.htm","        Business Box - SQL version         GL   Setup\n\r\n\r1 . Sales\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r2 . Purchase\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r3 . Inventory\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r4 . Other Information\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r5 . Others\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSales Invoice Workflows:\n\r\n\rThe SI module accommodates several workflows to match different business needs:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Direct Sales Invoice (No DR Required):\n\rThis workflow is used for immediate sales or cash transactions where items are billed directly to the customer without creating a Delivery Receipt. It simplifies the sales process for businesses that do not require separate delivery documentation while ensuring that the invoice captures all necessary sales and accounting information.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Standard Workflow (Sales Order → Delivery Receipt → Sales Invoice):\n\rIn this workflow, the invoice is generated after items have been delivered via a Delivery Receipt linked to a Sales Order. It provides a clear connection between the customer’s original order, the items delivered, and the final billing, ensuring accuracy in order fulfillment, inventory tracking, and customer billing. This workflow is particularly useful for businesses that need to closely monitor the full sales process from order to delivery to invoice.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Delivery Receipt → Sales Invoice:\n\rThis workflow allows the invoice to be generated directly from an existing Delivery Receipt. It is ideal when items are delivered without a prior Sales Order, such as ad-hoc or walk-in sales. This ensures that the customer is billed accurately based on what was actually delivered, while still maintaining proper accounting and inventory records.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sales Order → Sales Invoice:\n\rIn cases where items or services are sold based on a Sales Order but do not require a Delivery Receipt, the invoice can be generated directly from the Sales Order. This workflow is commonly used for services, digital products, or transactions where physical delivery tracking is not required. It ensures that the customer is billed accurately according to the order, while maintaining proper accounting documentation.","Setup - Trading","topics\\Setup_-_Trading.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  3  2  2025-12-17T09:47:00Z  2025-12-17T09:49:00Z  1  42  244  2  1  285  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rSTOCK REQUISITION   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Stock Requisition moduleallows warehouse branches to easily request the stock they need from the mainwarehouse or other branches. Branches can submit their orders, and the systemtracks each request from submission to fulfillment.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","Stock Requistion","topics\\Stock_Requisition.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  39  123  2025-12-16T09:02:00Z  2026-02-24T10:02:00Z  16  2438  13902  115  32  16308  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Stock Requisition \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Stock Requisition from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Source Warehouse from which theitem will be released, and select the DestinationWarehouse to which the item should be delivered or transferred. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number, thenumber field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, if applicable.This field is used to categorize the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Itemized data Grid, allows you to customize the layout byrearranging the columns according to your preference. To do this, click on thecolumn header using your optical mouse, hold theclick, and drag the header to the position you want. Once the column is in thedesired location, release the optical mouse button to set the new position.This feature helps you organize the grid in a way that makes it easier to viewand work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addingand Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r8.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;PriceReference filter is not applicable on this module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the fields provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf you enter a positive quantity,this indicates that items are being released from the Source Warehouseand deliveredto the Destination Warehouse.\n\r\n\r\n\rHowever, if you enter a negative quantity, thisindicates that items are being returned from the Destination Warehouseback to the Source Warehouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unitof Measure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdownlist to select a different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rServed Qty      \n\r\n\rShows how many units of the item have already been issued  or fulfilled. This field updates automatically when a Stock Requisition (RS) extracted to Stock Transfer (ST) module.  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rThe quantity is automatically converted to the base unit.  For example, if the conversion rate is 10 and the quantity is 3, the served  quantity will be 30 upon extraction to IS..        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese  columns are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s  setup or any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rD button      \n\r\n\rClick the D button to see which module the item has been extracted to   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the Requisition,press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 8.1 to 8.5. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To delete a line item, select itby clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete Item Entry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe Remarksfield to enter additional notes, or specific instructions related to therequisition, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Stock Requisition is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means all stockrequisitions will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the stock requisition associated with that identifier, while stillapplying any other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, or Destination.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosestock requisitions whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All stockrequisitions matching the Document ID and Document Range will be included,regardless of their date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the&quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Destination:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific destinationwarehouse, or If you leave it empty, all destination warehouse will beincluded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage, the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields for additionalinformation not covered by the standard fields. You can input specific databased on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract SR Entry Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract SR Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract SR Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Stock Requisition module. When youclick this button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as warehouses details, items,&nbsp;quantities andetc... and creates a new transaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transation as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Stock Requisition","topics\\Stock_Requisition_creating.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  14  26  2025-12-16T11:56:00Z  2025-12-18T06:31:00Z  3  483  2757  22  6  3234  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Stock Requisition / BatchPrinting\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the StockRequisition window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templates available,you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select the form you wantto use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure that your printedreport displays the proper layout, includes all the necessary fields, andfollows the intended formatting, so that the output matches your requirementsaccurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means all stockrequisitions will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the stock requisition associated with that identifier, while stillapplying any other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, Source or Destination.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Document Range: These fields let you specify thenumeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosestock requisitions whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Date Range:Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is not checked. This meansthe date range filter will be ignored. All stock requisitions matching theDocument ID and Document Range will be included, regardless of their date. Ifyou want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Source:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific source warehouse,or If you leave it empty, all source warehouse will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Destination:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific destinationwarehouse, or If you leave it empty, all destination warehouse will beincluded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the stock requisitions that match the currently set filter criteriabefore printing them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected thecorrect stock requisitions and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall stock requisitions that match the currently set filter criteria to theprinter.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Stock Requisitionwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing a Stock Requisition","topics\\Stock_Requisition_print.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  1  2025-12-16T11:55:00Z  2026-02-06T10:29:00Z  2  108  619  5  1  726  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the StockRequisition \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Stock Requisition fromthe Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the stockrequisition.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Stock Requisition","topics\\Stock_Requisition_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  user  4  1  2025-12-17T09:47:00Z  2025-12-22T07:51:00Z  1  53  308  2  1  360  16.00        Print  108  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness  Box - SQL version        \n\r\n\rSTOCK TRANSFER   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Stock Transfer module is a system thatallows warehouses or branches to transfer stock between locations efficientlyand accurately. It is used whenever items need to be moved from one branch to anotheror from the main warehouse to a branch, ensuring that inventory levels aremaintained where they are needed.","Stock Transfer","topics\\Stock_Transfer.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  17  36  2025-12-17T09:28:00Z  2026-02-24T10:03:00Z  15  2418  13785  114  32  16171  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rI.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to use Stock Transfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Stock Transfer from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Source Warehouse from which theitem will be released, and select the DestinationWarehouse to which the item should be delivered or transferred. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdownlist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number, thenumber field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, if applicable.This field is used to categorize the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Itemized data Grid, allows you to customize the layout byrearranging the columns according to your preference. To do this, click on thecolumn header using your optical mouse, hold theclick, and drag the header to the position you want. Once the column is in thedesired location, release the optical mouse button to set the new position.This feature helps you organize the grid in a way that makes it easier to viewand work with the data. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: These changes only affect your personalview of the grid and will not impact how other users see it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Addingand Deleting an Item Details:\n\r\n\r8.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifyou know the item code, you may enter it directly into the ItemCode field. If the item code does not exist, a list of itemswill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Availablefilter options: \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rHow to use the filters\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Tickthe box next to each filter you want to apply (Item Classification, Warehouse).\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Aftermaking your selections, click Requery button to refresh the list and apply the filters.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Thelist will now show only the items that match all of the filters you selected.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Ifyou expect to see an item but don’t find it, Check the item’s setting in itemmodule, possible filters are not set on that items.\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;PriceReference filter is not applicable on this module. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting item from the list:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe first few characters of the ItemCode, Abbreviation,Barcode or ItemDescription in the fields provided;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Entera specific code or word in the field provided (5 Search) to filter the Item Description;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Browsethe list using the scroll bar,keyboard arrow keys, or optical mouse scroll wheel.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherfields:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Stock on Hand - The total quantity of inventory recordedin the system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Available for Sales – refers to the quantity of inventorythat is currently eligible to be sold to customers according to system.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFormulafor Available for Sale:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAvailable for Sale = Stock on Hand + Pending Purchase Order – Pending Sales Order - Unposted Quantity \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote: Unposted quantity retrieve from following modules.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;DeliverReceipt \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;SalesInvoice (If not extracted from delivery receipt)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;ReceivingReport \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;PurchaseInvoice (If not extracted from receiving report)\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;InventoryAdjustment \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Issuance\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterselecting the Item from the Item list window, click the OKbutton. The selected Item will thenappear on the grid screen.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterthe required quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf you enter a positive quantity,this indicates that items are being released from the Source Warehouseand deliveredto the Destination Warehouse.\n\r\n\r\n\rHowever, if you enter a negative quantity, thisindicates that items are being returned from the Destination Warehouseback to the Source Warehouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Oncean item is selected, the default Unitof Measure (UOM) is automatically displayed. Click the dropdownlist to select a different UOM if necessary.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;MultipleUnit of Measure (UOMs) should be assigned in the Itemmodule so that you can select the appropriate UOM when usingthis module.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter additional notes or specialinstructions in Particulars columnthat related to the selected item, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Scrollto see the other available columns:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;     \n\r\n\rAvailable Columns      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rConversion      \n\r\n\rThis field  automatically shows the item’s default unit conversion.        \n\r\n\rCustom 1 – 5      \n\r\n\rThese columns  are reserved for additional information as defined by your company’s setup or  any other user-defined reference.        \n\r\n\rSR number      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Stock Requisition (SR) number  where the extracted details originated. This helps the user easily identify  which Stock Requisition was used as the source of the items shown in the  transaction.        \n\r\n\rPI number      \n\r\n\rDisplays the  Purchase Invoice (PI) number where  the extracted details originated. This helps the user easily identify which  Purchase Invoice was used as the source of the items shown in the  transaction.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add another item in the StockTransfer, press the Arrow Down key on your keyboard and repeat steps 8.1to 8.5. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAlternatively, using your optical mouse,select any column on the grid except theItem Code column, then right-clickanywhere within the module and choose AddItem Entry. A new line willappear, allowing you to add another item.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou can also use other options such as Vertical Entry or Filter Items, depending on your preferred method of adding items.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Todelete a line item, select it by clicking any column other than the Item Code column. Then, right-click using optical mouse and choose Delete ItemEntry.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe confirmation message may appear toensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the item or No tocancel the action.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Usethe Remarksfield to enter additional notes, or specific instructions related to the stocktransfer, if needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. The system automatically calculates the Total Quantity and Total Items once the Stock Transfer is saved. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. To modify anexisting record, click the Edit button. This will allow you to updatethe information as needed, and once finished, you can save your changes toapply them.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r13. To remove arecord from the system, click the Delete button. A confirmation messagemay appear to ensure you want to proceed—click Yes to delete the recordor No to cancel the action. This helps prevent accidental deletion ofimportant data.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar that located at the top of the window. And the BatchPosting window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use the available filters to retrieve thespecific transactions that you need.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means all stocktransfers will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the stock transaction associated with that identifier, while stillapplying any other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, or Destination.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentRange: These fields letyou specify the numeric range of document numbers you want to post (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosestock transfer whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DateRange: Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is notchecked. This means the date range filter will be ignored. All stock transfermatching the Document ID and Document Range will be included, regardless oftheir date. If you want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With daterange&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Destination:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific destination warehouse,or If you leave it empty, all destination warehouse will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Afterapplying the filters, At the bottom of this window, click the Requery buttonto refresh the grid and display only the unposted transactions that match yourselected criteria.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the checkboxes next to each document are selected, meaning alldocuments will be included in the batch posting unless you manually uncheckthem.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r14.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK toproceed with posting. Only the documents you have checked will be included inthe posting process. Click Cancel to close thebatch posting window without posting any transactions, and any selections youmade will be discarded.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r15. If you wish to cancel the transaction,click the Cancel button. Aconfirmation message may appear—click Yesto cancel the record or No to abortthe cancellation. This helps preventaccidental cancellation of important data. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUpon click Yes button on promptmessage, the Cancel document windowwill appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Enterthe date and reason for cancellation, then click OK to confirm the cancellation. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther Information Button:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r16. Click Other Information button, If needed. Andthe Other Information window willopen, this window provides additional details related to the transaction, suchas grouping, custom fields, posting, and cancellation records.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Groups (up to 5 dropdownlist) - This sectionallows you to categorize or group transactions for reporting or organizationalpurposes. You may select values from the dropdown lists as defined in yoursystem setup.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Custom Files (up to 5 text fields) - These are user-defined fields foradditional information not covered by the standard fields. You can inputspecific data based on your business requirements or processes.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Transaction Posting Details \n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Posted– Displays the date and time when the transaction was officially posted to thesystem.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Post User– Indicates the username of the person who posted the transaction\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Cancellation Details\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Date Cancelled – Displays the exact the date when thetransaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Cancel User – Shows the username of the person whoperformed the cancellation. This provides accountability and traceability.\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp;Reason of Cancellation – A text field where the user enters thejustification, notes, or remarks explaining why the transaction was cancelled.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rExtract ST Entry Button :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r17. Atthe lower portion of the module,Click Extract ST Entry Button, If needed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe Extract ST Entry button is used to copyor duplicate the current transaction under Stock Transfer module. When youclick this button, the system automatically extracts all information from theexisting transaction—such as warehouses details, items,&nbsp;quantities andetc.—and creates a new transaction entry with the same details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis function is useful for:\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Creatinga new transaction that has similar information to an existing one.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Savingtime by eliminating the need to re-encode the same data.\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Maintainingconsistency and accuracy in repeat or recurring transactions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rAfterextraction, you may edit or update the new transaction as needed (for example,changing the document date, quantities, or items) before saving it.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","I. How to use Stock Transfer","topics\\Stock_Transfer_creating.htm","   user  CCC_MARIENEL  6  46  2025-12-22T06:42:00Z  2026-02-24T10:04:00Z  4  543  3096  25  7  3632  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from Purchase Invoice moduleto Stock Transfer module\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Purchase Invoice module to theStock Transfer module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item detailsand quantities, making the delivery process faster, more accurate, and lessprone to errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Stock Transfer from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Source Warehouse from which theitem will be released, and select the DestinationWarehouse to which the item should be delivered or transferred. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdown list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, if applicable.This field is used to categorize the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract from Purchase Invoice then Search Document Number window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.1. Enter the document number in spaceprovided and the corresponding supplier will appear\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.2. Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding the extractions.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceedto update the required fields.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section&nbsp;I. Creating a Stock Transfer. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","V. Extraction from Purchase Invoice  to ST","topics\\Stock_Transfer_Extraction_from_PIST.htm","   user  CCC_MARIENEL  7  33  2025-12-22T05:47:00Z  2026-02-24T10:03:00Z  7  925  5279  43  12  6192  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIV.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extractions from&nbsp;Stock Requisitionmodule to Stock Transfer module \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis feature allows the system toautomatically transfer information from the Stock Requisition module to the StockTransfer module. By doing this, you avoid manually re-entering item details andquantities, making the delivery process faster, more accurate, and less proneto errors.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Stock Transfer from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Source Warehouse from which theitem will be released, and select the DestinationWarehouse to which the item should be delivered or transferred. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selecta Document ID from the dropdown list.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is set to auto number,the number field will be disabled, and the number will be automaticallygenerated when you save.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ifthe Document ID is not auto number,the number field will be enabled, allowing you to edit or change the number asneeded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enterdate on Document Date Field.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Selectthe Transaction Type, if applicable.This field is used to categorize the transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using optical mouse, right-click anywhere within the module and choose Extract from Stock Requistion then Extractions of Stock Requisition window will appear.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; The Extractions ofStock Requisition window has two main sections: the top grid shows a listof stock requisitions, and when you select one, the bottom grid displays all theitem details for that stock requisition.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Top Grid     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the  entire stock requisition for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDoc.ID      \n\r\n\rDocument type or ID of  the stock requisition.        \n\r\n\rDoc. No.      \n\r\n\rUnique stock  requisition number.        \n\r\n\rDoc. Date      \n\r\n\rDate the stock  requisition was created or any preferred date.        \n\r\n\rSource       \n\r\n\rRefers  to the warehouse where the item is released from.        \n\r\n\rDestination      \n\r\n\rRefers  to the warehouse where the item is delivered or transferred to.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rØ&nbsp; Bottom Grid – Item Details     \n\r\n\rColumn      \n\r\n\rDescription        \n\r\n\rX / Tag      \n\r\n\rTo check/mark the item for extraction.        \n\r\n\rDelivery Qty      \n\r\n\rQuantity that should be issued.        \n\r\n\rOrder Qty       \n\r\n\rQuantity originally ordered by the  employee.        \n\r\n\rPending Qty       \n\r\n\rThe Pending Qty  column shows the remaining quantity of the item available for delivery. When  creating a Stock Transfer, these  quantities are automatically converted to the base unit of  measure to ensure consistent and accurate inventory tracking,  and  to allow flexibility in case the unit of measure changes upon Transfer (e.g.,  an order for 3 boxes can be issued as 30 pieces).  \n\r\n\rExample:\n\r  If the pending quantity is 3 boxes  and 1  box = 10 pieces (base unit), the system converts 3  boxes into 30 pieces.         \n\r\n\rUOM      \n\r\n\rUnit of measure (e.g.,  pcs, box, kg).        \n\r\n\rItem Code      \n\r\n\rProduct or SKU code.        \n\r\n\rDescription      \n\r\n\rDescription of the item.   \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Filter by Item Classification: The system only displays stock requisitionsthat include at least one-line item with the chosen item classification, andthe bottom grid shows only the line items that match the filtered itemclassification.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Click Search Document to lookup a specific stock requisition transaction.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;TaggingStock Requisition for Extraction to Stock Transfer:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; To select an entire Stock Requisition,click the X next to the Doc.ID inthe top grid. All corresponding items in the bottom grid will automatically beselected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp; Toselect individual items within a Stock Requisition, first select the stockrequisition in the top grid, then in the bottom grid, either click the Xnext to each item or enter the delivery quantity.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click OK button to extracts the Details, Click the Cancel button to exit and discarding any selections you have made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.  Proceed to update the required fields.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r11. Click the Save button to save therecord. Click the Cancel button to discard the entry you have made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r12. Click the Post button in theNavigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rNote:\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Oncethe transaction has been posted, it is considered final and cannot be edited ordeleted.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rFor further explanation of the itemizedgrid, other fields and buttons, please refer to the Section&nbsp;I. Creating a Stock Transfer. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","IV. Extraction from Stock Requisition to ST","topics\\Stock_Transfer_extraction_SRST.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  4  10  2025-12-18T04:01:00Z  2025-12-18T06:31:00Z  3  477  2720  22  6  3191  16.00        Print  140  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rIII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Printing a Stock Transfer / BatchPrinting\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Print button in the Navigation Toolbar that locatedat the top of the window. And the StockTransfer window will appear. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bydefault, the ReportName field will automatically display the form that is mostappropriate for your report. However, if there are multiple report templates available,you will need to click the dropdown list and carefully select the form you wantto use. Choosing the correct form is important to ensure that your printedreport displays the proper layout, includes all the necessary fields, andfollows the intended formatting, so that the output matches your requirementsaccurately.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Use the available filters:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;DocumentID: You can set DocumentID to All, which means all stocktransfers will be included without restriction based on their uniqueidentifiers. However, if you want to focus on specific transactions, you canselect a particular Document ID, allowing the system to retrieve and displayonly the stock transfer associated with that identifier, while still applyingany other filters you may have set, such as Document Range, Date Range, Source or Destination.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Document Range: These fields let you specify thenumeric range of document numbers you want to print (Example: From 1 To 50 — means only thosestock transfers whose document number is between 1 and 50 will be included).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Date Range:Notice that the &quot;With date range&quot; checkbox is not checked. This meansthe date range filter will be ignored. All stock transfers matching theDocument ID and Document Range will be included, regardless of their date. Ifyou want to filter by date, you must check the &quot;With date range&quot; box.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Source:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific source warehouse,or If you leave it empty, all source warehouse will be included.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Destination:Click the dropdown list If you want to filter by a specific destinationwarehouse, or If you leave it empty, all destination warehouse will beincluded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Buttons:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Preview: This button allows you to view apreview of the stock transfers that match the currently set filter criteriabefore printing them. This is useful for verifying that you have selected thecorrect stock transfers and that the printed output will be as expected.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Print: This button initiates the batch printing process. It sendsall stock transfers that match the currently set filter criteria to theprinter.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rü&nbsp;Close: Click this button to exit the Stock Transferwindow.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;SampleOutput:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","III. Printing a Stock Transfer","topics\\Stock_Transfer_print.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  5  1  2025-12-18T04:00:00Z  2026-02-06T10:28:00Z  2  105  605  5  1  709  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n\r\n\rII.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Searching for a Transaction in the StockTransfer \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Stock Transfer fromthe Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Find button in the Navigation Toolbar. And enter the document number you wantto search in the space provided.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ClickOK button to display the stocktransfer.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","II. Searching for a Transaction in the Stock Transfer","topics\\Stock_Transfer_searching.htm","   CCC_MARIENEL  Normal  CCC_MARIENEL  28  125  2025-10-15T08:56:00Z  2025-11-03T05:18:00Z  16  1697  9677  80  22  11352  16.00        Print  Clean  Clean  false      false  false  false    EN-US  X-NONE  X-NONE            MicrosoftInternetExplorer4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \n\r\n\rBusiness Box - SQL  version        \n\r\n\rSUPPLIER    \n\r\n\rA supplieris an individual or organization that provides goods or services to thecompany. Suppliers are essential to business operations as they ensure theavailability of materials, products, or services required for daily activities.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIn this module, usersare allowed to create and maintain supplier records byentering the necessary details such as the supplier’s name, contactinformation, address, and tax identification number (TIN).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIt is important toensure that all supplier information entered is accurate andcomplete. This will help facilitate smooth purchasingtransactions, maintain proper documentation, and support effectivecommunication with suppliers.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding a Supplier\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select Supplier from the Menu and the module will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the New button in the Navigation Toolbar.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the SupplierCode and Supplier Name in their respective fields.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In General Section: \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.1. The&nbsp; Group is used to categorizesuppliers that have multiple branches. In some cases, one branch may handlepayments or transactions on behalf of other branches. When this occurs, thesesuppliers should be grouped accordingly to ensure accurate monitoring andproper transaction processing within the system.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.2. Enter the E-mail address,URL (Uniform Resource Locator), and TIN (Tax Identification Number), if any.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.3. Enter the BillingAddress, Contact Person, TelephoneNumber&nbsp;,&nbsp; andFax Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r4.4. Select the&nbsp; Areaand enter the Zip Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rAdding an Address:\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the magnifyingglass besides the Address label and the Address List window will open:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Addbutton to add a new address.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Address,Contact Person, Telephone Number and Fax Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Select the&nbsp; Areaand enter the Zip Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\re.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To addanother address follow steps&nbsp;a to d.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rf.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tick the “Default Billing Address” checkbox before saving to designate thisaddress as the most frequently used.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rg.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Close button toclose the window.&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enter the Particulars, if any. The Particulars may be any informationabout the supplier (i.e. Date when they become the company’s supplier, etc.)\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inthe Details section (Transaction Default Values):\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.1. Selectthe Transaction Type, ifany.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.2. Select the&nbsp; Currency Codeaccording to the supplier’s location or the currency used in the transaction.Make sure that the chosen code accurately reflects the currency applied forbilling and payment to ensure correct financial recording.&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.3. Select the&nbsp; Terms of Payment.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.4. Select the  Tax Code, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.5. Enter the Discounts, if any. Ifdiscount/s has been assigned to the supplier then upon transaction suchdiscount/s will be the default discount.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.6. Tick/Un-tick the box besides theTaxable label. When the supplier has been set as taxable then upon transaction(i.e. A/P Summary Entry) the VAT Inclusive box will have a check marker. Thismeans that the transaction is VAT Inclusive.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r6.7. Clickthe box besides the Require P.O. Number. If the feature is activatedthen upon transaction system will not allow empty P.O. Number.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Inthe Details section (Other Information):\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.1. &nbsp;Select the&nbsp; Company Class 1 to5, if any. The Company Class is use to classify the supplier’s transaction.These classifications are useful in report generation.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.2. &nbsp;Enter the CreditLimit, if any.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r7.3. &nbsp;Other fields include in thismodule. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOutstandingBalance&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Displays the total outstanding balance forthe selected supplier or vendor. This amount represents the total payable orunsettled transactions recorded in the system. This field is computer generatedand is automatically updated during transactions in the Purchase Invoice, APSummary Entry, Cash Disbursement modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTotalPurchase &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Displays the total net amount ofall purchases made from the selected supplier or vendor. This field is computergenerated and is automatically updated during transactions in the PurchaseInvoice and AP Summary Entry.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rStatus&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Indicateswhether the supplier/vendor is classified as Active, Inactive, orOn Hold.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Active\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; Thesupplier/vendor is available for normal use within the system.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; Canbe selected in all applicable modules such as Purchase Order, ReceivingReport, Purchase Invoice, AP Summary Entry, Cash Disbursement, and Accounts Payable Application.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;On Hold\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; Notransactions can be processed for this supplier in the Purchase Order, ReceivingReport, Purchase Invoice, and AP Summary Entry modules.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; Avalidation message will be displayed upon clicking the Save button.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; Statusis typically used for temporary restrictions.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rv&nbsp;Inactive\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; Thesupplier will not appear in the supplier selection lists in the PurchaseOrder, Receiving Report, Purchase Invoice, AP SummaryEntry, Cash Disbursement,and Accounts Payable Applicationmodules.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; Preventsthe creation of any new transactions involving this supplier.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp; Status is generally used when thesupplier relationship is permanently discontinued or no longer in use.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Clickthe Save button to save the record. Click the Cancel button todiscard changes made.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Click the Edit button toedit the record. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r10.Click the Delete button todelete the record. Deletion will only be allowed if thesaid record has not been used in other modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rInformation inputted canbe selected in the Purchase Order, Receiving Report, Purchase Invoice, AccountPayables Application, and Cash Disbursement modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;“ SAVE TO “ Feature\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIf you want a current Supplier to be included in the Customer, Agent orEmployee Lists, the **SAVE TO** feature maybe used. The **Save To** featureallows you to copy or extract supplier information to other modules such as Customer, Agent or Employee. Thisensures consistency of data across modules.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r(e.g.Save to Customer)\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r Click the     Save To button and the Save To window will appear.     Select the module to which the Supplier Information will be extracted. To     select, tick the circle besides     the Customer, Agent or Employee labels. \n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r Click the     OK button to save the supplier information. Click     the Cancel button to close the window. When you select     Customer and click the OK button the Customer module will open.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSince all pertinent information in the Supplierrecord has already been extracted, you only need to review the details andprovide any additional information required by the Salesdepartment.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r Click the Save button to     save the record. Click the Cancel button to discard changes made.\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rSearching a Supplier&nbsp; \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click the Find button in theNavigation Toolbar. The list of suppliers will appear.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ways of selecting Supplier from thelist.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Codein the space provided (1);\n\r\n\rb.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typethe first few characters of the Namein the space provided (2);\n\r\n\rc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Typea specific code or word in the space provided (3) to filter the Name;\n\r\n\rd.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Browsethrough the list using the ScrollBar or the keyboard arrowkeys or scroll wheel of opticalmouse.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After selecting the Supplier, click the OK button. The supplier’s details willbe displayed.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","Supplier","topics\\Supplier.htm");